1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:00,880
CHAPTER ONE

2
00:00:01,680 --> 00:00:02,800
Monkey's Story

3
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:11,280
Monkey pulled out some hairs from his chest 
and, crying 'Change!' threw them into the air.  

4
00:00:12,160 --> 00:00:15,920
At once, they became several 
hundred small monkeys.

5
00:00:18,320 --> 00:00:23,520
From the beginning of time, the rock was 
smoothed and cleaned by Heaven and Earth,  

6
00:00:24,160 --> 00:00:30,560
by the strong sun and the gentle moon, 
until one day it broke into two pieces  

7
00:00:30,560 --> 00:00:39,760
and gave birth to a stone egg, about as big as a 
child's ball. From the egg came a stone monkey.

8
00:00:41,120 --> 00:00:48,080
At once, this monkey learned to climb 
and run. But first, it looked north  

9
00:00:48,080 --> 00:00:56,080
and south and east and west. As it looked, 
a strange light came from its eyes.

10
00:00:56,960 --> 00:01:05,520
The light shone as far as the Jade Emperor, who 
sat in the Cloud Palace of the Golden Gates. The  

11
00:01:05,520 --> 00:01:12,400
Jade Emperor asked his ministers to open the gate 
of the Southern Heaven and look out at the light.

12
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:21,440
'This light,' reported the ministers, 
'comes from the small country of Ao-lai,  

13
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:25,840
to the east of the Mountain of Flowers and Fruit.'

14
00:01:26,800 --> 00:01:30,880
And in the country of Ao-lai, 
the monkey ran and jumped.  

15
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:37,200
He picked flowers, ate grass and fruit, 
and drank from streams and rivers.  

16
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:44,880
His friends were all the animals of that 
country, and the other monkeys were his family.  

17
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:54,320
At night, he slept among the rocks and 
in the day he walked through the caves.

18
00:01:54,320 --> 00:02:01,280
One day, the monkeys were washing in 
a stream when one of them spoke. 'None  

19
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:07,840
of us knows where this stream comes 
from. Let's follow it and find out.'

20
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:14,160
So they all ran up the stream until 
they came to a great waterfall.

21
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:23,680
The monkeys shouted, 'Lovely water, lovely 
water! It starts in a mountain cave and  

22
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:31,120
runs all the way to the Great Sea. Who can 
find the place where the water comes from?  

23
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:38,800
If one of us could find this place and 
return safely, we would make him our king!'

24
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:45,040
'I will go!' shouted the 
Stone Monkey. 'I will go!'

25
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:54,800
Look at him! He shuts his eyes, and with one 
big jump he passes through the curtain of water.  

26
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,640
But there is no water where he has landed.  

27
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:04,560
Instead he finds a great, shining 
iron bridge in front of him.

28
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:13,040
Monkey walked along the bridge and came to 
a cave. Outside the cave there was a sign:  

29
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:22,240
This Cave of the Water Curtain in the Country of 
the Mountain of Flowers and Fruit Leads to Heaven.

30
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:26,800
Monkey laughed and jumped with happiness.  

31
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:35,840
He ran back across the bridge, shut his eyes and 
jumped through the waterfall to the other monkeys.

32
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:43,120
'Good news!' he shouted. 'Good 
news! Come with me, all of you!'

33
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:48,960
They followed the Stone Monkey 
to the Cave of the Water Curtain.  

34
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:53,840
There the Stone Monkey sat 
down and talked to them.

35
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:59,840
'Gentlemen!' he said. 'I have 
been through the waterfall  

36
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:09,280
and have come back again. I have given you a 
home in this cave, so am I not your king now?'

37
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:18,000
The monkeys bowed to the Stone Monkey and they 
all cried, 'Great King for a thousand years!'  

38
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:28,160
The Stone Monkey became the Monkey King 
and he made other monkeys his ministers.

39
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:34,000
And all the monkeys were happy. During 
the day they walked and played on the  

40
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:39,600
Mountain of Flowers and Fruit, and 
at night they slept in the Cave  

41
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:46,880
of the Water Curtain. They had everything 
they wanted. Their lives were complete.

42
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:53,840
The Monkey King enjoyed this simple 
life for several hundred years.  

43
00:04:54,720 --> 00:05:01,040
But one day at a great party with all the 
other monkeys, he suddenly started to cry.

44
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:07,760
The other monkeys all bowed, 
saying, 'Why is our king so sad?'

45
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:19,040
'Today,' said the Monkey King, 'I am not sad. 
But I am worried about the future. Sadly, the  

46
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:28,160
time will come when I will become old and weak. 
Yama, King of Death, is waiting to destroy me.  

47
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:37,840
I do not want to be born again on Earth. How can 
I live for all time among the people of the sky?'

48
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:48,720
The monkeys all started to cry, each thinking of 
his own mortality. One of them said, 'Only Buddhas  

49
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:55,600
and Immortals do not go to Yama, King 
of Death. Only they live forever.'

50
00:05:56,880 --> 00:06:01,680
'Where can I find these 
Immortals?' asked the Monkey King.

51
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:07,600
'Here on Earth they live in 
very old caves far to the West.'

52
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:17,600
'Tomorrow,' said the Monkey King, 'I shall say 
goodbye to you. I shall go down the mountain and  

53
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:25,440
travel to the end of the world. I want to learn 
to live for all time and to escape from death.'

54
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:35,840
Next morning, he walked to the sea and sailed in 
a boat to the borders of the Southern World. There  

55
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:45,520
he climbed out on to the beach. And then he walked 
and walked, through towns and cities, to the West.

56
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:54,880
On the way, he learned to wear clothes and 
to behave like a human. But he met humans  

57
00:06:54,880 --> 00:07:01,840
who wanted only to be rich and famous. He 
met nobody who worried about his mortality.

58
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:11,680
One day, he came to the Western Ocean, where 
he built another boat. Then he sailed to the  

59
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:20,160
Western Continent, where he saw a very high 
and beautiful wooded mountain. At the top  

60
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:27,120
of the mountain was the Cave of the Moon and 
Three Stars, where the Immortal Subodhi lived.

61
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:33,200
Monkey at once bowed and touched the 
ground with his head three times.

62
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:38,560
'Where do you come from?' asked the Immortal.

63
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:42,160
'I am from the Cave of the Water Curtain,'  

64
00:07:42,160 --> 00:07:47,200
said Monkey, 'on the Mountain of Flowers 
and Fruit in the country of Ao-lai.'

65
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:51,840
'That is impossible!' shouted the Immortal.  

66
00:07:52,480 --> 00:08:00,160
'Between there and here are two oceans and the 
whole of the Southern Continent. You are lying!'

67
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:06,240
'I have sailed across the oceans and 
walked over the continents for more  

68
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:11,840
than ten years,' said Monkey. 
'At last I have reached here.'

69
00:08:13,440 --> 00:08:17,520
Monkey told the Immortal how 
he had come from a magic stone.  

70
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:23,600
The Immortal thought that Monkey was 
a natural product of Heaven and Earth,  

71
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:29,600
so he agreed to teach him. Monkey 
jumped up and down with happiness.

72
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:39,200
Day after day, he and the other students learned 
to speak and behave correctly. They learned to  

73
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:46,800
write well and to study the Scriptures. When they 
were not studying, the students grew flowers and  

74
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:55,520
trees. They lit fires and fetched water. And so 
Monkey lived in this way for six or seven years.

75
00:08:56,880 --> 00:09:00,960
Finally, the Immortal sent 
for Monkey late one night  

76
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:04,880
because he wanted to teach 
him the Way of Long Life.

77
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:11,600
'Come close and listen 
carefully,' said the Immortal.

78
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:18,720
Monkey went down on his knees on the floor 
at the Immortal's feet, listening carefully.  

79
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:30,400
The Immortal recited a magic poem with many lines. 
The words shook Monkey's soul and he was never the  

80
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:38,880
same Monkey again. He thanked the Immortal many 
times, because now he knew the Way of Long Life.

81
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:48,080
Time passed quickly and three years later the 
Immortal again invited Monkey to his room,  

82
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:57,200
where he taught him seventy-two transformations. 
Monkey was a quick learner and he practised until  

83
00:09:57,200 --> 00:10:03,840
he could change himself into something 
else, using all seventy-two ways.

84
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:09,840
One day, when the Immortal and his 
students were in front of the cave  

85
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:18,640
admiring the evening view, the Immortal spoke 
to Monkey. 'Monkey, how much have you learned?'

86
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:23,680
'Thanks to you,' said Monkey, 
'I have learned a lot.  

87
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:29,520
In addition to changing myself into 
other forms, I can already fly.'

88
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:34,480
'Let me see you do it,' said the Immortal.

89
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:42,240
Monkey put his feet together, jumped twenty 
metres into the air and rode the clouds for a  

90
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:49,280
few minutes. Then he dropped to the ground, 
saying, 'You see, I can ride the clouds.'

91
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:58,560
'That is not riding the clouds,' said the 
Immortal, laughing. 'A real cloud-rider  

92
00:10:58,560 --> 00:11:01,760
can start in the morning from the Northern Sea,  

93
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:10,000
cross the Eastern, the Western and the 
Southern Seas and land again in one day.'

94
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:14,320
'It sounds very difficult,' said Monkey.

95
00:11:15,040 --> 00:11:22,880
'Nothing in the world is difficult,' said the 
Immortal. 'Only our own thoughts make things  

96
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:30,720
seem difficult. Now I will teach you 
to fly from one continent to another.'

97
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:37,600
The other students laughed, saying, 
'If Monkey flies all that way,  

98
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:41,920
he will be able to earn a living as a postman.'

99
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:46,000
But Monkey spent all night practising 
what the Immortal had taught him.

100
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:50,880
By morning he could fly wherever he wanted.

101
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:56,720
One summer day, some students 
were sitting under a tree.  

102
00:11:57,760 --> 00:12:04,320
A student said, 'Monkey, why do you 
deserve private teaching by the Immortal?  

103
00:12:05,040 --> 00:12:09,840
Has he taught you the transformations, 
by all the seventy-two ways?'

104
00:12:10,640 --> 00:12:16,720
'I have been working on them day and night 
and now I can do them all,' said Monkey.

105
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:18,800
'Could you show us?'

106
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:28,800
Proudly, Monkey made a magic sign, said some 
magic words and transformed himself into a tree.

107
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:36,560
'Well done, Monkey, well done!' shouted 
the other students. They all laughed.

108
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:42,240
The Immortal heard their laughter and 
he came running out from the cave.

109
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:47,760
'Who is making all this noise?' he asked.

110
00:12:48,720 --> 00:12:55,680
Monkey changed himself back from a tree to 
a monkey. He sat with the students again  

111
00:12:55,680 --> 00:13:00,240
and said, 'Immortal, we are 
practising our lessons out here.'

112
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:08,320
'You were all shouting and laughing!' said 
the Immortal, angrily. 'I want to know why.'

113
00:13:09,920 --> 00:13:16,960
Then one student said, 'Monkey was transforming 
himself into a tree, just for fun.'

114
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:23,440
'You, Monkey, come here!' shouted the Immortal.  

115
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:31,440
'Why do you think I taught you these secrets 
of life? So you can make other people laugh?'

116
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:36,000
'I am very sorry,' said Monkey.

117
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:45,840
'I will not punish you,' said the Immortal. 
'But you cannot stay here. You must leave us.'

118
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:52,400
Monkey started to cry. 'Where can I go?' he asked.

119
00:13:53,760 --> 00:14:01,120
'Go back to where you came from. Go as 
quickly as you can. Never tell anyone  

120
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:07,600
that you were a student of mine. I am 
sure that no good will come of your life.'

121
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:17,440
And so poor Monkey said goodbye to everybody. 
He flew back to the Eastern Sea and his home  

122
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:21,440
in the Cave of the Water Curtain on 
the Mountain of Flowers and Fruit.

123
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:27,920
'Little ones,' shouted the 
Monkey King, 'I have come back!'

124
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:36,880
At once, big and small monkeys leapt out of 
trees with cries of 'Long live our King!'  

125
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:44,800
Then, pushing each other to get near him, 
they cried, 'Why did you go for so long?  

126
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:52,080
We have been watching for your return day 
after day! While you were away, a demon took  

127
00:14:52,080 --> 00:15:00,720
our cave and everything we own and many of our 
children. Now we dare not sleep, night or day.'

128
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:08,480
'What demon dares to do this?' 
cried Monkey. 'I will make him pay!'

129
00:15:09,840 --> 00:15:12,880
'King, he is called the Destroying Demon,  

130
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:20,240
and he lives north of here. But he 
comes and goes like a cloud, like wind,  

131
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:27,600
like rain, like thunder and lightning, so we 
do not know where his home is or how far away.'

132
00:15:28,880 --> 00:15:33,920
'Well, don't worry,' said Monkey. 
'I will go and look for him.'

133
00:15:35,280 --> 00:15:43,440
Dear Monkey! He leapt into the sky and 
soon saw in front of him a high mountain  

134
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:47,600
and a cave, where the Destroying 
Demon was waiting for him.

135
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:54,240
'Where is the owner of the Cave of 
the Water Curtain?' cried the Demon.

136
00:15:55,440 --> 00:16:02,080
'You have such large eyes,' shouted 
Monkey, 'but you cannot see Monkey?'

137
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:06,320
'Oh! You are not half a metre high!  

138
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:12,400
If I killed such a small creature 
with my sword, I would look foolish.'

139
00:16:13,920 --> 00:16:20,960
So the two of them fought with their hands and 
feet, hitting and kicking each other. Soon the  

140
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:29,440
Demon was fighting like a wild animal. Monkey 
pulled out some hairs from his chest and, crying  

141
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:37,280
'Change!' threw them into the air. At once, 
they became several hundred small monkeys.

142
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:42,880
See how the monkeys jump on the 
Demon, pulling and hitting him.  

143
00:16:43,840 --> 00:16:51,280
Then Monkey takes up the Demon's great sword and 
brings it down on his head, breaking it in two.  

144
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:58,400
Then, by his magic, he transforms 
all the monkeys back into hairs.

145
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:04,880
When Monkey returned home to the cave 
on the Mountain of Flowers and Fruit,  

146
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:08,640
he brought the great sword 
of the Destroying Demon,  

147
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:14,320
and he amused the other monkeys by 
teaching them to make weapons of wood.

148
00:17:15,840 --> 00:17:20,960
Then, one day, the Monkey King 
called all the other monkeys to him.

149
00:17:22,640 --> 00:17:26,320
'All this,' he said, pointing 
to their wooden weapons,  

150
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:33,120
'is only a game. We cannot defend 
ourselves from a real enemy with these.'

151
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:42,000
'We know a city that is full of soldiers. They 
must have plenty of weapons,' the others said.  

152
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:45,840
They quickly told Monkey where it was.

153
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:52,480
'Stay here and amuse yourselves,' 
Monkey said. 'I will see what I can do.'  

154
00:17:54,320 --> 00:18:03,280
Dear Monkey! Using his magic, he flew to the city 
and, with his breath, blew such a strong wind that  

155
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:11,200
all the people locked themselves indoors. This was 
his chance. He found where the weapons were kept,  

156
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:19,200
kicked down the door, and changed his hairs into 
thousands of small monkeys who took the weapons.  

157
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:24,560
Carried on a magic wind, they 
were soon back at the cave.

158
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:28,640
The monkeys learned to use the weapons,  

159
00:18:29,360 --> 00:18:36,400
and all sorts of wild animals and demon 
kings began to call Monkey their king.

160
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:41,840
But Monkey found his own weapon too heavy,  

161
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:50,720
so he went to the Dragon of the Eastern Sea in 
search of something lighter. The Dragon King  

162
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:57,840
welcomed him to the palace, with his dragon 
children, dragon grandchildren and fish soldiers.

163
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:05,920
Monkey made his request, and a fish 
soldier brought out a great sword.

164
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,840
'Too heavy,' said Monkey.

165
00:19:11,360 --> 00:19:14,880
More fish soldiers brought out an enormous fork.

166
00:19:16,720 --> 00:19:18,720
'Too light,' said Monkey.

167
00:19:19,840 --> 00:19:22,160
The dragon mother and her daughter  

168
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:28,160
came from a back room in the palace 
and suggested their magic iron cudgel.

169
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:33,440
'The Gods used it when they 
decided how deep the rivers  

170
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:39,680
and the seas should be,' said the Dragon 
King. He agreed that Monkey should have it.

171
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:46,560
When it was brought, Monkey saw that it 
was a thick piece of iron six metres long.  

172
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:52,240
He used his magic to bring 
it down to less than a metre.  

173
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:57,680
Then he waved it over his head, striking 
terror into everybody in the room.

174
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:03,440
But now he demanded something 
to wear, to go with the weapon,  

175
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:14,720
and this was too much. A pair of cloud-stepping 
shoes, a cap of red gold and a coat of light metal  

176
00:20:14,720 --> 00:20:22,160
were brought to him, but the angry Dragon King 
also sent for his brothers from the Southern,  

177
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:27,600
Northern and Western Seas and told 
them about Monkey's many requests.

178
00:20:29,040 --> 00:20:35,200
The Dragon of the South was angry. 
'Put him in prison!' he cried.

179
00:20:35,760 --> 00:20:38,800
'No, no,' warned the Dragon King.  

180
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:46,320
'We cannot go near him now. If he touches 
us with that iron cudgel, he will kill us.  

181
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:54,960
Let him keep the clothes. We will complain 
to Heaven, and Heaven will punish him.'

182
00:20:56,720 --> 00:21:02,240
Monkey took the clothes, but he knew that 
they were going to complain about him.

183
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:10,720
Soon after that, the Jade Emperor received the 
complaint from the Dragon of the Eastern Sea.

184
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:16,560
'How long,' the Jade Emperor asked his ministers,  

185
00:21:17,120 --> 00:21:22,720
'has this Monkey existed, and why 
does he behave like an Immortal?'

186
00:21:24,080 --> 00:21:31,840
'In the last three hundred years, he has 
learned a lot,' said a minister. 'Let's  

187
00:21:31,840 --> 00:21:36,640
give him work here in Heaven where 
we will be able to watch hint.'

188
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:43,840
This suggestion pleased the Jade Emperor, and 
a minister was sent to bring Monkey to Heaven.  

189
00:21:44,960 --> 00:21:50,800
Monkey tidied his clothes, told the older 
monkeys to look after the younger ones,  

190
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:52,880
and followed the minister to Heaven.

191
00:21:54,720 --> 00:21:59,520
'I am going to give you a job,' 
said the Jade Emperor to Monkey.  

192
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:03,520
'You are going to look after the Apple Garden.'

193
00:22:05,120 --> 00:22:13,280
Monkey was very happy and ran to the Apple Garden 
to start work. He was told that on the outer side  

194
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:20,480
of the garden were special apples. They were 
ready to eat once in three thousand years.  

195
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:28,960
If you ate one of these, you would become wise, 
with strong arms and legs and a light body.  

196
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:37,440
In the middle were trees with apples that 
were ready to eat once in six thousand years.  

197
00:22:38,560 --> 00:22:44,880
If you ate these, you would go up in the air 
and stay there, and would never grow old.  

198
00:22:46,320 --> 00:22:53,840
At the back were trees with apples chat were 
ready to eat once in nine thousand years.  

199
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:59,920
If you ate these, you would live 
longer than Heaven and Earth.

200
00:23:01,760 --> 00:23:04,320
Monkey was very happy with this information.  

201
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:12,240
He watched the trees closely, making up his mind 
to eat the fruit before anybody else got a chance.

202
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:19,760
Soon, noticing that some apples were 
ready to eat, he sent his helpers away.

203
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:26,240
He climbed into a high tree and 
ate until he could eat no more.

204
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:32,000
When the Queen of Heaven sent 
her lady assistants for apples,  

205
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:35,840
they were turned away at the 
gates by Monkey's helpers.  

206
00:23:37,120 --> 00:23:43,040
'We must ask the Monkey King first,' they 
said. 'He is resting in one of the trees.'

207
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:51,840
But when they came to the tree, they found only 
Monkey's cap and shoes. They could not see him.  

208
00:23:53,040 --> 00:24:00,560
In fact, Monkey had made himself five 
centimetres long and was asleep under a leaf.

209
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:09,040
The Queen of Heaven's lady assistants picked three 
basketfuls from each of the first two groups of  

210
00:24:09,040 --> 00:24:18,000
trees. When they came to the third, they found 
just one apple. When one of the ladies tried to  

211
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:23,440
pick it, Monkey woke up. At once, 
he changed back to his true size.

212
00:24:24,560 --> 00:24:27,040
'Who are you?' shouted Monkey.

213
00:24:28,080 --> 00:24:33,840
The lady assistants went down on their 
knees. 'Monkey King, don't be angry.  

214
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:40,240
We were sent by the Queen and we could 
not find you. Please forgive us.'

215
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:48,640
'Get up from your knees,' said Monkey, 
his voice full of kindness. 'I have  

216
00:24:48,640 --> 00:24:54,800
heard that the Queen of Heaven is having a 
banquet. Can you tell me who is invited?'

217
00:24:57,040 --> 00:25:02,960
Monkey was told that all the Immortals, 
Emperors of the Four Quarters and Gods  

218
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:09,840
of the seas and hills would be there. He 
immediately asked, 'Will I be invited?'

219
00:25:11,120 --> 00:25:17,200
'I have not heard,' said one of the 
lady assistants. 'We do not know.'

220
00:25:18,800 --> 00:25:24,400
'Quite right, ladies,' said Monkey. 
'Just wait here while I go and see.'

221
00:25:26,320 --> 00:25:32,640
Dear Monkey! He recited some 
magic lines, crying 'Stay, stay,  

222
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:41,840
stay!' The lady assistants were suddenly unable 
to move while he went off on his magic cloud.

223
00:25:43,360 --> 00:25:48,880
No one had arrived at the banquet yet, 
but Monkey could smell the food and wine.  

224
00:25:49,760 --> 00:25:56,640
He sent the servants to sleep by magic. Look 
at them, how their hands fall to their sides,  

225
00:25:57,280 --> 00:26:06,560
their heads drop on to their chests, their 
eyes close! Monkey then took some of the  

226
00:26:06,560 --> 00:26:14,320
finest and best of the food and drank glass 
after glass of wine until he was quite drunk.

227
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:18,960
'Bad! Bad!'  

228
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:28,960
he thought to himself. 'I will certainly get 
into trouble, so I will go home and sleep.'

229
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:32,160
But it was too late for that.

230
00:26:33,440 --> 00:26:37,840
Back at the Apple Garden, the 
Queen's ladies were finally saved.  

231
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:45,040
They reported that the Monkey King had eaten many 
of the biggest apples and had now disappeared.

232
00:26:47,360 --> 00:26:54,960
When the great Goddess Kuan-yin arrived for 
the banquet, she found half the food eaten and  

233
00:26:54,960 --> 00:27:01,920
all the wine gone. When the servants were 
woken, they explained that the Monkey King  

234
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:07,520
had sent them to sleep. That was the last 
time they had seen the food and the wine.  

235
00:27:08,640 --> 00:27:14,160
The Jade Emperor was informed and he 
sent heavenly soldiers to find Monkey.

236
00:27:15,840 --> 00:27:21,920
Monkey was burned in fire for nine 
days, and at the end of it his  

237
00:27:21,920 --> 00:27:29,040
eyes were red but he was still alive. He 
was attacked with swords and the Gods of  

238
00:27:29,040 --> 00:27:33,840
Thunder threw thunder at him. 
But nothing could destroy him.

239
00:27:35,200 --> 00:27:42,720
In the end, hearing of this situation, the great 
Buddha himself arrived and called Monkey to him.  

240
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:51,600
'How long ago,' he asked him, 'did you 
try to become an Immortal and learn  

241
00:27:51,600 --> 00:27:55,280
the things that make you dare behave like this?'

242
00:27:56,960 --> 00:27:58,960
Monkey at once recited:

243
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:03,920
Born of Earth and Sky, I am a magic Immortal.

244
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:08,000
I am an old monkey from the 
Mountain of Flowers and Fruit;

245
00:28:08,800 --> 00:28:13,120
In the Cave of the Water Curtain, 
I work and laugh and play.

246
00:28:14,240 --> 00:28:18,160
I found a friend and teacher 
who taught me the Great Secret;

247
00:28:19,040 --> 00:28:23,200
I made myself perfect in the Ways of Immortality,

248
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:26,400
I learned transformations without limit or end,

249
00:28:27,200 --> 00:28:32,000
I tired of the narrow world of 
men, and lived in the Jade Heaven.

250
00:28:32,960 --> 00:28:36,400
But why should Heaven's 
palace have only one emperor?

251
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:42,240
On Earth king follows king, as 
the strong bow to the stronger.

252
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:46,400
Only a hero fights with the Gods of Gods.

253
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:49,920
That was what Monkey recited.  

254
00:28:51,360 --> 00:28:59,600
Buddha laughed. 'But you are only a 
monkey-spirit,' he said. 'The Jade Emperor  

255
00:28:59,600 --> 00:29:07,280
has been making himself perfect for countless 
years. How can you hope to take his place and  

256
00:29:07,280 --> 00:29:15,920
become emperor yourself? You are only an animal 
that looks half human! Talk no more of this.'

257
00:29:17,760 --> 00:29:23,760
'Why should he be emperor for all time? 
Tell him to go and to give me my chance,'  

258
00:29:24,480 --> 00:29:31,920
said Monkey. 'That is all I ask. And if he will 
not, I will see that he never has any peace.'

259
00:29:33,520 --> 00:29:39,440
'What magic have you got that would 
help you to take Heaven for yourself?'

260
00:29:39,440 --> 00:29:46,320
'I have a lot of magic,' replied Monkey. 'I 
can jump through the clouds from continent  

261
00:29:46,320 --> 00:29:51,120
to continent. Am I not good enough 
to live in the palaces of Heaven?'  

262
00:29:52,640 --> 00:30:02,480
Buddha said, 'If you are really so clever, you 
will sit here in my right hand and then jump off.  

263
00:30:03,200 --> 00:30:11,760
If you succeed, you can become the Jade Emperor. 
But if you fail, you will go back to Earth  

264
00:30:11,760 --> 00:30:14,400
and you will be punished for centuries.'

265
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:23,040
Monkey thought, 'This Buddha is a complete 
fool. How could I fail to jump off his hand!'

266
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:30,240
Buddha held out his hand, which 
looked about the size of a large leaf.  

267
00:30:31,440 --> 00:30:35,840
Monkey took the magic iron cudgel 
that the Dragon King had given him,  

268
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:40,000
and that he had transformed into 
a stick the size of a needle.  

269
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:47,840
He put it behind his ear and then he jumped 
from the hand as far and as fast as he could.

270
00:30:49,040 --> 00:30:54,000
He was flying very fast, but Buddha 
watched him with the eye of wisdom.  

271
00:30:55,200 --> 00:30:59,280
Monkey came at last to five high pink towers.

272
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:08,080
'This must be the end of the world,' said 
Monkey to himself. 'Now I will return to Buddha,  

273
00:31:08,640 --> 00:31:16,240
become emperor, and all Heaven will be mine. But 
I had better leave some sign that I was here.'

274
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:22,960
Pulling out a hair, he changed it 
into a writing-brush heavy with ink,  

275
00:31:23,760 --> 00:31:31,840
and at the bottom of the middle tower he wrote: 
The great Monkey King reached this place.  

276
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:35,440
Then he jumped back to where he had come from.

277
00:31:36,640 --> 00:31:38,880
Standing on Buddha's hand, he said,  

278
00:31:40,080 --> 00:31:46,480
'I have gone and I have returned. You can 
tell the Jade Emperor that his job is mine.'

279
00:31:47,840 --> 00:31:55,760
'You smelly creature,' said Buddha, 
'you have been on my hand all the time.'

280
00:31:56,640 --> 00:32:02,400
'You are completely wrong,' said Monkey. 
'I travelled to the end of the world,  

281
00:32:02,400 --> 00:32:09,120
saw five pink towers and wrote on one of them. 
Would you like me to take you and show you?'

282
00:32:10,560 --> 00:32:14,720
'No need,' said Buddha. 'Just look down.'

283
00:32:16,160 --> 00:32:21,280
Monkey looked down, with his eyes 
still red from the nine days of fire.

284
00:32:22,560 --> 00:32:26,400
There, at the bottom of the 
middle finger of Buddha's hand,  

285
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:32,400
he saw the words "The great 
Monkey King reached this place."

286
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:39,760
Monkey could not speak and his 
red eyes opened wide in surprise.  

287
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:49,440
At last he said, 'Impossible! Impossible! I 
wrote that on a tower going high into the sky.  

288
00:32:50,560 --> 00:32:56,800
How did it get on the Buddha's finger? 
It is magic! I shall go back to look!'

289
00:32:58,240 --> 00:33:04,640
Dear Monkey! He was preparing to jump again 
when Buddha pushed him out of the Western  

290
00:33:04,640 --> 00:33:12,720
Gate of Heaven. As he did, he changed 
his five fingers into Metal, Wood, Water,  

291
00:33:13,360 --> 00:33:23,920
Fire and Earth. They became a mountain which 
pressed poor Monkey down with its great weight.

292
00:33:23,920 --> 00:33:31,840
The name Mountain of Metal, Wood, Water, Fire and 
Earth was written on a large rock on the mountain.  

293
00:33:33,200 --> 00:33:38,000
Under the mountain there was 
enough air for Monkey to breathe,  

294
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:42,400
but no opening which Monkey's head 
or hand could squeeze through.

295
00:33:44,400 --> 00:33:49,680
Buddha then told a spirit to look after 
Monkey and give him food and drink.

296
00:33:50,960 --> 00:33:58,480
'And when the days of his punishment are 
finished,' said Buddha, 'a man will come here  

297
00:33:59,280 --> 00:34:00,000
and save him.'

298
00:34:01,840 --> 00:34:11,200
Time passed, and then one day the Buddha said to 
his followers, 'I have noticed a lot of difference  

299
00:34:11,200 --> 00:34:19,040
between the people who live in the four continents 
of the world. The people in the East are polite,  

300
00:34:19,680 --> 00:34:28,320
peaceful and cheerful. People in the North 
are lazy and stupid, so do little harm.  

301
00:34:29,360 --> 00:34:38,240
In our Western Continent, there is no killing, 
although there is little real wisdom. But in the  

302
00:34:38,240 --> 00:34:47,840
South, they are greedy and murderous. A knowledge 
of the True Scriptures might improve them.'

303
00:34:49,280 --> 00:34:52,560
'Do you have these Scriptures?' 
asked his followers.

304
00:34:53,760 --> 00:35:03,360
'Yes, three baskets of them,' said Buddha. 'One 
speaks of Heaven, another of Earth, and a third  

305
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:12,240
can save people from the Wrong Way. These are the 
path to perfection, the only gate to the True Way.  

306
00:35:13,600 --> 00:35:22,080
But down in the real world, people are so stupid 
that they laugh at them. I need to find someone  

307
00:35:22,080 --> 00:35:29,840
who will go to the Eastern land. There he might 
find a believer who could come here from China.

308
00:35:30,800 --> 00:35:33,840
I would give this believer the Scriptures  

309
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:38,480
to take back to China and change 
the hearts of the people.'

310
00:35:41,200 --> 00:35:45,600
The Goddess Kuan-yin came 
forward and bowed three times.

311
00:35:46,960 --> 00:35:52,080
'I would like to go to the Eastern land 
and find someone to fetch the Scriptures.'

312
00:35:53,600 --> 00:35:58,160
'Who would be better than you!' said Buddha.

313
00:35:58,160 --> 00:36:01,440
So Kuan-yin called her bodyguard, Hui-yen,  

314
00:36:02,240 --> 00:36:06,640
who carried a great iron cudgel, 
and they started at once.

315
00:36:08,240 --> 00:36:14,240
After they had travelled a long way, 
they came to the River of Sands. There,  

316
00:36:14,240 --> 00:36:20,560
a horribly ugly creature leapt out of the water 
and began a terrible fight with the bodyguard.

317
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:27,520
Suddenly, the creature stopped fighting, 
looked hard at the bodyguard and asked, 'Who  

318
00:36:27,520 --> 00:36:34,800
dares to fight with me? Surely I have seen you 
before in the gardens of the Goddess Kuan-yin?'

319
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:41,440
'The Goddess herself is here, in 
front of you,' Hui-yen replied.

320
00:36:42,800 --> 00:36:50,320
'I ask you to forgive me!' cried the creature. 
'I am not really the ugly creature that you see.  

321
00:36:51,120 --> 00:36:56,960
I was given this horrible shape as a 
punishment for a crime that I did in Heaven.  

322
00:36:57,840 --> 00:37:05,200
I was sent to the world below, where I am always 
hungry and I must attack travellers and eat them.'

323
00:37:06,640 --> 00:37:10,800
'But you are adding new crimes 
on Earth to your crime in Heaven  

324
00:37:10,800 --> 00:37:14,160
by killing people,' said the Goddess Kuan-yin.

325
00:37:14,960 --> 00:37:19,280
'Why not come with us? If 
our journey is successful,  

326
00:37:19,280 --> 00:37:22,800
you will be forgiven and 
allowed to return to Heaven.'

327
00:37:24,960 --> 00:37:31,520
'I would gladly go back,' the creature 
answered. 'But I have eaten so many humans.  

328
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:37,760
Even now, nine heads are lying on 
the waters of the River of Sands.  

329
00:37:38,560 --> 00:37:45,200
I have played games with them and I do not think 
I will be allowed back into Heaven after that.'

330
00:37:46,640 --> 00:37:52,480
'Don't be silly,' she replied. 'Take 
the heads and hang them round your neck.

331
00:37:53,440 --> 00:37:58,080
I shall make you a priest and 
give you the name "Sandy Priest".

332
00:37:59,040 --> 00:38:06,240
Wait here and never again take a human life. 
You will see that a man will come this way.  

333
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:12,560
He will be looking for the Scriptures and a 
good use will be found for the nine heads.'

334
00:38:14,560 --> 00:38:20,880
So the Goddess and her bodyguard continued 
their journey and came to a high mountain  

335
00:38:21,520 --> 00:38:28,000
with a most horrible smell. A 
dirty, smelly, piglike creature  

336
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:34,240
leapt out and attacked Kuan-yin with a great 
fork and fought hard with her bodyguard.

337
00:38:35,680 --> 00:38:39,600
For safety, Kuan-yin stood in the sky above them  

338
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:45,840
and then threw down flowers, which fell 
between the bodyguard's cudgel and the fork.

339
00:38:46,640 --> 00:38:51,440
'Fighting with flowers?' cried the 
pig. 'What kind of priest are you?'

340
00:38:52,960 --> 00:38:57,120
'The great Goddess Kuan-yin threw 
them down on us from her cloud,  

341
00:38:57,120 --> 00:38:59,840
where she is standing,' replied the bodyguard.

342
00:39:01,040 --> 00:39:07,600
At once, the pig bowed to the sky. 
'Forgive me, Goddess, forgive me!  

343
00:39:08,240 --> 00:39:15,200
I am not really a pig at all. For a crime in 
Heaven, the Jade Emperor sent me down here.'

344
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:24,160
'This is a chance for you,' said Kuan-yin. 'We 
are on our way to China to look for a man who  

345
00:39:24,160 --> 00:39:31,760
will collect the Scriptures. If you went with 
him to India, we would forgive all your crimes.'

346
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:37,120
'I will! I will!' the pig-like creature shouted.

347
00:39:38,320 --> 00:39:40,960
So they gave him the name of Pigsy,  

348
00:39:41,600 --> 00:39:45,840
and left him to watch for the pilgrim 
who would collect the Scriptures.

349
00:39:47,520 --> 00:39:50,720
The Goddess and her bodyguard went on their way  

350
00:39:51,440 --> 00:39:55,840
and soon they met a dragon who 
had fought against the Gods.

351
00:39:56,560 --> 00:40:00,080
'Can you help me?' the dragon cried out.

352
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:06,800
Kuan-yin went back to Heaven. She 
asked the Gods to forgive the dragon  

353
00:40:06,800 --> 00:40:12,800
if he would transform himself into a white 
horse and carry the pilgrim to India.

354
00:40:14,720 --> 00:40:18,560
Continuing their journey, 
the Goddess and her bodyguard  

355
00:40:18,560 --> 00:40:25,040
suddenly saw a mountain covered in magic 
fog and lit by golden light from Heaven.  

356
00:40:26,240 --> 00:40:30,480
They recognised it at once as the 
mountain which covered the Monkey King.

357
00:40:32,080 --> 00:40:34,400
Kuan-yin looked sad and recited:

358
00:40:35,440 --> 00:40:38,320
Long ago he was purposelessly brave.

359
00:40:39,280 --> 00:40:43,760
In his blackness of heart he 
spoiled the Heavenly Apple Banquet

360
00:40:43,760 --> 00:40:46,880
And tried to take the place of the Jade Emperor.

361
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:51,840
Will he ever again be free and win back his name?

362
00:40:53,760 --> 00:41:00,080
Then came a voice from inside the mountain: 
'Who is reciting a list of my crimes?'

363
00:41:01,440 --> 00:41:04,640
Kuan-yin found the spirit who looked after Monkey.  

364
00:41:05,600 --> 00:41:12,000
This spirit led her to Monkey's prison under 
the mountain, which was a kind of stone box.

365
00:41:13,360 --> 00:41:21,200
Monkey looked out through a thin opening with his 
red eyes and cried, 'You are the Goddess Kuan-yin!  

366
00:41:22,160 --> 00:41:29,680
Why have you come here? Buddha tricked me and 
I have sat in this little box for five hundred  

367
00:41:29,680 --> 00:41:37,280
years. But I am very sorry for the things I have 
done and now I want to do good in the world.'

368
00:41:38,800 --> 00:41:43,680
Kuan-yin was very happy. 'Just wait quietly here  

369
00:41:43,680 --> 00:41:49,040
until I return with my pilgrim 
and he will save you,' she said.

370
00:41:50,320 --> 00:41:56,080
And so they left Monkey and went on 
to the East, to find the pilgrim.
 
 
 

371
00:41:59,360 --> 00:42:00,240
CHAPTER TWO

372
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:02,720
The Journey Begins

373
00:42:04,800 --> 00:42:07,840
'I can tell you that I have 
killed quite a lot of people.  

374
00:42:08,560 --> 00:42:12,480
And I am still the great 
Monkey King!' answered Monkey.

375
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:18,240
At a time when the great and 
very old city of Ch'ang-an  

376
00:42:18,240 --> 00:42:24,080
was the capital of China, there was an examination 
to find the cleverest men in the country.  

377
00:42:25,280 --> 00:42:27,920
These men would do the work of the government.

378
00:42:29,200 --> 00:42:35,360
A man by the name of Ch'en O decided 
to try his luck at the examination,  

379
00:42:35,360 --> 00:42:41,760
as it was his mother's wish. Arriving late, 
he found that the examination had begun.  

380
00:42:42,640 --> 00:42:49,200
But to his surprise, he won first place and 
he received a letter signed by the Emperor.

381
00:42:51,360 --> 00:42:57,200
In those days, the winner of first place in 
the examination was led through the streets  

382
00:42:57,200 --> 00:43:04,480
on horseback. And by chance, on that day, the 
only daughter of a minister sat in her high  

383
00:43:04,480 --> 00:43:12,880
tower with a ball in her hand. Seeing the handsome 
Ch'en riding by, and knowing of his success in the  

384
00:43:12,880 --> 00:43:20,960
examination, she threw the ball cleverly on to 
his hat. This was how a lady chose her husband.

385
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:28,400
No time was wasted. Ch'en and the minister's 
daughter were married, and hand in hand they  

386
00:43:28,400 --> 00:43:36,160
went into the bedroom as man and wife. Early next 
morning, Ch'en was made Governor of Chiang-chou  

387
00:43:36,880 --> 00:43:42,800
and, as he was told to begin work at once, 
he started on the journey with his wife.

388
00:43:44,240 --> 00:43:52,240
It was late spring. There was a gentle wind in 
the trees and a light rain fell. The road to  

389
00:43:52,240 --> 00:43:59,920
Chiang-chou took Ch'en and his wife close to his 
home, so they stopped at his mother's house. Ch'en  

390
00:43:59,920 --> 00:44:05,920
said to his mother, 'You wanted me to take 
the examination, and look at all the good  

391
00:44:05,920 --> 00:44:11,360
luck that has come from it. I would like to 
thank you and to ask you to come with us.'

392
00:44:12,480 --> 00:44:19,520
His mother happily agreed and after travelling 
for some days, the three arrived at the Hotel of  

393
00:44:19,520 --> 00:44:26,320
Ten Thousand Flowers. But here the mother 
suddenly became ill and asked to rest.

394
00:44:27,600 --> 00:44:34,640
Next day, a man arrived with a gold-coloured fish 
for sale and young Ch'en bought it for his mother.  

395
00:44:35,760 --> 00:44:43,120
Suddenly, he noticed that the fish's eyes were 
strange. 'This is not an ordinary creature,' he  

396
00:44:43,120 --> 00:44:49,840
said. He asked where it was caught and then 
returned it to the river in the same place.

397
00:44:51,120 --> 00:44:54,400
'You were right to put the 
fish back in the river,'  

398
00:44:54,400 --> 00:44:58,960
said his mother when he told her 
about the fish's eyes. Then she said,  

399
00:44:59,920 --> 00:45:05,600
'Leave me here with some of the luggage and 
I shall follow when the days are cooler.'

400
00:45:07,680 --> 00:45:14,960
When Ch'en, his wife and servants arrived at the 
same river, they were met by two boatmen who Ch'en  

401
00:45:14,960 --> 00:45:20,880
had harmed in an earlier life. They stared 
at his young wife, who was very beautiful.  

402
00:45:21,920 --> 00:45:28,400
Then they took the boat to a lonely place 
and killed first the servants and then Ch'en  

403
00:45:28,400 --> 00:45:34,320
himself. The young woman tried to throw 
herself into the river, but they stopped her.

404
00:45:35,920 --> 00:45:38,480
One of the murderers, whose name was Liu,  

405
00:45:39,120 --> 00:45:45,840
put on the Governor's clothes, took the official 
papers and left for Chiang-chou with Mrs Ch'en.

406
00:45:46,960 --> 00:45:54,000
Liu left the boat with the other boatman, Li, 
who threw the bodies into the river. The bodies  

407
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:59,840
of the servants could be seen on the river, 
but Ch'en's body went straight to the bottom.  

408
00:46:00,960 --> 00:46:07,840
A servant of the Dragon King saw it there and went 
to the palace to tell the Dragon King himself.  

409
00:46:08,640 --> 00:46:10,720
The Dragon King asked to see it.

410
00:46:11,840 --> 00:46:16,080
When Ch'en's body was brought 
to him, he recognised this man.  

411
00:46:17,200 --> 00:46:24,640
In the body of a gold-coloured fish, the Dragon 
King had been saved by him only a few days before.  

412
00:46:25,840 --> 00:46:31,600
In return for Ch'en's kindness, the Dragon 
King sent his servant to the place where the  

413
00:46:31,600 --> 00:46:41,840
souls of the newly dead go. The servant returned 
with Ch'en's soul and Ch'en woke from the dead.

414
00:46:42,560 --> 00:46:48,880
When he had heard Ch'en's story, the 
Dragon King said, 'You certainly helped me.  

415
00:46:49,600 --> 00:46:56,240
So I shall now give you back your life. 
I want you to work in my Water Office.'

416
00:46:58,400 --> 00:47:03,440
While this was happening, Mrs 
Ch'en was so unhappy with Liu  

417
00:47:03,440 --> 00:47:08,640
that she could not eat or sleep. But because 
she was going to have her husband's child,  

418
00:47:09,280 --> 00:47:13,040
she thought it was best to 
follow this terrible man quietly.  

419
00:47:14,320 --> 00:47:21,440
After a long journey they reached Chiang-chou, 
where Liu the boatman became the new governor.

420
00:47:22,800 --> 00:47:32,080
Time passed and Mrs Ch'en gave birth to a son. 
At the same time a mysterious voice whispered  

421
00:47:32,080 --> 00:47:40,000
in her ear, 'Listen to what I am telling you. 
This child will be famous around the world.  

422
00:47:40,800 --> 00:47:48,640
But you must protect him from Liu, who will 
certainly try to harm him. Your husband is safe  

423
00:47:48,640 --> 00:47:56,800
with the Dragon King and one day you will all be 
together again and your enemies will be punished.'  

424
00:47:59,120 --> 00:48:02,320
Then there was silence. Mrs Ch'en  

425
00:48:02,320 --> 00:48:07,760
held her son in her arms, but she could 
think of no other way to protect him.

426
00:48:09,040 --> 00:48:16,400
And as the voice had said, when Liu returned he 
ordered the death of the child. But the unhappy  

427
00:48:16,400 --> 00:48:23,840
mother wanted more time with her son. 'I will 
put him in the river tomorrow,' she promised Liu.  

428
00:48:25,040 --> 00:48:28,960
'Perhaps,' she thought, 'a 
kind god will save him.'

429
00:48:31,120 --> 00:48:38,320
She bit her finger and, with her blood, wrote a 
letter giving the names of the child's parents.  

430
00:48:39,280 --> 00:48:41,760
Then, so that she would know her child again,  

431
00:48:42,480 --> 00:48:48,240
she bit off the top of the little toe 
of his left foot. When morning came,  

432
00:48:48,800 --> 00:48:54,080
she tied the baby into one of her shirts 
and went quietly down to the river with him.

433
00:48:56,000 --> 00:49:03,840
As she stood at the water's edge, a large piece 
of wood came down the river. Quickly, she tied the  

434
00:49:03,840 --> 00:49:10,880
shirt with the baby in it to the wood and put 
the letter she had written in the shirt. Then  

435
00:49:10,880 --> 00:49:17,760
she pushed the wood to the centre of the river 
and walked back, crying every step of the way.

436
00:49:19,520 --> 00:49:25,680
The piece of wood with the baby on it was carried 
at last to the Temple of the Golden Mountain.  

437
00:49:26,720 --> 00:49:30,720
The Holy Master, hearing 
the sound of a baby crying,  

438
00:49:30,720 --> 00:49:38,240
went to the river and found the strange boat. 
He read the letter about the child's father, and  

439
00:49:38,240 --> 00:49:45,760
immediately gave the child the name of River Wood. 
Then he asked some farmers to look after him.

440
00:49:47,920 --> 00:49:54,000
Seventeen years later, the young man had been 
given the new name of Hsuan Tsang and had been  

441
00:49:54,000 --> 00:50:01,920
made a priest in the Holy Master's temple. One 
day an old and stupid priest cried out, 'Who do  

442
00:50:01,920 --> 00:50:09,040
you think you are? No one even knows your real 
name!' He was jealous of the young man's wisdom.

443
00:50:10,160 --> 00:50:18,000
The unhappy boy ran to the Holy Master. 'Can there 
be,' he asked, 'a man without a father or mother?'

444
00:50:19,440 --> 00:50:26,560
From a hiding-place in his room, the Holy Master 
took down a small box containing the blood-letter  

445
00:50:26,560 --> 00:50:34,320
and the shirt. Soon Hsuan Tsang knew the whole 
story and the terrible wrong done to his parents.  

446
00:50:35,440 --> 00:50:37,840
He wanted to kill his father's murderer.

447
00:50:39,200 --> 00:50:46,960
'If you must go,' said the Holy Master, 'take 
these things with you. Travel as a poor priest,  

448
00:50:48,000 --> 00:50:50,880
go to Chiang-chou and demand to see your mother.'

449
00:50:52,560 --> 00:50:59,040
That same night, his mother dreamed of a moon 
behind the clouds. When the clouds moved,  

450
00:50:59,040 --> 00:51:05,840
she saw a full moon, and then she thought 
of her son. 'He must be seventeen by now.  

451
00:51:06,720 --> 00:51:08,960
Perhaps Heaven will bring us together again.'

452
00:51:10,560 --> 00:51:15,200
Suddenly, she heard a priest asking 
for money at the gate and went out to  

453
00:51:15,200 --> 00:51:22,880
him. When she heard his place of birth, the 
Golden Mountain, she looked at him closely  

454
00:51:22,880 --> 00:51:28,880
and said, 'Little priest, you are very 
like my husband. Who were your parents?'

455
00:51:30,560 --> 00:51:37,520
'A wrong was done to my parents,' was the answer. 
'My Holy Master told me to come here and find my  

456
00:51:37,520 --> 00:51:45,440
mother. My father's name is Ch'en, but my holy 
name is Hsuan Tsang.' Then he took from the box  

457
00:51:45,440 --> 00:51:52,080
the blood-letter and the shirt. She recognised 
them at once and she put her arms around him.

458
00:51:53,040 --> 00:52:00,400
'Leave me, leave me!' she cried. 'If Liu finds 
you, he will kill you. Go now, as fast as  

459
00:52:00,400 --> 00:52:06,960
lightning! But tomorrow I will say that I have 
promised a hundred pairs of shoes to the poor  

460
00:52:06,960 --> 00:52:12,560
and I must journey to the temple to offer 
this present to the Gods. There we can talk.'

461
00:52:14,800 --> 00:52:21,200
True to her promise, within five days a 
hundred pairs of shoes were put on a boat  

462
00:52:21,200 --> 00:52:25,120
and, with some servants, she made 
the journey to the Golden Mountain.  

463
00:52:26,400 --> 00:52:32,720
All the priests came out to welcome the visitor, 
but when she had prayed she asked them to leave.

464
00:52:34,320 --> 00:52:40,560
Then, on her knees in front of Hsuan Tsang, she 
took off the shoe and sock from his left foot.  

465
00:52:41,520 --> 00:52:45,840
As she expected, the top of 
his left toe was missing.

466
00:52:46,720 --> 00:52:50,560
Again the mother and son put 
their arms around each other,  

467
00:52:50,560 --> 00:52:57,680
and she thanked the Holy Master for his great 
kindness. Then she gave Hsuan Tsang a ring to  

468
00:52:57,680 --> 00:53:03,280
take to the Hotel of Ten Thousand Flowers, 
where his grandmother had been left behind.

469
00:53:04,880 --> 00:53:08,640
'Here, also, is a letter to 
my father in the capital,'  

470
00:53:08,640 --> 00:53:15,440
she said. 'Tell him to ask the Emperor to 
send horses and men to kill Liu and save me.  

471
00:53:16,560 --> 00:53:20,480
Now I dare not stay any 
longer, but must return home.'

472
00:53:22,240 --> 00:53:29,280
Hsuan Tsang went to the Hotel of Ten Thousand 
Flowers and asked about his grandmother. The  

473
00:53:29,280 --> 00:53:36,000
owner of the hotel told him, 'The lady was 
here for several years. But she went blind  

474
00:53:36,000 --> 00:53:41,840
and now, asking people in the streets 
for money, she lives in a box.'

475
00:53:41,840 --> 00:53:47,200
Hsuan Tsang finally found his 
poor grandmother, who cried,  

476
00:53:47,200 --> 00:53:55,840
'Oh! I thought my son had forgotten me! And 
now Heaven has sent a grandson to find me.'

477
00:53:56,480 --> 00:54:01,120
After paying her bills and leaving her 
in a comfortable room at the hotel,  

478
00:54:01,680 --> 00:54:07,840
Hsuan Tsang rushed back to the capital 
and to the house of Minister Yin. But  

479
00:54:07,840 --> 00:54:13,280
they refused to let him in. 'No one in 
our family is a priest,' he was told.

480
00:54:14,400 --> 00:54:21,440
'Last night I dreamed about my daughter,' said 
the wife. 'Perhaps he has a message from her.'

481
00:54:22,880 --> 00:54:27,120
Hsuan Tsang bowed to them and took out 
the letter that his mother had written.  

482
00:54:28,240 --> 00:54:36,400
The minister cried, 'Wife! This is our grandchild. 
Ch'en has been killed and our daughter has been  

483
00:54:36,400 --> 00:54:41,920
forced to live with the murderer. I will ask 
the Emperor for soldiers to kill that man.'

484
00:54:44,160 --> 00:54:50,160
The Emperor was wild with anger and sent an 
army of sixty thousand men to Chiang-chou.  

485
00:54:51,040 --> 00:54:55,200
They easily found Liu and took 
him away to cut his head off.

486
00:54:56,480 --> 00:55:03,760
Now Yin sent for his daughter. She did not wish 
to see her father because she was ashamed. Had she  

487
00:55:03,760 --> 00:55:10,080
not lived as the wife of her husband's murderer? 
But Yin told her that it was not her fault.  

488
00:55:10,800 --> 00:55:20,240
He put his arms around her and around his grandson 
and kept them in his arms for a long, long time.

489
00:55:20,240 --> 00:55:28,400
By now, the soldiers had found the other boatman, 
Li, and had cut his head off too. And where he had  

490
00:55:28,400 --> 00:55:35,280
killed Ch'en, Li's body was cut open. His heart 
was offered to the soul of the man he had killed.

491
00:55:36,960 --> 00:55:43,920
The Dragon King heard of this and he sent 
a message to Ch'en. 'Congratulations!  

492
00:55:44,640 --> 00:55:49,200
Your wife and her father and 
your child are all by the river,  

493
00:55:49,760 --> 00:55:57,200
offering the heart of the man who killed you. I 
will now return your soul to you and let you go.'

494
00:55:59,280 --> 00:56:04,000
Mrs Ch'en wanted to throw herself into 
the river where her husband had died,  

495
00:56:04,720 --> 00:56:08,560
but suddenly a body came up 
from the bottom of the river.  

496
00:56:09,440 --> 00:56:16,240
Mrs Ch'en recognised it as her 
husband's body and cried and screamed.

497
00:56:16,240 --> 00:56:24,800
The hands moved, and then the legs, and then the 
whole body, until Ch'en himself climbed out of the  

498
00:56:24,800 --> 00:56:31,440
water. He looked at them in great surprise 
and said, 'What are you all doing here?'

499
00:56:32,720 --> 00:56:40,160
A great banquet was ordered and next day they 
all left for home. On the way, they called  

500
00:56:40,160 --> 00:56:46,560
at the Hotel of Ten Thousand Flowers for the 
grandmother and took her back to the capital.

501
00:56:48,560 --> 00:56:55,760
At last Chen became a government advisor. 
His son, Hsuan Tsang, went back to his work  

502
00:56:55,760 --> 00:57:01,440
as a priest at the Temple of the Golden 
Mountain. But when the Emperor died,  

503
00:57:01,440 --> 00:57:09,400
priests all over China were asked to choose 
the holiest priest, and they chose Hsuan Tsang.

504
00:57:11,440 --> 00:57:17,520
At this time, the search was still continuing for 
a priest holy enough to fetch the Scriptures from  

505
00:57:17,520 --> 00:57:24,800
India. The Goddess Kuan-yin, realising 
that the holiest priest was River Wood,  

506
00:57:24,800 --> 00:57:28,880
said to herself, 'No one could 
be a better man than him.'

507
00:57:30,080 --> 00:57:31,600
In the great city of Ch'ang-an,  

508
00:57:32,400 --> 00:57:37,760
the new Emperor asked Hsuan Tsang to 
go to India and fetch the Scriptures.  

509
00:57:38,720 --> 00:57:46,400
When Hsuan Tsang agreed to go, the Emperor said, 
'If you dare to go on a journey as long as this,  

510
00:57:46,400 --> 00:57:55,680
with all its dangers, I will make you here and now 
the brother of my soul.' Then he bowed four times.

511
00:57:57,040 --> 00:58:01,520
'If I do not reach India and do not 
bring the Scriptures back to China,  

512
00:58:02,080 --> 00:58:05,600
I must be sent to Hell,' the young priest replied.

513
00:58:06,720 --> 00:58:12,240
The Emperor called for wine and 
said, 'I suggest that you take the  

514
00:58:12,240 --> 00:58:21,840
name of the Scriptures in India 
- Tripitaka. What do you think?'

515
00:58:23,880 --> 00:58:30,160
Hsuan Tsang accepted the name and 
from that day he was called Tripitaka.

516
00:58:31,200 --> 00:58:38,400
It was three days before the full moon when 
Tripitaka left the gates of Ch'ang-an. After  

517
00:58:38,400 --> 00:58:46,320
a day or two of hard riding, he reached the Temple 
of the Low Cloud. There the Holy Master and almost  

518
00:58:46,320 --> 00:58:52,320
five hundred priests discussed his journey 
and its terrible dangers and difficulties.  

519
00:58:53,360 --> 00:58:56,080
Tripitaka pointed in silence to his heart.

520
00:58:57,200 --> 00:59:03,920
'It is only the heart that can win against 
difficulties. I have made my promise and I  

521
00:59:03,920 --> 00:59:10,240
cannot go back until I have reached India, 
seen Buddha and got the Scriptures.'

522
00:59:11,920 --> 00:59:18,400
Next morning, Tripitaka got up early. A bright 
moon was shining on the snow on the ground  

523
00:59:18,400 --> 00:59:26,880
as he left. Almost immediately, he lost his way, 
and suddenly the ground moved under his horse.  

524
00:59:27,920 --> 00:59:31,840
The horse and rider fell into a deep hole.

525
00:59:32,480 --> 00:59:34,880
'Take him! Take him!'

526
00:59:36,240 --> 00:59:43,440
Looking up, Tripitaka saw a crowd of ugly 
creatures looking down at him. They pulled him  

527
00:59:43,440 --> 00:59:50,080
out of the hole. Their leader was an ugly 
Demon King, who gave orders to eat him.

528
00:59:51,600 --> 00:59:58,960
But two dark ugly creatures arrived as guests, and 
two other men were brought out as a meal for them.  

529
00:59:59,680 --> 01:00:06,240
The ugly creatures ate like wild animals, 
their teeth pulling at the men until they  

530
01:00:06,240 --> 01:00:13,840
had completely eaten them. Watching this, 
Tripitaka was almost dead with fear.

531
01:00:14,720 --> 01:00:17,600
But then all the ugly creatures went to sleep.  

532
01:00:18,640 --> 01:00:24,240
Tripitaka was losing all hope of escape 
when suddenly an old man appeared.  

533
01:00:25,120 --> 01:00:32,320
He blew in Tripitaka's face and asked him 
if the horse belonged to him. Tripitaka  

534
01:00:32,320 --> 01:00:38,800
saw to his surprise that his horse was 
not harmed. He asked what this place was  

535
01:00:38,800 --> 01:00:46,480
and who the ugly creatures were. He was told it 
was a mountain full of demons and animal-spirits.

536
01:00:48,000 --> 01:00:53,760
'They did not eat you because your 
soul was too good,' said the old man.

537
01:00:54,480 --> 01:01:02,400
'It was your soul that saved you. Follow me 
and I will show you the way out of here.'

538
01:01:04,080 --> 01:01:12,080
The old man led him out of that place; then, 
as Tripitaka turned to thank him, the old man  

539
01:01:12,080 --> 01:01:20,400
flew up into the sky on a great white bird. A 
piece of paper blew down, and on it was written,  

540
01:01:21,280 --> 01:01:30,560
'I was sent by the Gods to protect you on your 
journey. Remember, the Gods will be watching you.'

541
01:01:32,160 --> 01:01:37,840
Tripitaka could only bow low in thanks 
before he began his journey again.  

542
01:01:40,320 --> 01:01:45,360
After half a day he found himself 
in difficult mountain country,  

543
01:01:45,360 --> 01:01:54,000
moving forward slowly over sharp rocks. In front 
of him, two tigers waited. Realising the danger,  

544
01:01:54,000 --> 01:02:02,400
he looked behind him and there he saw an insect 
that could kill him. On his right stood a wild  

545
01:02:02,400 --> 01:02:08,400
animal that he had never seen before. His 
frightened horse went down on its knees.

546
01:02:09,760 --> 01:02:13,200
As the terrible creatures all 
started attacking him at once,  

547
01:02:13,760 --> 01:02:18,480
a man appeared with a sword. He 
took Tripitaka from his horse.

548
01:02:19,600 --> 01:02:25,040
'I am a hunter who these animals know 
and fear. You and I are from the same  

549
01:02:25,040 --> 01:02:29,840
country and you and your horse can 
rest at my house until tomorrow.'

550
01:02:31,280 --> 01:02:37,280
On the way to his house the hunter 
killed a tiger, saying, 'This is luck!  

551
01:02:37,280 --> 01:02:39,520
Enough meat to last you for days!'

552
01:02:41,840 --> 01:02:47,200
Arriving at a mountain farm, Tripitaka 
was presented to the hunter's mother,  

553
01:02:47,200 --> 01:02:52,880
who invited him to stay overnight. But when 
the cooked tiger was put in front of him  

554
01:02:53,440 --> 01:03:02,080
he had to say that, as a priest, he did not 
eat meat. He was given rice and salad instead.  

555
01:03:02,080 --> 01:03:06,080
Then, putting his hands 
together, he said a prayer.

556
01:03:07,280 --> 01:03:13,120
The hunter was surprised. 'You priests 
are certainly strange,' he said.  

557
01:03:13,840 --> 01:03:15,840
'You cannot even eat without a prayer.'

558
01:03:18,000 --> 01:03:23,680
After dinner the hunter led his guest 
to a little house full of animal skins.  

559
01:03:24,640 --> 01:03:28,800
Tripitaka did not like that very much, so his host  

560
01:03:28,800 --> 01:03:36,960
took him instead to a field of red and gold 
flowers. There, animals ran to him when he called.

561
01:03:38,560 --> 01:03:43,840
Tripitaka had been asked by the hunter's 
mother to say prayers for her dead husband.  

562
01:03:45,040 --> 01:03:51,440
So scriptures were read and prayers were 
said all through the next day until evening.

563
01:03:53,600 --> 01:04:00,800
That night everyone in the family dreamed the 
same dream: the hunter's father had been allowed  

564
01:04:00,800 --> 01:04:09,520
to leave the Lower World and was born again as the 
child of a rich landowner. This, they were sure,  

565
01:04:09,520 --> 01:04:16,720
was a result of Tripitaka's prayers and they all 
thanked him. They wanted to give him presents of  

566
01:04:16,720 --> 01:04:23,680
silver, but he refused the presents and left 
on his journey, with the hunter as his guide.

567
01:04:25,600 --> 01:04:30,320
At the Mountain Between Two 
Countries, which was steep and rocky,  

568
01:04:30,320 --> 01:04:34,880
the hunter climbed quickly 
but Tripitaka was very tired.

569
01:04:36,240 --> 01:04:43,600
'This country to the East,' said the hunter, 
'is our land of Tang, and to the West is the  

570
01:04:43,600 --> 01:04:49,920
country of the Tartars. I cannot go into 
their country, so you must continue alone.'

571
01:04:51,440 --> 01:04:56,320
Feeling a great fear and hopelessness, 
Tripitaka held the hunter's arm.  

572
01:04:58,560 --> 01:05:06,320
Suddenly, from under the mountain, a voice 
cried, again and again, 'The Master has come.'

573
01:05:07,520 --> 01:05:10,720
'Who is that?' Tripitaka asked, fearfully.

574
01:05:11,840 --> 01:05:19,440
'It is the voice of the old monkey calling from 
his stone box under the mountain. The story is  

575
01:05:19,440 --> 01:05:26,400
that long ago, when the mountain was called the 
Mountain of Metal, Wood, Water, Fire and Earth,  

576
01:05:26,960 --> 01:05:31,680
a magic monkey was put in 
a stone box by angry gods.  

577
01:05:32,560 --> 01:05:38,880
He is certainly still alive. You need not 
be afraid. We will go down and have a look.'

578
01:05:40,640 --> 01:05:45,520
As the hunter had said, there was 
a stone box with a hole in it,  

579
01:05:45,520 --> 01:05:48,560
and through the opening they 
could see the head of a monkey.

580
01:05:49,680 --> 01:05:56,320
'Master! Master! Free me from here and I will 
protect you on your journey to the West!'

581
01:05:57,520 --> 01:06:01,440
The hunter said, 'First, we 
want to know more about you.'

582
01:06:02,960 --> 01:06:08,800
'I will not tell you anything,' said 
Monkey. 'I wish to speak to the priest.'

583
01:06:10,320 --> 01:06:13,520
'What do you want to say to me?' asked Tripitaka.

584
01:06:14,720 --> 01:06:19,840
'Were you sent by the Emperor of T'ang 
to fetch the Scriptures from India?'

585
01:06:20,800 --> 01:06:21,440
'I was.'

586
01:06:22,400 --> 01:06:30,560
'I am the Monkey King and five hundred years ago I 
made trouble, so Buddha put me in this stone box.  

587
01:06:31,520 --> 01:06:37,840
The Goddess Kuan-yin has visited me. She 
said that if I protect the pilgrim on his  

588
01:06:37,840 --> 01:06:44,240
way to India I will be forgiven and 
freed. So let me be your follower.'

589
01:06:45,440 --> 01:06:48,000
'But how can I get you out of this stone box?'

590
01:06:49,200 --> 01:06:52,560
'If you make a wish, Master, I will be out,'  

591
01:06:53,200 --> 01:07:00,800
said Monkey. 'Go to the top of the mountain and 
there you will see a rock with letters of gold  

592
01:07:00,800 --> 01:07:05,920
written by Buddha himself. Lift 
the rock and I will be free.'

593
01:07:07,840 --> 01:07:11,680
'How can we believe him?' the 
hunter whispered to Tripitaka.

594
01:07:12,240 --> 01:07:17,840
'It is true! It is true!' screamed 
Monkey, from inside his box.

595
01:07:19,440 --> 01:07:23,680
Tripitaka and the hunter climbed up 
again to the top of the mountain,  

596
01:07:24,320 --> 01:07:30,480
and there they saw golden light pouring 
from a rock which had gold writing on it.

597
01:07:31,920 --> 01:07:37,360
Tripitaka went down on his knees and 
said, 'If this is the wish of the Gods,  

598
01:07:38,000 --> 01:07:43,760
I will take this Monkey with me to 
India. Take away this rock and free him.'

599
01:07:45,120 --> 01:07:52,880
A warm and sweet-smelling wind blew across the 
mountain and lifted the rock and Buddha's writing  

600
01:07:52,880 --> 01:07:58,560
up into the air. Tripitaka and 
the hunter returned to Monkey.

601
01:08:00,400 --> 01:08:06,480
'You can come out,' they said. With 
a great noise of breaking stone,  

602
01:08:06,480 --> 01:08:11,280
Monkey came out of the stone box 
and bowed in front of Tripitaka.  

603
01:08:11,920 --> 01:08:20,320
He cried, 'Master, I am out,' and then he began 
to prepare Tripitaka's horse for the journey.

604
01:08:22,720 --> 01:08:28,960
Tripitaka thanked the hunter for his kindness 
and he and Monkey continued their journey.

605
01:08:30,960 --> 01:08:37,280
When Tripitaka and Monkey left the mountain, 
a tiger appeared in front of them, showing its  

