He took a needle from behind his ear and the 
needle was immediately transformed into a cudgel.  

608
01:08:53,280 --> 01:08:58,080
'It is five hundred years since I 
last used this weapon,' he cried.

609
01:08:59,200 --> 01:09:08,720
Look at Monkey! He walks forward bravely, down 
comes the cudgel, and the tiger falls dead.

610
01:09:11,520 --> 01:09:16,240
'Sit down,' said Monkey to 
Tripitaka, 'while I take his coat.'

611
01:09:18,800 --> 01:09:25,920
Dear Monkey! He took a single hair from his own 
tail, blew on it, and said some magic words.  

612
01:09:26,800 --> 01:09:33,840
The hair became a sharp little knife, and 
with this knife he cut off the tiger's skin.  

613
01:09:34,720 --> 01:09:39,280
'Now we can leave this place,' he 
said. 'When we reach the next house,  

614
01:09:39,280 --> 01:09:41,600
I will make a fine coat from the skin.'

615
01:09:43,920 --> 01:09:50,160
Monkey then explained the magic of his cudgel, 
which was not only for killing tigers and dragons,  

616
01:09:50,720 --> 01:09:56,000
but also for making rivers go backwards 
or starting storms on the sea.  

617
01:09:57,440 --> 01:10:01,840
But then he saw a house in some trees, 
where they could spend the night.

618
01:10:02,560 --> 01:10:06,720
He got down from his horse 
and cried, 'Open the door!'

619
01:10:08,320 --> 01:10:16,240
A very old man, angry at the rude command, began 
to push open the door. But seeing Monkey carrying  

620
01:10:16,240 --> 01:10:23,280
a tiger skin and looking like a demon, he became 
very frightened. Then he saw that Monkey was  

621
01:10:23,280 --> 01:10:32,320
with a priest and he was told that Monkey was the 
priest's follower. Suddenly, he recognised Monkey.

622
01:10:33,520 --> 01:10:40,880
'You are the Stone Monkey in the stone 
box,' said the old man in great surprise.  

623
01:10:41,760 --> 01:10:43,840
'How did you get out?'

624
01:10:45,280 --> 01:10:49,440
Monkey told his story and then was asked his age.

625
01:10:50,560 --> 01:10:54,080
'First, how old are you?' asked Monkey.

626
01:10:54,960 --> 01:10:58,800
'One hundred and thirty.'

627
01:10:58,800 --> 01:11:02,480
'You are young enough to be 
my great-great-grandson,'  

628
01:11:03,280 --> 01:11:08,480
said Monkey. 'I was under that 
mountain for five hundred years.'

629
01:11:09,520 --> 01:11:14,080
'True,' said the old man. 'And when I was a boy,  

630
01:11:14,640 --> 01:11:18,880
there was grass on your 
head and dirt on your face.'

631
01:11:19,840 --> 01:11:25,280
'Yes!' said Monkey. 'I do not 
wish to make trouble, but it  

632
01:11:25,280 --> 01:11:31,040
is five hundred years since I last washed. 
Could you let us have a little hot water?'

633
01:11:32,720 --> 01:11:36,560
When they had both washed, 
Monkey took Tripitaka's white  

634
01:11:36,560 --> 01:11:43,120
shirt, made himself a tiger-skin coat and 
asked, 'How do I look in these clothes?'

635
01:11:44,080 --> 01:11:54,000
'Fine!' said Tripitaka. 'You really look like 
a pilgrim!' And he let Monkey keep the shirt.

636
01:11:54,000 --> 01:11:58,880
Many days later, the two travellers 
were attacked by six men with swords.

637
01:11:59,600 --> 01:12:03,120
The men demanded their horses and 
everything they had with them.

638
01:12:04,240 --> 01:12:08,160
'You are just thieves!' cried Monkey.  

639
01:12:08,160 --> 01:12:13,600
'If you give me one seventh of everything 
you have ever stolen, I will let you live.'

640
01:12:14,640 --> 01:12:18,400
Angrily, they all hit Monkey 
on the head, again and again.

641
01:12:19,760 --> 01:12:24,880
Monkey said, 'Let me know when you are 
tired and I will take out my needle.'

642
01:12:26,000 --> 01:12:31,200
Of course the needle from behind Monkey's 
ear transformed itself into a cudgel,  

643
01:12:31,840 --> 01:12:36,160
and soon he had killed all six of them.  

644
01:12:36,160 --> 01:12:41,360
He returned, crying, 'Master, we can 
start now. I have killed them all.'

645
01:12:43,840 --> 01:12:47,440
'You should never kill,' said Tripitaka, sadly.

646
01:12:47,440 --> 01:12:49,840
'But I had to! They were going to kill you!'

647
01:12:52,400 --> 01:12:56,160
'It is better for a priest 
to die than to kill others.'

648
01:12:57,200 --> 01:13:02,000
'Well, I can tell you that I have 
killed quite a lot of people. And I  

649
01:13:02,000 --> 01:13:06,000
am still the great Monkey King!' answered Monkey.

650
01:13:07,280 --> 01:13:13,600
'Your bad behaviour in Heaven caused you to 
live in a stone box for five hundred years,'  

651
01:13:14,320 --> 01:13:21,040
said Tripitaka. 'If you hope to come with me 
to India, you will need to change your ways.'

652
01:13:22,400 --> 01:13:26,480
Monkey was very angry that Tripitaka 
had spoken to him like that.  

653
01:13:27,120 --> 01:13:32,240
'Master,' he shouted, 'I am leaving.'

654
01:13:32,240 --> 01:13:39,200
Tripitaka said nothing, so Monkey leapt up, 
ran away and was soon out of Tripitaka's sight.

655
01:13:41,360 --> 01:13:47,680
Tripitaka thought, 'It is no use trying 
to teach people who are like that.' So,  

656
01:13:47,680 --> 01:13:52,160
putting all the luggage on the horse's 
back, he left alone and on foot.

657
01:13:53,360 --> 01:13:58,000
The young priest had not gone far when 
he met an old woman carrying a cap.  

658
01:13:58,960 --> 01:14:02,880
She asked him why he was travelling 
alone without a follower to help him.

659
01:14:04,240 --> 01:14:10,160
'I had a follower, but he behaved badly. 
When I told him that, he ran away.'

660
01:14:11,760 --> 01:14:18,480
'That is unfortunate,' she said. 'This 
cap belonged to my son, who died.  

661
01:14:19,120 --> 01:14:22,720
I can gladly give it to your 
follower if he would like it.'

662
01:14:23,840 --> 01:14:26,560
'He ran away to the East,' said Tripitaka.

663
01:14:27,360 --> 01:14:31,680
'Then he will certainly go to my 
house and I shall send him back.  

664
01:14:32,560 --> 01:14:40,560
If you want him to return, you will need a spell.' 
She told him the words. 'You must make him wear  

665
01:14:40,560 --> 01:14:48,560
this cap. When he disobeys, say the words of 
the spell and he will give you no more trouble.'

666
01:14:50,160 --> 01:14:56,400
The old woman transformed herself into a 
golden light and disappeared towards the East.  

667
01:14:57,920 --> 01:15:02,560
Tripitaka knew then that she 
was really the Goddess Kuan-yin.

668
01:15:03,520 --> 01:15:10,160
Monkey had jumped on to a cloud and was returning 
to his cave in the Mountain of Flowers and Fruit.  

669
01:15:10,160 --> 01:15:13,760
On the way, he decided to 
drink tea with the Dragon King.  

670
01:15:14,880 --> 01:15:20,640
When Monkey had told his story, the Dragon 
King told him about the value of patience.

671
01:15:21,680 --> 01:15:28,800
'Monkey King, it is necessary to control yourself 
if you do not want to spoil all your chances.'

672
01:15:30,480 --> 01:15:33,280
Monkey thought about that and then jumped up.  

673
01:15:33,840 --> 01:15:38,960
'Don't say another word!' he said. 
'I will return to my Master at once.'

674
01:15:41,120 --> 01:15:46,480
'Master,' said Monkey, when he found Tripitaka 
sitting sadly by the side of the road,  

675
01:15:47,360 --> 01:15:49,520
'what are you doing, still sitting here?'

676
01:15:50,800 --> 01:15:54,960
'Waiting for you,' he answered. 
'I could not continue alone.'

677
01:15:56,160 --> 01:16:00,080
'I only went to drink tea with 
the Dragon King,' said Monkey.

678
01:16:01,680 --> 01:16:06,240
'If that is true, you should think 
about my thirst and my hunger too.'

679
01:16:07,520 --> 01:16:12,000
Monkey went to their luggage to look 
for food and found the gift of the cap.

680
01:16:13,040 --> 01:16:16,640
'If a person wears that cap,' said Tripitaka,  

681
01:16:17,360 --> 01:16:21,040
'they can recite the Scriptures 
without learning them first.'

682
01:16:21,600 --> 01:16:24,080
'Let me put it on!' cried Monkey.

683
01:16:24,080 --> 01:16:26,000
'Yes, put it on.'

684
01:16:27,360 --> 01:16:32,080
As Monkey put it on, Tripitaka 
pretended to eat some dried fruit,  

685
01:16:32,880 --> 01:16:35,600
but he was really reciting the magic spell.

686
01:16:37,360 --> 01:16:41,280
'My head is hurting!' screamed Monkey.

687
01:16:42,000 --> 01:16:43,920
Monkey fell on the ground,  

688
01:16:43,920 --> 01:16:51,280
trying to take the cap off, but a metal ring 
inside the cap was getting tighter and tighter.  

689
01:16:52,400 --> 01:16:59,040
Tripitaka stopped reciting the spell because he 
was afraid that Monkey would break the metal ring.

690
01:17:00,320 --> 01:17:05,440
The pain in Monkey's head disappeared, 
but the cap was still tightly there.

691
01:17:06,480 --> 01:17:10,000
'You have put a spell on me,' cried Monkey.

692
01:17:11,040 --> 01:17:18,720
'Yes,' said Tripitaka. 'It is called the Scripture 
of the Tight Cap. Will you make trouble again?'

693
01:17:19,520 --> 01:17:22,960
'Never! I promise,' answered Monkey,  

694
01:17:23,600 --> 01:17:29,840
but in his heart he was very angry. 
He ran at Tripitaka with his cudgel.

695
01:17:30,400 --> 01:17:34,160
Quickly, the priest again 
recited the words of the spell,  

696
01:17:34,160 --> 01:17:38,880
and Monkey fell to the ground screaming. 
The cudgel dropped from his hand.

697
01:17:40,080 --> 01:17:43,120
'Were you going to hit me?' Tripitaka asked.

698
01:17:43,840 --> 01:17:47,680
'Hit you? I dare not!' cried Monkey.

699
01:17:48,640 --> 01:17:54,880
Tripitaka stopped reciting because he did not 
like to see Monkey suffering such terrible pain.

700
01:17:56,720 --> 01:18:01,040
'Who taught you this trick?' 
Monkey asked when the pain stopped.

701
01:18:02,080 --> 01:18:04,400
'An old woman who I met recently.'

702
01:18:05,520 --> 01:18:11,840
'Then it was the Goddess Kuan-yin. I will go to 
the Southern Ocean and hit her with my cudgel!'

703
01:18:13,280 --> 01:18:18,640
'As she taught me this spell, she can 
surely use it herself,' said Tripitaka.

704
01:18:19,840 --> 01:18:26,640
Monkey sat up, holding his head, which 
still hurt him. 'I am very sorry,' he said.  

705
01:18:27,200 --> 01:18:33,280
'I will travel to India and never leave 
you. I will protect you until the end.'

706
01:18:34,960 --> 01:18:36,480
Unable to defend himself,  

707
