01:24:51,280 --> 01:24:58,160
The Goddess laughed. 'Because you are so full of 
tricks, there is no other way to control you.'

769
01:24:58,800 --> 01:25:02,480
'But what about this dragon? 
That is your work too.  

770
01:25:03,280 --> 01:25:08,800
Why did you let him eat my Master's 
horse? You should be ashamed of yourself!'

771
01:25:09,920 --> 01:25:12,800
'That dragon,' said the Goddess Kuan-yin,  

772
01:25:13,600 --> 01:25:20,720
'behaved badly in Heaven. If he carries the priest 
of the Emperor T'ang on his journey to India,  

773
01:25:20,720 --> 01:25:27,360
he will be forgiven and he knows this. No 
ordinary Chinese horse could possibly do it.  

774
01:25:28,240 --> 01:25:33,840
I cannot understand why he ate the 
horse. I will go with you and find out.'

775
01:25:36,000 --> 01:25:42,160
She got down from her seat inside her cave 
and rode on a magic light to find the Dragon.  

776
01:25:43,200 --> 01:25:47,040
When the Dragon saw Kuan-yin, 
he changed into a human.

777
01:25:48,320 --> 01:25:52,800
'Did you know that this is 
Tripitaka's follower?' asked Kuan-yin.

778
01:25:53,680 --> 01:25:59,680
'How could I? I asked him what kind of 
creature he was and he shouted at me,  

779
01:25:59,680 --> 01:26:04,560
"That is not your business." I ate 
his horse because I was hungry.  

780
01:26:05,120 --> 01:26:11,040
He never said anything about looking for 
Scriptures. He never once used the word "T'ang".'

781
01:26:12,800 --> 01:26:19,360
'Monkey is fonder of showing others his own 
powers than explaining anything,' said Kuan-yin.  

782
01:26:20,080 --> 01:26:26,400
'But in future, if anyone questions him, he 
must say that he is looking for Scriptures.  

783
01:26:26,960 --> 01:26:28,880
Then there will be no more trouble.'

784
01:26:30,240 --> 01:26:37,920
The Goddess went to the Dragon and put some drops 
of sweet water on him. Then with her magic breath  

785
01:26:37,920 --> 01:26:44,880
she shouted 'Change!' She transformed the 
Dragon into the horse that he had just eaten.  

786
01:26:45,680 --> 01:26:51,760
She told the Dragon to change his bad behaviour 
and to promise never to go back to his old ways.

787
01:26:52,800 --> 01:26:56,000
'If you keep this promise, you will be given a  

788
01:26:56,000 --> 01:27:00,640
golden body,' she told him, 
'and you will be given wisdom.'

789
01:27:01,840 --> 01:27:06,160
The Dragon said, 'Thank you. 
I will keep this promise.'

790
01:27:07,280 --> 01:27:15,360
Then the Goddess turned to go, but Monkey held her 
arm saying, 'That is not good enough! How can I  

791
01:27:15,360 --> 01:27:22,000
help a priest to travel over these mountains with 
only a horse? I cannot continue this journey.'

792
01:27:23,680 --> 01:27:29,760
'That is strange,' said the Goddess. 'You 
always used to be brave, if nothing else.  

793
01:27:30,720 --> 01:27:33,520
But there is one more power I can give you.'

794
01:27:34,560 --> 01:27:38,560
She took three leaves from a tree 
and dropped them on Monkey's back,  

795
01:27:39,200 --> 01:27:42,240
where they immediately became magic hairs.

796
01:27:43,200 --> 01:27:47,520
'These,' she said, 'will 
get you out of any trouble.'

797
01:27:49,040 --> 01:27:53,600
Monkey thanked her. Then he took 
the horse and led him to Tripitaka.

798
01:27:55,200 --> 01:27:58,160
'This horse is in much better 
condition than the old one.  

799
01:27:58,880 --> 01:28:01,920
How did you manage to find it?' asked Tripitaka.

800
01:28:02,880 --> 01:28:08,160
Monkey answered, 'Kuan-yin changed the 
Dragon into the horse that he had eaten.'

801
01:28:09,520 --> 01:28:15,440
Tripitaka wanted to say 'thank you' to Kuan-yin, 
but Monkey said that she was already far away.  

802
01:28:16,480 --> 01:28:22,960
So Tripitaka bowed towards the South. Then 
he helped Monkey to prepare their luggage.

803
01:28:24,320 --> 01:28:27,840
'We still need a boat to cross 
this river,' said the priest.

804
01:28:28,880 --> 01:28:33,600
'Just sit on the horse and he will 
carry you across,' Monkey replied.

805
01:28:34,320 --> 01:28:40,320
But then an old fisherman in a strange 
boat appeared. Monkey waved to him.  

806
01:28:41,280 --> 01:28:44,000
'We have come from the East to fetch scriptures.  

807
01:28:44,640 --> 01:28:49,680
My Master does not know how to get 
across the river. Could you take him?

808
01:28:50,960 --> 01:28:55,840
The old fisherman took them all across 
the river, without asking for payment.

809
01:28:56,960 --> 01:29:00,160
'Do you know who that fisherman was?' said Monkey.  

810
01:29:00,800 --> 01:29:06,400
'He is the God of the River and he did not 
help us in our fight against the Dragon.  

811
01:29:07,040 --> 01:29:11,680
He knew he had done wrong. That 
is why he did not take any money.'

812
01:29:13,280 --> 01:29:16,720
Tripitaka did not know how true that story was.  

813
01:29:17,440 --> 01:29:21,520
But he sat on the horse and followed 
Monkey along the road to the West.

814
01:29:22,960 --> 01:29:26,640
One evening they saw a group 
of houses in the far distance.

815
01:29:27,840 --> 01:29:34,400
'Let me go and see if it is a farm and if 
it seems lucky or unlucky,' said Monkey.

816
01:29:35,840 --> 01:29:41,680
A young man in a blue jacket came out of the farm 
and tried to walk past Monkey without a word.  

817
01:29:42,400 --> 01:29:46,880
But Monkey held his arm tightly 
while the young man tried to escape.

818
01:29:47,840 --> 01:29:51,760
'Now, you must not be angry,' laughed Monkey,  

819
01:29:51,760 --> 01:29:56,240
holding him even tighter. 'We only 
want to know the name of this place.'

820
01:29:57,440 --> 01:30:04,640
The young man, seeing that he could not get away 
from Monkey, answered, 'The place is called Kao  

821
01:30:04,640 --> 01:30:11,760
Farm and I am Kao Ts'ai. Old Mr Kao has 
a daughter of twenty who is unmarried.  

822
01:30:12,400 --> 01:30:20,000
Three years ago, a creature took her and has 
lived with her here as his wife. Six months ago  

823
01:30:20,000 --> 01:30:25,360
the creature locked her in his little house, 
and none of the family has seen her since then.  

824
01:30:26,400 --> 01:30:30,560
I am going to find someone with strong 
enough magic to fight this creature.'

825
01:30:32,000 --> 01:30:37,600
'This is your lucky day,' said Monkey. 
'Here I am, and I can help you.  

826
01:30:38,400 --> 01:30:41,200
Come, lead us to the master of the house.'

827
01:30:42,400 --> 01:30:48,560
'Your words are true, I hope,' said the young man. 
'You will get me into great trouble if you fail.'

828
01:30:49,520 --> 01:30:53,520
'I promise,' said Monkey. 'Now, take us in.'

829
01:30:55,680 --> 01:31:03,600
Seeing the young man returning, old Mr Kao 
shouted, 'You fool!' But he quickly became  

830
01:31:03,600 --> 01:31:11,040
more polite when he saw the young priest. Seeing 
Monkey, though, he said, 'It is surely bad enough  

831
01:31:11,040 --> 01:31:18,000
to have a dirty creature living with my daughter. 
Now another ugly creature has come to visit me.'

832
01:31:19,600 --> 01:31:25,760
'You have lived a long time but have learned 
very little wisdom,' said Monkey. 'You should  

833
01:31:25,760 --> 01:31:31,120
not judge people only by appearances. 
But I shall return your daughter to you.'

834
01:31:32,560 --> 01:31:36,640
'I do not understand. I thought 
you wanted a bed for the night.'

835
01:31:36,640 --> 01:31:43,520
'Yes, we do,' said Monkey. 'But I am also 
happy to kill any dirty creatures for you,  

836
01:31:43,520 --> 01:31:44,480
for something to do.'

837
01:31:46,240 --> 01:31:52,160
'We have three daughters. Our hope was that the 
youngest would marry a farmer and work this farm.  

838
01:31:53,040 --> 01:32:00,640
Well, about three years ago, a nice-looking young 
man came here and said his name was Pig. He seemed  

839
01:32:00,640 --> 01:32:06,800
the right man for our daughter and at first he 
worked hard on the farm. But then he started  

840
01:32:06,800 --> 01:32:15,840
to change: his nose became longer, his ears 
became bigger, he ate more and more. Finally,  

841
01:32:16,400 --> 01:32:24,080
he turned into a pig. But that was not all. 
He could bring magic winds, he could disappear  

842
01:32:24,080 --> 01:32:31,920
and then appear again, he could make stones fly 
through the air. And now he keeps our daughter,  

843
01:32:31,920 --> 01:32:39,840
Blue Flower, in his little house, and for six 
months we have not known if she is alive or dead.'

844
01:32:41,040 --> 01:32:46,800
'Have no fear,' said Monkey. 'I shall catch 
him tonight and return your daughter to you.'

845
01:32:47,760 --> 01:32:49,920
'But do you need weapons?'

846
01:32:49,920 --> 01:32:52,000
'I have my weapon already,'  

847
01:32:52,720 --> 01:32:58,400
said Monkey, taking his needle from behind 
his ear and changing it into an iron cudgel.  

848
01:32:59,520 --> 01:33:08,160
'I need only a nice old person to sit with my 
Master and talk to him. And now I will leave you!'

849
01:33:08,160 --> 01:33:15,520
Old Mr Kao led Monkey to the little house and 
Monkey broke the door with one blow of his hand.  

850
01:33:16,640 --> 01:33:22,400
Inside it was dark as the old man 
called, 'Number three daughter!'

851
01:33:23,760 --> 01:33:25,680
'Father, I am here.'

852
01:33:27,120 --> 01:33:34,880
Monkey looked hard with his red eyes and saw 
a sad sight. The daughter's face was unwashed,  

853
01:33:34,880 --> 01:33:38,000
her hair was full of dirt and her lips were pale.  

854
01:33:39,200 --> 01:33:43,920
She walked slowly forwards and fell, 
crying, into her father's arms.

855
01:33:45,520 --> 01:33:50,800
'Don't make that noise. But where 
is the creature?' asked Monkey.

856
01:33:51,360 --> 01:33:54,320
'I do not know,' said the unhappy girl.  

857
01:33:55,040 --> 01:34:00,000
'He goes out early in the morning and 
does not come back until late at night.'

858
01:34:01,680 --> 01:34:04,960
'Take your daughter back to 
the house and stay with her,'  

859
01:34:04,960 --> 01:34:10,800
said Monkey to Mr Kao. 'I shall 
wait here and end your troubles.'

860
01:34:13,520 --> 01:34:19,920
When the girl and her father had gone, Monkey 
transformed himself into a girl who looked like  

861
01:34:19,920 --> 01:34:27,520
Blue Flower. Then he waited. Soon stones 
came flying through the air and there in  

862
01:34:27,520 --> 01:34:33,360
front of him stood a terrible creature. He 
had short hairs on his dark skin, a long  

863
01:34:33,360 --> 01:34:40,640
nose and enormous ears. He wore a green jacket and 
had a spotted handkerchief tied round his head.

864
01:34:42,160 --> 01:34:48,880
Dear Monkey! He did not say hello to the 
creature. He lay on the bed making noises  

865
01:34:48,880 --> 01:34:56,240
like a person who is ill. When the creature tried 
to kiss him, he pushed it hard across the room.

866
01:34:57,520 --> 01:35:00,400
'Why are you angry with me?' asked the creature.

867
01:35:01,200 --> 01:35:03,440
'I am not angry. Get into bed.'

868
01:35:04,480 --> 01:35:09,120
The creature undressed in the dark, 
but could not find his wife in the bed.  

869
01:35:09,920 --> 01:35:14,080
Then he heard her crying on 
the far side of the room.

870
01:35:14,080 --> 01:35:17,280
'Oh, I am so unhappy!'

871
01:35:18,480 --> 01:35:21,280
'What are you complaining 
about?' asked the creature.  

872
01:35:21,920 --> 01:35:26,720
'Have I not kept my promises to 
you? I have worked on the farm,  

873
01:35:26,720 --> 01:35:32,720
built walls and dug new fields. You have 
all the food and clothes that you need.'

874
01:35:33,600 --> 01:35:41,440
'That is not the problem,' said Monkey in Blue 
Flower's voice. 'Today my parents came and  

875
01:35:41,440 --> 01:35:47,760
shouted through the wall that you are ugly. And 
nobody knows anything about you or who you are.'

876
01:35:49,120 --> 01:35:51,520
'There is no mystery about who I am.  

877
01:35:52,320 --> 01:35:58,720
Because I look a little like a pig, I am called 
Pigsy. Next time they ask, just tell them that.'

878
01:36:00,400 --> 01:36:02,880
'They are looking for a priest to send you away,'  

879
01:36:03,440 --> 01:36:10,720
said Monkey. 'In fact, old Mr Kao has called 
the great Monkey King himself to help.'

880
01:36:11,920 --> 01:36:18,320
'If that is true, I am leaving this minute,' cried 
the creature. 'That Monkey is very powerful!'  

881
01:36:19,280 --> 01:36:23,840
And getting dressed quickly, 
he opened the door to leave.

882
01:36:24,560 --> 01:36:28,560
With a magic spell, Monkey 
transformed himself back again.

883
01:36:29,840 --> 01:36:34,320
'Look around,' he cried, 'and 
you will see that I am Monkey.'

884
01:36:35,440 --> 01:36:41,040
When Pigsy turned and saw Monkey, with 
his sharp little teeth and big smile,  

885
01:36:41,040 --> 01:36:47,920
his red eyes, flat head and hairy face, 
he ran like the wind back to his cave.

886
01:36:48,880 --> 01:36:54,400
Monkey cried after him, 'Where are you going? 
If you go up to Heaven, I will follow you.  

887
01:36:54,400 --> 01:36:59,760
And if you go down to the deepest part 
of Hell, I will follow you there too.'

888
01:37:01,360 --> 01:37:05,840
Monkey followed the creature to his 
cave and it came out waving a fork.

889
01:37:06,960 --> 01:37:13,600
They fought together all night, but at last 
the creature leapt back into the cave and  

890
01:37:13,600 --> 01:37:21,360
locked the door. Monkey now saw the name of 
the cave on a rock: it was Cloud-Ladder Cave.

891
01:37:22,960 --> 01:37:27,120
'I had better return to my Master 
now, because he might want something,'  

892
01:37:27,120 --> 01:37:31,120
Monkey thought. 'I can always 
return and catch this creature.'  

893
01:37:32,000 --> 01:37:36,880
And leaping from one cloud to 
another, he was soon back at the farm.

894
01:37:38,320 --> 01:37:41,600
No one had slept all night, 
waiting for Monkey's return.  

895
01:37:42,640 --> 01:37:46,480
Tripitaka was sitting with the 
old man when Monkey arrived.

896
01:37:47,520 --> 01:37:49,920
'Master, here I am,' he said.

897
01:37:51,840 --> 01:37:56,560
'Did you have to go a long way to 
catch the creature?' asked Tripitaka.

898
01:37:57,600 --> 01:38:03,200
'That is no ordinary creature. He used to 
live in Heaven, where he was in charge of  

899
01:38:03,200 --> 01:38:09,280
water-spirits. But he did wrong and he was 
sent down to Earth as a pig-like creature.  

900
01:38:10,000 --> 01:38:18,000
He still has all his magic powers. I chased him to 
his mountain cave, where he fetched a large fork  

901
01:38:18,000 --> 01:38:24,960
and we fought all night. As the sun came up, 
he gave up the fight and locked himself in his  

902
01:38:24,960 --> 01:38:32,240
cave. I was going to beat down the door, but I 
knew it was going to take some time. I thought  

903
01:38:32,880 --> 01:38:37,760
Master might be getting anxious 
so I wanted to report back here.'

904
01:38:39,840 --> 01:38:44,720
'Monkey King,' said old Mr 
Kao, 'you have driven him away,  

905
01:38:45,280 --> 01:38:53,120
but he is certain to come back. If you can get him 
for us, you can have half of all that is ours.'

906
01:38:54,560 --> 01:38:59,120
'I think you worry too much about 
him. He knows that he eats a lot.  

907
01:38:59,840 --> 01:39:06,640
But he has also done a lot of work around 
here. He feels that his work easily pays  

908
01:39:06,640 --> 01:39:12,400
for the cost of feeding him. He is a god 
who has been sent to Earth as a punishment.  

909
01:39:13,280 --> 01:39:18,160
It seems that he has done no harm 
to your daughter,' said Monkey.

910
01:39:18,960 --> 01:39:24,320
'It is true,' said old Mr Kao, 
'that he has done her no harm.  

911
01:39:25,040 --> 01:39:31,120
But it is very bad for our family 
name. Everywhere I go, I hear,  

912
01:39:31,120 --> 01:39:38,400
"Mr Kao has taken a dirty creature for his 
daughter's husband." What can I say to that?'

913
01:39:39,760 --> 01:39:47,120
'Monkey,' said Tripitaka, 'do you not think that 
you should return? Have one more fight with him  

914
01:39:47,120 --> 01:39:51,120
and see if you can find a way to 
end this difficult situation.'

915
01:39:52,880 --> 01:39:58,400
'Don't worry. I was only having a little 
game with him. This time I will catch him  

916
01:39:58,400 --> 01:40:05,200
and bring him back here. Look after my Master 
until I get back!' Monkey said to Mr Kao.

917
01:40:06,800 --> 01:40:11,120
Monkey disappeared into the clouds 
and soon arrived at the cave.  

918
01:40:12,000 --> 01:40:17,520
This time, Pigsy was asleep in his cave 
when Monkey broke the door in pieces.  

919
01:40:18,640 --> 01:40:22,560
Angrily, Pigsy jumped out of 
bed and took up his fork again.

920
01:40:23,680 --> 01:40:30,400
'You dirty rat! What do you think you are doing? 
It is a crime to break down someone else's door!'  

921
01:40:30,400 --> 01:40:36,960
shouted Pigsy. 'I remember you now...' 
he said, looking more closely at Monkey.  

922
01:40:37,920 --> 01:40:43,920
'You once lived in a cave behind a 
Water Curtain. How did you get here?'

923
01:40:45,360 --> 01:40:50,880
'I am a priest now. I am going with 
a Chinese pilgrim called Tripitaka  

924
01:40:50,880 --> 01:40:52,640
to fetch scriptures from India.'

925
01:40:54,000 --> 01:41:01,360
The fork fell from Pigsy's hand. 'Where is 
the pilgrim?' he said. 'Take me to him.'

926
01:41:02,720 --> 01:41:05,280
'Why do you want to see him?' asked Monkey.

927
01:41:06,320 --> 01:41:12,080
'The Goddess Kuan-yin put me here to prepare 
myself for the arrival of a pilgrim who I  

928
01:41:12,080 --> 01:41:19,280
must follow. After doing this, I will receive 
wisdom. I have been waiting for this pilgrim for  

929
01:41:19,280 --> 01:41:26,480
years. Why did you not tell me that you are his 
follower? Why did you prefer to fight with me?'

930
01:41:27,840 --> 01:41:34,080
'I am not so sure that your story is true. If 
you really want to follow my Master to India,  

931
01:41:34,080 --> 01:41:38,800
you must promise that this story is 
true. Then I will take you to him.'

932
01:41:40,960 --> 01:41:47,840
Pigsy threw himself down on his knees and 
bowed repeatedly. 'I promise holy Buddha, this  

933
01:41:47,840 --> 01:41:57,280
is true - every word. If it is not true, let the 
judges in Heaven cut me into ten thousand pieces.'

934
01:41:59,040 --> 01:42:05,840
'I believe you,' said Monkey, 'but give 
me your fork.' Then Monkey took a hair,  

935
01:42:06,480 --> 01:42:11,600
blew on it with his magic breath, and 
changed it into a long thick string.

936
01:42:12,640 --> 01:42:18,800
He tied Pigsy's hands behind his back, took 
him by the ear and pulled him along with him.

937
01:42:20,320 --> 01:42:25,920
When Monkey arrived at Mr Kao's farm 
with Pigsy, everyone was very happy.  

938
01:42:26,880 --> 01:42:31,760
After hearing Pigsy's story, 
Tripitaka told Monkey to untie him.  

939
01:42:32,560 --> 01:42:37,440
Tripitaka said some prayers and then 
they sat down and ate supper together.

940
01:42:38,720 --> 01:42:45,440
The next day, Tripitaka sat on the white horse 
that had been a dragon. Pigsy carried the luggage  

941
01:42:46,080 --> 01:42:50,720
and Monkey carried his cudgel, 
as they all left for the West.

942
01:42:52,000 --> 01:42:57,280
At last they came to a flat country. 
Summer had passed and autumn had come,  

943
01:42:58,000 --> 01:43:02,320
and now in front of them was a great, wild river.

944
01:43:05,520 --> 01:43:09,840
Monkey leapt into the air and 
looked far down into the water.

945
01:43:10,720 --> 01:43:17,760
'Master,' he reported, 'this will not be easy. 
For me, it will not be difficult because I can  

946
01:43:17,760 --> 01:43:24,080
jump across in one leap, but for you it 
will be impossible. When I looked down,  

947
01:43:24,640 --> 01:43:28,480
I saw that this river is twelve 
thousand kilometres across.'  

948
01:43:30,080 --> 01:43:36,400
Tripitaka was very unhappy but, looking down, 
he saw a rock with some writing which said  

949
01:43:37,040 --> 01:43:41,280
River of Sands. Under that, in 
small letters, were the words:

950
01:43:42,080 --> 01:43:45,920
In the River of Sands, twelve thousand wide,

951
01:43:46,480 --> 01:43:50,160
In Dead Waters, fifteen thousand deep,

952
01:43:50,960 --> 01:43:53,680
Nothing will stay on the water -

953
01:43:53,680 --> 01:43:56,960
Even the lightest flower 
goes straight to the bottom.

954
01:43:59,040 --> 01:44:04,400
As they looked, a terrible creature came 
towards them through the water. His eyes  

955
01:44:04,400 --> 01:44:11,360
were like bright lights, and around his neck were 
nine heads. He rushed straight at the pilgrims.

956
01:44:12,560 --> 01:44:16,320
Monkey pushed Tripitaka to 
a safe place while Pigsy  

957
01:44:16,320 --> 01:44:20,800
attacked the creature with his 
fork. The creature fought hard  

958
01:44:20,800 --> 01:44:28,240
and the fight was a good one. Monkey was impatient 
to join in and at last, with a wild scream,  

959
01:44:28,240 --> 01:44:35,600
he leapt at the creature. As he brought his cudgel 
down on its head, it disappeared into the water.

960
01:44:36,880 --> 01:44:44,640
Pigsy was very angry. 'Brother, who asked you to 
fight my fight? That creature was just getting  

961
01:44:44,640 --> 01:44:49,840
tired and I had almost finished 
him. You have spoilt everything.'

962
01:44:51,040 --> 01:44:58,080
'I am sorry,' laughed Monkey. 'But I could 
not stand and watch. I have not used my  

963
01:44:58,080 --> 01:45:05,520
cudgel for months and I got so excited that I 
could not stop myself. I wanted to join the fun.'

964
01:45:07,040 --> 01:45:10,960
So, hand in hand, they returned to Tripitaka.

965
01:45:12,160 --> 01:45:15,840
'It will be your turn next time,' promised Pigsy.

966
01:45:16,800 --> 01:45:24,320
'Thank you, but I am really not at my best in 
water,' said Monkey. 'I am happier in the clouds  

967
01:45:24,320 --> 01:45:30,240
and I have enough tricks on land. If you 
can make this creature leave the river,  

968
01:45:30,240 --> 01:45:31,520
I will come and help you.'

969
01:45:33,360 --> 01:45:37,040
Pigsy went into the river and 
discovered that he had not  

970
01:45:37,040 --> 01:45:42,240
lost his water-magic. He soon found the 
creature at the bottom of the river.

971
01:45:43,680 --> 01:45:50,560
'You ugly pig,' the creature shouted. 'Can you 
not see that I am not an ordinary creature?  

972
01:45:50,560 --> 01:45:57,840
I am a god. One day, at a banquet in Heaven, 
I accidentally broke the Jade Emperor's bowl.  

973
01:45:58,400 --> 01:46:07,760
He was very angry and I was sent down here to the 
River of Sands. When I am hungry, as I am now,  

974
01:46:07,760 --> 01:46:16,240
I eat people. You would taste very good if I 
cut you up and put some sugar and salt on you.'

975
01:46:17,280 --> 01:46:20,880
'You will not eat me! You can eat my fork!'

976
01:46:21,920 --> 01:46:30,240
So again they started fighting, and they fought 
for two hours. After that, Pigsy pretended to  

977
01:46:30,240 --> 01:46:40,080
be tired and ready to stop. When he left the water 
and climbed on to the land, the creature followed.

978
01:46:40,080 --> 01:46:45,280
'Come on,' cried Pigsy. 'With 
the hard earth under our feet,  

979
01:46:45,280 --> 01:46:48,320
we will have a better fight than we did before.'

980
01:46:49,280 --> 01:46:55,840
'I know what you are trying to do,' said the 
creature. 'You are trying to get me out of the  

981
01:46:55,840 --> 01:47:03,200
river so your friend can help you. We will go 
back in the water and finish the fight there.'

982
01:47:04,400 --> 01:47:08,720
The creature refused to move, so 
they fought on the water's edge.  

983
01:47:09,600 --> 01:47:11,600
Monkey was watching from a distance.

984
01:47:12,800 --> 01:47:17,120
'Wait here,' he said to Tripitaka, 
'while I try one of my tricks.'

985
01:47:18,960 --> 01:47:23,440
Monkey leapt into the air and jumped 
straight down at the creature.  

986
01:47:24,240 --> 01:47:28,080
But the creature saw him coming 
and ran back into the water.

987
01:47:29,680 --> 01:47:33,360
'He is probably not going to 
come out again,' Monkey said.

988
01:47:34,080 --> 01:47:38,160
'This is difficult,' said Pigsy. 
'What are we going to do?'

989
01:47:39,680 --> 01:47:42,480
'Let's go and see the Master,' said Monkey.

990
01:47:44,240 --> 01:47:52,800
They told Tripitaka, who started crying loudly. 
'We will never get across,' he said sadly.

991
01:47:53,840 --> 01:47:58,800
'Don't worry,' Monkey said. 'It 
is true that we cannot get across  

992
01:47:58,800 --> 01:48:04,560
yet. That creature is a terrible 
problem, but he is not going to stop us.'

993
01:48:06,160 --> 01:48:08,720
'What are we going to do?' asked Pigsy.

994
01:48:09,920 --> 01:48:16,000
'Pigsy,' said Monkey, 'stay here with the 
Master while I go to the Southern Ocean to  

995
01:48:16,000 --> 01:48:23,600
find the Goddess Kuan-yin. This search for the 
Scriptures was her idea and she must help us now.'

996
01:48:25,360 --> 01:48:29,680
'You had better go now,' said 
Tripitaka, 'and get back here quickly.'

997
01:48:31,280 --> 01:48:36,160
Leaping through the clouds, Monkey reached 
the Southern Ocean in no time at all.  

998
01:48:37,040 --> 01:48:40,800
He found the Goddess with 
the Dragon King's daughter.

999
01:48:42,800 --> 01:48:46,640
'Why are you not looking after 
your Master?' she asked at once.

1000
01:48:47,520 --> 01:48:54,560
'When we came to the River of Sands,' said Monkey, 
'we found a creature that we cannot destroy.  

1001
01:48:54,560 --> 01:49:02,240
He is a very good fighter. My friend Pigsy tried 
hard to beat him, but he was not successful.  

1002
01:49:03,280 --> 01:49:05,040
This is why I have come to you.'

1003
01:49:06,480 --> 01:49:12,480
'Monkey, do you ever listen? It 
is the same story again and again.  

1004
01:49:13,520 --> 01:49:17,360
Why did you not say that you 
are with the Priest of T'ang?'

1005
01:49:18,560 --> 01:49:22,400
'I suppose we were too busy 
trying to catch him,' said Monkey.

1006
01:49:23,120 --> 01:49:29,120
'I put him there. I intended him to 
help the Master and his pilgrims,'  

1007
01:49:29,680 --> 01:49:36,320
said Kuan-yin. 'You did not tell him that you 
were from China and looking for the Scriptures,  

1008
01:49:36,320 --> 01:49:42,480
did you? That was your mistake. He 
is there to help you, you fool!'

1009
01:49:43,840 --> 01:49:49,760
'He is sitting at the bottom of the river 
and he is not happy,' said Monkey. 'How  

1010
01:49:49,760 --> 01:49:55,840
can I make him come out and help us? And how 
is Tripitaka going to get across the river?'

1011
01:49:57,360 --> 01:50:02,880
Kuan-yin gave a red water-bottle to 
her follower Hui-yen. She told him,

1012
01:50:03,600 --> 01:50:11,440
'Go with Monkey to the river and shout "Sandy!" 
The creature will come out at once. Take him  

1013
01:50:11,440 --> 01:50:18,640
to the Master. Then put this red water-bottle in 
the middle of the nine heads that he wears around  

1014
01:50:18,640 --> 01:50:26,560
his neck. A ship will be sent from the Gods. It 
will carry Tripitaka across the River of Sands.'

1015
01:50:28,120 --> 01:50:37,840
Hui-yen went to the river and called, 'Sandy, 
Sandy! Come out and meet the Master and his  

1016
01:50:37,840 --> 01:50:45,360
pilgrims. They are looking for the Scriptures 
and they have been here for a long time.'

1017
01:50:46,880 --> 01:50:54,160
The creature came up at once. He bowed 
politely and asked, 'Where are the pilgrims?'

1018
01:50:55,280 --> 01:50:59,360
'They are sitting over there, on 
the eastern side,' replied Hui-yen.

1019
01:51:00,400 --> 01:51:06,960
'Well,' said Sandy, looking at Pigsy, 
'that dirty creature never said a word  

1020
01:51:06,960 --> 01:51:11,680
about Scriptures and I fought 
with him for two whole days.'  

1021
01:51:12,960 --> 01:51:19,840
Then, seeing Monkey, he cried, 'Him 
too? I am not going near them.'

1022
01:51:21,280 --> 01:51:28,640
'The first is Pigsy,' said Hui-yen, 
'and the second is Monkey. They are both  

1023
01:51:28,640 --> 01:51:35,120
Tripitaka's followers and both were made 
priests by Kuan-yin. You have nothing to fear.  

1024
01:51:35,920 --> 01:51:38,560
I myself will introduce you to the Master.'

1025
01:51:40,080 --> 01:51:46,960
Sandy came out of the river, tidied himself and 
went down on his knees in front of Tripitaka.  

1026
01:51:47,680 --> 01:51:55,360
He said, 'I did not recognise you, Master, 
so forgive me for being so impolite.'

1027
01:51:56,320 --> 01:51:59,600
'You rude creature,' said Pigsy,  

1028
01:51:59,600 --> 01:52:04,400
'why did you want to fight with us, 
instead of joining us from the beginning?'

1029
01:52:05,360 --> 01:52:09,280
'Brother,' laughed Monkey, 
'don't be angry with him,  

1030
01:52:09,280 --> 01:52:14,320
because it is all our fault. We never told 
him that we are going to get the Scriptures.'

1031
01:52:15,360 --> 01:52:19,360
'Do you really want to be a priest 
in our religion?' asked Tripitaka.

1032
01:52:20,240 --> 01:52:25,120
Sandy said that he did, so Monkey 
was asked to shave Sandy's head.

1033
01:52:26,080 --> 01:52:30,960
Monkey took a knife and soon Sandy 
had no hair left on his head.

1034
01:52:32,160 --> 01:52:38,880
Sandy bowed many times in front of Tripitaka, 
but only once in front of Monkey and Pigsy.  

1035
01:52:40,080 --> 01:52:45,440
Tripitaka liked Sandy's new appearance and 
he was very pleased with his new follower.

1036
01:52:47,280 --> 01:52:51,200
'You had better be quick and start 
your boat-building,' said Hui-yen.

1037
01:52:52,560 --> 01:52:57,280
Taking the heads from his neck, Sandy 
laid them at the edge of the water  

1038
01:52:57,280 --> 01:53:02,480
in the shape of a magic square. He put 
Kuan-yin's water-bottle in the middle.  

1039
01:53:03,280 --> 01:53:08,400
At once, the heads and the bottle 
became a ship, sent by the Gods.

1040
01:53:09,440 --> 01:53:16,640
Tripitaka came down to the water and walked on to 
the holy ship. Pigsy supported him on the left,  

1041
01:53:17,200 --> 01:53:23,680
Sandy on the right. Monkey, behind him, held 
on to the white horse, which followed as well  

1042
01:53:23,680 --> 01:53:29,840
as it could. They soon arrived perfectly 
safely at the other side.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

1043
01:53:33,200 --> 01:53:34,000
CHAPTER FOUR

1044
01:53:34,960 --> 01:53:37,120
A Dead King and a Competition

1045
01:53:39,280 --> 01:53:42,640
Then Manjusri said a spell, the magician  

1046
01:53:42,640 --> 01:53:47,840
returned to his tiger shape, and the 
God rode him away over the clouds.

1047
01:53:49,840 --> 01:53:57,280
Tripitaka sat in the Great Hall of the Wood Temple 
reciting the True Scriptures. It was midnight and  

1048
01:53:57,280 --> 01:54:04,640
he was tired. Soon he lay across his reading 
desk and slept. Although his eyes were closed,  

1049
01:54:04,640 --> 01:54:11,280
he seemed to know what was happening. He heard 
a voice outside the Hall whispering 'Master.'

1050
01:54:12,720 --> 01:54:21,040
Tripitaka lifted his head. In his dream he saw 
a man who was wet from head to foot. When he  

1051
01:54:21,040 --> 01:54:28,160
looked more closely, he saw that the man was 
a king. The King told Tripitaka his story:

1052
01:54:30,560 --> 01:54:37,360
'Five years ago, the rain stopped falling, 
the grass stopped growing and all my people  

1053
01:54:37,360 --> 01:54:43,600
were dying of hunger. I prayed to the 
Gods, but still the rivers were empty.  

1054
01:54:44,560 --> 01:54:51,760
But then a magician came who could call the 
wind and the rain. I asked him to pray for rain  

1055
01:54:51,760 --> 01:55:00,080
and he did. The rain came pouring down. For the 
next two years I was very kind to this magician.  

1056
01:55:01,200 --> 01:55:06,240
Then, in spring, when the two of us were 
walking by the great water hole in my palace,  

1057
01:55:06,960 --> 01:55:14,160
I suddenly saw a white light and he pushed 
me into the hole. He covered the top of it  

1058
01:55:14,160 --> 01:55:22,720
and then made a tree grow over it. Pity me! I 
have been dead for three years and nobody knows.'

1059
01:55:24,320 --> 01:55:30,480
Tripitaka was white with fear, but at last 
he said, 'Why did nobody look for you?'

1060
01:55:31,680 --> 01:55:38,320
'Ah, with his great power the magician 
transformed himself into a man who looked like me.  

1061
01:55:38,960 --> 01:55:45,920
Now he is the king of my people. But the 
Night Spirit blew me to you and gave me  

1062
01:55:45,920 --> 01:55:51,520
hope with talk of a great Monkey King 
who can kill demons with his cudgel.'

1063
01:55:53,200 --> 01:55:56,560
'But everybody in your country 
thinks that the magician is you.  

1064
01:55:57,360 --> 01:56:01,840
My follower would be attacked if 
he tried to help,' said Tripitaka.

1065
01:56:03,120 --> 01:56:09,360
'I have a son, the Prince, who spends most 
of his time in the Palace of Golden Bells.  

1066
01:56:10,240 --> 01:56:16,720
He is not allowed to see his mother, the 
Queen, because she might say something. He  

1067
01:56:16,720 --> 01:56:23,040
knows nothing about his true father except 
that I had this piece of white jade.'

1068
01:56:24,320 --> 01:56:28,480
'But how can a poor priest like me 
get to the Palace of Golden Bells?'

1069
01:56:29,760 --> 01:56:35,440
'Tomorrow my son will hunt with three 
thousand followers, and when you give  

1070
01:56:35,440 --> 01:56:43,520
him the jade he will know what to do. But now 
I must tell my Queen everything in a dream.'

1071
01:56:46,080 --> 01:56:49,840
As he turned to go, the dead 
king hit his head on the floor  

1072
01:56:50,480 --> 01:56:56,640
and Tripitaka woke up. 'Followers!' 
he called. 'Where are my followers?'

1073
01:56:58,000 --> 01:57:05,120
'Now what?' said Pigsy. 'I was happier with 
my old life, although the food was bad.  

1074
01:57:05,840 --> 01:57:10,480
Now I am woken up in the middle of 
the night to look after a priest.'

1075
01:57:11,680 --> 01:57:17,040
'I had a strange dream,' 
said Tripitaka, uncertainly.

1076
01:57:18,240 --> 01:57:25,520
Monkey then came in and said, 'Master, your 
dreams come from your waking thoughts because  

1077
01:57:25,520 --> 01:57:32,640
you worry all the time. I think only of seeing 
Buddha in the West, and no dream comes near me.'

1078
01:57:34,080 --> 01:57:37,840
But Tripitaka made Monkey 
listen to the dead king's story.

1079
01:57:39,120 --> 01:57:43,120
'Say no more,' said Monkey. 'This is work for me!'

1080
01:57:44,480 --> 01:57:51,840
'The King left this,' said Tripitaka, 
remembering, and he gave Monkey the piece of jade.

1081
01:57:52,800 --> 01:57:58,960
Dear Monkey! He pulled a hair from his 
tail, blew on it, and said a magic spell.  

1082
01:58:00,160 --> 01:58:06,080
When a beautiful small box appeared, 
he put the piece of jade in it.

1083
01:58:06,080 --> 01:58:08,720
'In the early morning,' he told Tripitaka,  

1084
01:58:09,520 --> 01:58:16,480
'read the Scriptures in the Great Hall. I 
shall transform myself into a little priest,  

1085
01:58:16,480 --> 01:58:23,600
five centimetres high, and I shall jump into the 
box with the jade. When the Prince opens the box,  

1086
01:58:24,160 --> 01:58:28,640
I shall jump out, show him the 
jade and tell him the dream.'

1087
01:58:30,000 --> 01:58:34,400
Both the follower and his teacher 
were too excited to sleep that night.  

1088
01:58:35,280 --> 01:58:41,280
At last, the first light of morning came 
in the East. After giving whispered orders  

1089
01:58:41,280 --> 01:58:47,840
to Pigsy and Sandy to wait quietly for 
him, Monkey leapt into the air and flew.

1090
01:58:49,520 --> 01:58:57,760
At once, his red eyes found a walled city to the 
West. The sadness of its people hung in clouds  

1091
01:58:57,760 --> 01:59:05,760
over the city. But as Monkey was watching this sad 
sight, the gates opened and the huntsmen came out.  

1092
01:59:06,880 --> 01:59:11,440
It was clear from his fine clothes 
which huntsman was the Prince.

1093
01:59:12,960 --> 01:59:16,480
'Let me play a trick on 
him,' said Monkey to himself.

1094
01:59:18,320 --> 01:59:25,600
Dear Monkey! Coming down from his cloud, he 
transformed himself into a small woodland animal  

1095
01:59:26,240 --> 01:59:33,360
and ran in front of the Prince's horse. The Prince 
chased it and the huntsmen followed the Prince.  

1096
01:59:34,320 --> 01:59:38,160
Soon, Monkey had led all 
of them to the Wood Temple.

1097
01:59:40,160 --> 01:59:44,000
'Of course, I have known of 
this place,' said the Prince,  

1098
01:59:44,000 --> 01:59:47,520
'although I have never visited it. I will go in.'

1099
01:59:48,800 --> 01:59:55,200
As the Prince and his followers went into the 
Great Hall, everybody welcomed him and bowed,  

1100
01:59:55,200 --> 02:00:02,320
except Tripitaka. The angry Prince told his 
followers to take the priest and tie him up.  

1101
02:00:03,280 --> 02:00:10,800
But Monkey, now five centimetres high and in 
the box, told the Gods to protect Tripitaka,  

1102
02:00:10,800 --> 02:00:12,640
so the huntsmen could not touch him.

1103
02:00:13,680 --> 02:00:18,880
'What magic are you using,' asked 
the Prince, 'to protect yourself?'

1104
02:00:20,160 --> 02:00:27,280
'I have no magic,' replied Tripitaka. 'I am 
only a priest from China, on the way to India  

1105
02:00:27,280 --> 02:00:33,840
to fetch the Scriptures. But in this box there 
is someone who knows something very important.'

1106
02:00:35,360 --> 02:00:41,520
As he spoke, Tripitaka opened the box 
and out leapt a very small Monkey.

1107
02:00:42,720 --> 02:00:47,280
The Prince laughed and said, 'What 
can that little creature know!'

1108
02:00:48,560 --> 02:00:55,040
But Monkey, to the great surprise of everybody, 
used his magic to return to his full size.  

1109
02:00:56,240 --> 02:01:02,800
'Prince,' he said, 'please listen to me. 
Five years ago your country had no food  

1110
02:01:02,800 --> 02:01:09,360
because no rain fell, but then a magician 
came and he brought rain. Is this true?'

1111
02:01:10,240 --> 02:01:12,800
'Yes, yes, yes. Go on!'

1112
02:01:13,760 --> 02:01:15,360
'And what happened to the magician?'

1113
02:01:16,800 --> 02:01:23,120
'Three years ago, when he and my father were 
walking in the garden, a magic wind blew a  

1114
02:01:23,120 --> 02:01:29,760
piece of jade out of the King's hand and the 
magician went back to his mountains with it.  

1115
02:01:30,560 --> 02:01:35,840
But the King, my father, still misses the 
magician and he has locked the garden.'

1116
02:01:37,680 --> 02:01:44,400
Monkey laughed, but he asked the huntsmen to move 
away so he could speak privately to the Prince.  

1117
02:01:45,440 --> 02:01:52,400
'Sir, it was your father who disappeared. The man 
in the palace is the magician who brought rain.'

1118
02:01:53,360 --> 02:01:56,160
'That is not true!' said the Prince.

1119
02:01:56,880 --> 02:01:59,920
'Here is the piece of jade,' said Monkey.

1120
02:02:00,720 --> 02:02:06,000
'You stole the jade!' shouted the 
Prince to the priest. 'Take him away!'

1121
02:02:07,120 --> 02:02:13,760
Tripitaka shouted fearfully to Monkey, 
'Oh Monkey, you fool. What have you done?'

1122
02:02:14,640 --> 02:02:23,280
'Wait!' cried Monkey. 'I am the Monkey King 
and a follower of Tripitaka. Last night  

1123
02:02:23,280 --> 02:02:27,120
in this temple your father 
came to my Master in a dream.  

1124
02:02:27,920 --> 02:02:33,040
He told him that the magician had pushed 
him into a great water hole in the palace  

1125
02:02:33,040 --> 02:02:38,480
and changed into a man who looked like 
him. He could then pretend to be the king.

1126
02:02:39,600 --> 02:02:45,040
I changed into a hunted animal to lead 
you here because I wanted to tell you  

1127
02:02:45,040 --> 02:02:52,160
this. Will you believe my story or not?' The 
young Prince did not know what to believe.  

1128
02:02:53,680 --> 02:03:00,000
'Ride home,' suggested Monkey. 'Take 
this piece of jade with you and ask  

1129
02:03:00,000 --> 02:03:04,800
your mother, the Queen, if the 
present king is her husband.'

1130
02:03:06,320 --> 02:03:09,600
The young Prince agreed and 
went back to the palace.  

1131
02:03:10,640 --> 02:03:15,440
He found his mother, the Queen, still worried 
about a dream she had had the night before.

1132
02:03:17,040 --> 02:03:21,600
'Mother,' said the Prince, 'forgive 
my words before I speak them.  

1133
02:03:22,720 --> 02:03:27,440
Compare your life with my 
father in the last three years  

1134
02:03:27,440 --> 02:03:33,840
with the years before that, and tell 
me if his love is as warm today.'

1135
02:03:35,120 --> 02:03:37,760
In answer the Queen recited:

1136
02:03:39,040 --> 02:03:46,720
'Three years ago something warm and kind. These 
last three years has been as cold as ice.'

1137
02:03:48,960 --> 02:03:52,320
The Prince told his mother everything 
that he had heard that day.  

1138
02:03:53,440 --> 02:03:56,320
Then he showed her the piece of jade.

1139
02:03:57,680 --> 02:04:06,640
'Oh, my son,' said the Queen, 'when you came I 
was crying because of a dream I had last night.  

1140
02:04:06,640 --> 02:04:14,080
I dreamt I saw your father. His head was 
under water and he was dead. But his soul  

1141
02:04:14,080 --> 02:04:22,160
had visited a priest of T'ang and asked him to 
destroy the magician. He also asked him to save  

1142
02:04:22,160 --> 02:04:28,880
his own body from where it had been thrown. 
Go quickly and ask that priest to help us.'

1143
02:04:30,400 --> 02:04:33,600
The young prince ran out, jumped on his horse,  

1144
02:04:34,160 --> 02:04:41,280
rode back to the Wood Temple and asked the 
pilgrims to find his father. So the next  

1145
02:04:41,280 --> 02:04:48,560
night Monkey and Pigsy were at the gates of the 
locked Flower Garden. But Monkey had told Pigsy  

1146
02:04:48,560 --> 02:04:54,000
that there was gold at the bottom of the water 
hole. He had said nothing about the dead king.

1147
02:04:56,080 --> 02:05:00,080
Pigsy brought his fork down on the 
lock of the gates and broke it.  

1148
02:05:00,960 --> 02:05:06,240
Inside the garden, Monkey could not stop 
himself jumping and shouting happily.

1149
02:05:06,880 --> 02:05:13,120
'Brother,' said Pigsy, 'you will 
ruin us, making all that noise!'

1150
02:05:14,080 --> 02:05:17,920
'Why are you trying to make 
me nervous?' said Monkey.

1151
02:05:19,120 --> 02:05:23,520
They found the tree that the magician 
had planted on top of the hole.  

1152
02:05:24,640 --> 02:05:29,760
'Now, Pigsy, the gold is hidden 
under this tree,' said Monkey.

1153
02:05:30,800 --> 02:05:36,400
At once, the fool Pigsy hit the tree 
with his fork until it fell down.  

1154
02:05:37,280 --> 02:05:44,320
Then he used his nose to dig under it until, 
about a metre down, he found a big stone.  

1155
02:05:45,440 --> 02:05:51,280
'Brother!' he cried. 'This is 
luck. The gold will be under this.'

1156
02:05:52,720 --> 02:05:56,320
Pigsy used his nose again 
and lifted the big stone.  

1157
02:05:57,520 --> 02:06:05,840
Below it something was shining. 'That is 
the gold!' cried Pigsy. But looking closer,  

1158
02:06:05,840 --> 02:06:10,160
they saw it was the light of the 
stars and the moon in the water.

1159
02:06:12,000 --> 02:06:18,560
Monkey made his cudgel grow until it was 
ten metres long, and Pigsy climbed down it.  

1160
02:06:19,600 --> 02:06:27,360
When he was in the water, he began to swim. Monkey 
called down to him, 'The gold is at the bottom.'

1161
02:06:28,720 --> 02:06:36,720
So Pigsy dived down and, opening his eyes 
again, saw a door with a sign on it that said  

1162
02:06:36,720 --> 02:06:43,840
The Palace at the Bottom of the Water Hole. 
Pigsy went in and a servant called out,  

1163
02:06:44,720 --> 02:06:50,720
'Great King, something awful has happened 
- a priest with a long nose has come in.

1164
02:06:52,320 --> 02:06:59,440
The Dragon King of the Water Hole was not 
surprised. 'That must be Pigsy,' he explained.  

1165
02:06:59,440 --> 02:07:03,600
'He has come with the Monkey King 
to find the dishonest magician.  

1166
02:07:04,640 --> 02:07:09,200
Please come in and sit down,' he called to Pigsy.

1167
02:07:11,280 --> 02:07:18,960
Pigsy, happy and wet, sat in the best 
seat and asked, 'Where is the gold?'

1168
02:07:19,920 --> 02:07:22,240
'I am sorry,' said the Dragon King,  

1169
02:07:22,960 --> 02:07:30,560
'but I live down here in this hole and never 
see the sky above. Where would I get gold from?'

1170
02:07:31,680 --> 02:07:39,840
'Oh, please!' said Pigsy. 'I know it is here 
somewhere, so you had better bring it out.'

1171
02:07:41,200 --> 02:07:46,800
'I have one thing that is of value. 
You can look,' said the Dragon King.  

1172
02:07:47,920 --> 02:07:55,840
He led Pigsy to the body of the dead king. 
Pigsy went back up to Monkey. Monkey told him  

1173
02:07:55,840 --> 02:08:02,640
that the body was better than gold. So Pigsy 
dived back down again and brought the body up.

1174
02:08:04,320 --> 02:08:08,640
Monkey looked closely at the body, 
which had been dead for three years.  

1175
02:08:09,760 --> 02:08:15,840
He asked Pigsy, 'After three years, 
how can it still look so fresh?'

1176
02:08:16,960 --> 02:08:25,680
'The Dragon King used a magic stone to keep it 
like that,' Pigsy answered. 'That was a bit of  

1177
02:08:25,680 --> 02:08:32,720
luck,' said Monkey. 'But we must still get his 
enemy and make him pay for this terrible murder.  

1178
02:08:33,520 --> 02:08:39,520
And we will be thanked for our good work. 
Quickly, Pigsy, carry the King away.'

1179
02:08:40,720 --> 02:08:43,440
'Where to?' asked Pigsy.

1180
02:08:44,400 --> 02:08:48,560
'To the temple,' said Monkey, 
'to show him to Tripitaka.'

1181
02:08:49,600 --> 02:08:53,600
'What an idea!' Pigsy complained to himself.  

1182
02:08:54,320 --> 02:09:01,040
'I was tricked into doing this job. I 
do not want to carry this dead body.'

1183
02:09:02,400 --> 02:09:05,520
'Hurry, Pigsy,' said Monkey impatiently.

1184
02:09:06,560 --> 02:09:10,880
'I am not going to carry it,' said Pigsy.

1185
02:09:11,920 --> 02:09:18,000
'If you do not want to be beaten, you 
will carry it away now,' said Monkey.

1186
02:09:18,000 --> 02:09:23,280
Pigsy feared the cudgel, so he lifted 
up the dead body and put it on his back.

1187
02:09:24,080 --> 02:09:31,920
'This Monkey,' he said to himself, 'has 
played a dirty trick on me, but he will be  

1188
02:09:31,920 --> 02:09:40,160
sorry. When we get back to the temple, I will tell 
Tripitaka that Monkey can bring the dead to life.  

1189
02:09:41,200 --> 02:09:48,480
Monkey will say that he cannot. And I 
will tell Tripitaka to recite the spell.  

1190
02:09:49,440 --> 02:09:59,840
Monkey's head will hurt, but I will not be 
happy until his brains shoot out of his head.'

1191
02:09:59,840 --> 02:10:04,160
They took the body back to the 
temple and showed it to Tripitaka.  

1192
02:10:05,120 --> 02:10:07,680
He told Monkey to bring it back to life.

1193
02:10:09,360 --> 02:10:13,120
'Only Yama, King of Death, 
can do that,' said Monkey.

1194
02:10:13,760 --> 02:10:20,400
'Don't believe him!' cried Pigsy. 
'Just tighten that cap on his head.'

1195
02:10:22,160 --> 02:10:29,360
Poor Monkey! He was soon holding his head in 
great pain as Tripitaka recited the spell.  

1196
02:10:30,080 --> 02:10:33,040
The cap became tighter and tighter.

1197
02:10:34,080 --> 02:10:38,080
'But Master,' said Monkey, 
'what will happen if I fail?'

1198
02:10:39,440 --> 02:10:42,000
'If someone puts a good breath into him,  

1199
02:10:42,000 --> 02:10:48,640
he will be himself again, even after 
three years under water,' said Tripitaka.

1200
02:10:50,960 --> 02:10:56,400
Pigsy at once offered his breath, but 
Tripitaka knew that it was not pure.  

1201
02:10:57,040 --> 02:11:04,080
Pigsy had eaten the bodies of humans. So 
he asked for Monkey, whose food had been  

1202
02:11:04,080 --> 02:11:12,560
only apples and food from the forest. Monkey blew 
hard into the King's mouth and his soul returned.

1203
02:11:14,000 --> 02:11:19,600
Then they all went back to the city to find the 
magician who had taken the appearance of the King.  

1204
02:11:21,200 --> 02:11:24,480
When they were led to him, they refused to bow.

1205
02:11:26,000 --> 02:11:30,400
'And who are you?' asked 
the false king, surprised.

1206
02:11:31,360 --> 02:11:38,000
'My Master,' said Monkey, 'is called 
Tripitaka and he is like a younger brother  

1207
02:11:38,000 --> 02:11:46,400
to the Emperor of China. I am his main 
follower.' Then he told the false king  

1208
02:11:46,400 --> 02:11:52,480
about Pigsy and Sandy, but he introduced 
the true king as a temple servant.

1209
02:11:53,680 --> 02:12:00,800
The false king wanted to know more about this 
'temple servant'. He looked at the true king,  

1210
02:12:00,800 --> 02:12:06,960
who was afraid of him, but Monkey whispered, 
'It is all right! I will speak for you.'

1211
02:12:08,560 --> 02:12:14,880
Dear Monkey! He stepped forwards and cried 
to the magician in a loud, clear voice.  

1212
02:12:16,320 --> 02:12:23,440
'Oh, King, this old man has had some 
hard times in his life. Five years ago,  

1213
02:12:23,440 --> 02:12:31,280
disaster came to his family when Heaven sent no 
rain and people died because there was no water.  

1214
02:12:32,160 --> 02:12:40,480
Then from the mountains came a magician who helped 
the people. But he then destroyed this man's life.  

1215
02:12:41,120 --> 02:12:47,840
He pushed him into a great water hole in the 
palace and became a false king of the people.  

1216
02:12:48,560 --> 02:12:57,120
But I have returned life to the dead man and 
he should be king again - not this magician.'

1217
02:12:58,880 --> 02:13:02,160
The magician felt fear deep in his heart.  

1218
02:13:03,040 --> 02:13:07,760
Taking a sword from a soldier, he 
jumped on a cloud and disappeared.

1219
02:13:09,120 --> 02:13:17,040
Both Sandy and Pigsy were very angry. 'Now we 
will never be able to find him,' they shouted.

1220
02:13:18,560 --> 02:13:26,400
Dear Monkey! Telling Pigsy and Sandy to take 
good care of the Prince, the King, his ministers,  

1221
02:13:26,400 --> 02:13:34,640
the Queen and Tripitaka, he suddenly leapt into 
the clouds. Looking down, he saw the magician  

1222
02:13:34,640 --> 02:13:41,920
running to the North-east. He shouted, 'Where 
do you think you are going? Monkey has come!'

1223
02:13:42,960 --> 02:13:46,320
'Keep out of my way,' shouted the magician.

1224
02:13:48,640 --> 02:13:55,600
Monkey fought a terrible fight with his cudgel 
against the magician and his sword, but suddenly  

1225
02:13:55,600 --> 02:14:01,840
the magician escaped back to the city. 
He transformed himself into someone who  

1226
02:14:01,840 --> 02:14:08,560
looked like Tripitaka. Monkey followed 
him but did not dare use his cudgel.

1227
02:14:10,000 --> 02:14:14,640
'Which is the real Tripitaka?' 
he shouted to Pigsy and Sandy.

1228
02:14:15,760 --> 02:14:20,560
'We do not know,' they 
answered. 'We have no idea.'

1229
02:14:22,080 --> 02:14:25,840
'Master, recite your spell,' called Monkey.

1230
02:14:26,960 --> 02:14:34,560
The real Tripitaka at once recited. Pigsy lifted 
up his fork as the magician flew up into the air.  

1231
02:14:35,360 --> 02:14:41,120
Dear Pigsy! He chased the magician, 
with Sandy and Monkey close behind him.

1232
02:14:42,960 --> 02:14:49,760
What a fight there was then, with three 
wild priests hitting and kicking at one  

1233
02:14:49,760 --> 02:14:57,360
terrible ugly creature again and again. In the 
end, Monkey leapt above the creature, and he  

1234
02:14:57,360 --> 02:15:05,440
was going to cut him in half with his cudgel 
when a voice said, 'Monkey, stop the fight.'

1235
02:15:07,200 --> 02:15:11,680
It was the God Manjusri. He 
had come down from Heaven  

1236
02:15:11,680 --> 02:15:16,080
with a magic mirror which showed 
demons in their true form.

1237
02:15:17,760 --> 02:15:24,240
'But I do not understand,' said Monkey. 
'In this mirror, the magician is a tiger.'

1238
02:15:25,360 --> 02:15:32,400
'Yes,' said Manjusri. 'As a magician, 
he was acting under Buddha's orders.'

1239
02:15:33,440 --> 02:15:40,640
'What!' cried Monkey. 'The magician is 
protected by Buddha! How can that be?'

1240
02:15:42,080 --> 02:15:45,520
'Let me explain,' said Manjusri.  

1241
02:15:46,640 --> 02:15:52,640
'In the beginning, the true king pleased 
Buddha so much that he sent me to fetch  

1242
02:15:52,640 --> 02:15:58,480
him to the Western Heaven. But I said 
something to the King that offended him.  

1243
02:15:59,200 --> 02:16:07,520
He told his soldiers to throw me into the river. 
Then Buddha sent this magician to throw the King  

1244
02:16:07,520 --> 02:16:14,560
into the water hole for three years. But 
now, with your help, he has been forgiven.'

1245
02:16:16,160 --> 02:16:19,360
'Yes, but the people of the city?' asked Monkey.

1246
02:16:20,400 --> 02:16:28,000
'Nothing has happened to them. During these three 
years, rain has fallen and there has been peace.'

1247
02:16:29,040 --> 02:16:31,840
'And the Queen, who has 
slept with him as his wife?'

1248
02:16:33,280 --> 02:16:40,160
'He has not been a husband to her,' was 
the answer. 'He is not a whole man.'

1249
02:16:41,840 --> 02:16:50,000
'Then take him away,' said Monkey. 'He can thank 
you for saving him.' Manjusri said a spell,  

1250
02:16:50,800 --> 02:16:56,720
the magician returned to his tiger shape, 
and the God rode him away over the clouds.

1251
02:16:58,479 --> 02:17:02,000
As the pilgrims travelled further 
on their journey to the West,  

1252
02:17:02,720 --> 02:17:06,080
they heard a noise that 
sounded like a thousand voices.

1253
02:17:07,600 --> 02:17:14,720
Dear Monkey! He leapt high into the clouds, 
looked down, and at a little distance he saw  

1254
02:17:14,720 --> 02:17:22,400
a hill outside a city. There, a great crowd of 
Buddhist priests were carrying bricks and wood  

1255
02:17:22,399 --> 02:17:28,960
for building. They were hot and tired and crying 
out to the God of Power to give them strength.

1256
02:17:30,560 --> 02:17:33,840
'They are going to build 
a temple,' thought Monkey.  

1257
02:17:34,800 --> 02:17:40,720
But suddenly the gates of the city 
opened and two Taoist priests came out.  

1258
02:17:41,760 --> 02:17:46,640
Monkey saw at once that the Buddhists 
were afraid of them. He thought,  

1259
02:17:47,280 --> 02:17:55,840
'This must be the city I have heard about. The 
religion of Buddha has been destroyed here.'

1260
02:17:55,840 --> 02:17:59,680
Monkey transformed himself into a Taoist magician,  

1261
02:18:00,479 --> 02:18:04,639
walked towards the two young 
Taoist priests and bowed low.

1262
02:18:06,240 --> 02:18:09,840
'Can a poor Taoist find food in this city?'

1263
02:18:10,479 --> 02:18:19,280
'Oh, yes,' said the priests. 'Even the King is 
pleased to give food to Taoists. Twenty years ago  

1264
02:18:19,280 --> 02:18:25,679
there was not enough food in this place 
and it was saved by three Taoist Immortals  

1265
02:18:25,680 --> 02:18:33,040
who came out of the sky. They can bring 
wind or rain or turn stones into gold.'

1266
02:18:34,560 --> 02:18:40,320
'Your king is lucky to have these 
Immortals here. I would like to meet him.'

1267
02:18:41,680 --> 02:18:48,400
'That is no problem,' said the priests. 
'But first we must count those Buddhists  

1268
02:18:48,399 --> 02:18:50,319
and check that they are working well.'

1269
02:18:51,600 --> 02:18:56,320
'But they are priests, like us! 
We should not make them work.'

1270
02:18:57,520 --> 02:19:03,840
'Well, when we had no food, the Buddhists 
prayed to Buddha with no success at all.  

1271
02:19:04,800 --> 02:19:13,440
We Taoists prayed to our gods and we were 
successful. So they are not really priests and we  

1272
02:19:13,439 --> 02:19:20,639
should really destroy their temples. But now 
they work for us as builders and cleaners.'

1273
02:19:22,000 --> 02:19:25,520
'Then I cannot meet your masters,' Monkey said,  

1274
02:19:26,160 --> 02:19:31,200
'because I am looking for an uncle 
who became a Buddhist priest.'

1275
02:19:32,800 --> 02:19:36,960
'That is no problem,' they replied. 'Take our list  

1276
02:19:36,960 --> 02:19:42,560
and check while we wait here. See 
if your uncle is among our priests.'

1277
02:19:44,800 --> 02:19:48,240
As Monkey walked towards 
the priests with the list,  

1278
02:19:48,240 --> 02:19:50,880
they all went down on their knees in front of him.

1279
02:19:52,000 --> 02:19:54,720
'Please don't harm us, Father!' they said.  

1280
02:19:55,359 --> 02:20:00,639
'We have all worked hard and we 
have never been ill or missed work.'

1281
02:20:01,760 --> 02:20:05,520
Monkey told them to get up. He said that they did  

1282
02:20:05,520 --> 02:20:09,680
not need to fear him - he was 
only looking for his uncle.

1283
02:20:11,200 --> 02:20:17,840
Hearing this, they all crowded near him. 
'Which of us do you want?' they asked.

1284
02:20:18,880 --> 02:20:22,400
Monkey laughed. 'You are priests!' he said.  

1285
02:20:23,280 --> 02:20:26,880
'Why do you work as servants 
instead of reading the Scriptures?'

1286
02:20:27,760 --> 02:20:35,680
'Ah, don't laugh at us,' cried the 
priests. 'Our King has chosen other masters  

1287
02:20:35,680 --> 02:20:42,720
and we do what they tell us. The three 
Immortals are very powerful and can perform  

1288
02:20:42,720 --> 02:20:51,440
a lot of magic. Now they are using magic to 
keep the King young. That is why he obeys them.'

1289
02:20:52,479 --> 02:20:55,280
'Why do you not run away?' asked Monkey.

1290
02:20:56,240 --> 02:21:00,160
'There are pictures of us 
in every part of the country  

1291
02:21:00,160 --> 02:21:07,599
and there are police everywhere. Many of us 
have taken our own lives. But the spirits  

1292
02:21:07,600 --> 02:21:15,201
tell us that one day a pilgrim will come and 
with him is a follower called the Monkey King.  

1293
02:21:15,840 --> 02:21:21,520
He will use his great powers to 
right wrongs, and he will free us.'

1294
02:21:23,439 --> 02:21:30,080
Monkey went back to the two Taoist priests. 
They asked him if he had found his relative.

1295
02:21:31,439 --> 02:21:38,879
'They are all relatives of mine,' replied 
Monkey. 'Two hundred on my father's side  

1296
02:21:38,880 --> 02:21:44,640
and three hundred on my mother's. 
I would like you to free them.'

1297
02:21:45,840 --> 02:21:48,480
'We cannot do that!' said the priests.  

1298
02:21:49,120 --> 02:21:56,880
'One or two of them can stop work if they are ill, 
but all of them? Impossible! You must be mad!'

1299
02:21:58,319 --> 02:22:04,319
'Really?' said Monkey and, taking his 
cudgel, he killed them where they stood.

1300
02:22:06,800 --> 02:22:14,080
The Buddhists came running. 'Oh, what have you 
done!' they said. 'The people will say that we  

1301
02:22:14,080 --> 02:22:22,240
killed the priests! You must come to the King 
at once and explain that you are responsible.'

1302
02:22:22,240 --> 02:22:28,080
'I am not what you think I am,' said Monkey. 
'I am the one who has come to free you.'

1303
02:22:28,880 --> 02:22:35,280
'But you are a murderer!' said the Buddhist 
priests. 'The spirits described the one who  

1304
02:22:35,280 --> 02:22:42,880
will free us. He has a flat head, bright 
red eyes, a hairy face and no chin.'

1305
02:22:44,000 --> 02:22:47,680
Monkey transformed himself 
back from a Taoist priest  

1306
02:22:47,680 --> 02:22:52,080
into himself, and the Buddhists 
bowed in front of him.

1307
02:22:53,359 --> 02:23:00,479
'Now go away from here!' cried Monkey. 'But 
first I shall give you some protecting magic.'

1308
02:23:01,760 --> 02:23:05,440
Dear Monkey! He pulled out a handful of his hairs,  

1309
02:23:06,000 --> 02:23:10,560
bit them into pieces and gave a 
small piece to each of the Buddhists.

1310
02:23:11,920 --> 02:23:19,920
'Put this behind your ear. If you are in any 
danger, press your ear and call out "Monkey King!"  

1311
02:23:20,800 --> 02:23:25,760
I will come at once to help you, even 
if I am thousands of kilometres away.'

1312
02:23:27,760 --> 02:23:34,720
Some of the braver priests tested the 
hairs and called out 'Monkey King!' At once  

1313
02:23:34,720 --> 02:23:41,920
a thunder god with a great cudgel appeared. 
'If you say "Quiet", he will disappear,'  

1314
02:23:41,920 --> 02:23:47,040
Monkey told them. And at the 
word 'Quiet', he disappeared.

1315
02:23:48,640 --> 02:23:53,440
'Don't go far from this place and 
there will be news for you soon,'  

1316
02:23:53,439 --> 02:23:59,839
Monkey called as the priests departed. He 
left to tell Tripitaka what had happened.

1317
02:24:01,200 --> 02:24:06,000
As the pilgrims entered the city, 
some people were afraid of them.  

1318
02:24:06,880 --> 02:24:14,080
But an old Buddhist priest recognised Monkey 
and shouted, 'I have dreamt of you, Monkey  

1319
02:24:14,080 --> 02:24:19,920
King. Thanks to you, we are not 
ghosts - we are living men.'

1320
02:24:21,680 --> 02:24:29,520
That night, Monkey's head was so full of plans for 
the next day that he could not sleep. He got up,  

1321
02:24:30,160 --> 02:24:35,840
looked down into the street and saw that the 
Taoists were all celebrating in the temple.  

1322
02:24:36,800 --> 02:24:39,200
They were led by the three Immortals.

1323
02:24:41,040 --> 02:24:44,399
At once, Monkey went to find Pigsy and Sandy.  

1324
02:24:45,520 --> 02:24:48,880
'Come and have some fun,' 
he whispered in Sandy's ear.

1325
02:24:49,920 --> 02:24:56,000
'Who wants fun in the middle of 
the night?' said Sandy, sleepily.

1326
02:24:56,000 --> 02:25:04,160
'The Taoist Temple has plenty of food in it,' 
said Monkey. 'Bread, cake, fruit, sweets...'

1327
02:25:05,200 --> 02:25:12,240
Pigsy woke up at the sound of a list of 
food. 'Brother, I am coming too,' he cried.

1328
02:25:13,280 --> 02:25:21,439
When they arrived at the temple, Pigsy could not 
wait. 'They are all still praying!' he complained.

1329
02:25:22,319 --> 02:25:25,840
'I will soon stop that,' said Monkey,  

1330
02:25:25,840 --> 02:25:32,880
and he blew hard. A great wind passed through 
the temple, blowing everything on to the ground  

1331
02:25:32,880 --> 02:25:38,720
and putting all the lights out. Frightened 
in the dark, all the Taoists ran away.

1332
02:25:39,920 --> 02:25:44,480
The three pilgrims went inside and the 
three of them finished all the food.

1333
02:25:45,680 --> 02:25:51,920
But a little Taoist remembered that he had left 
his hand-bell in the temple and went back for it.  

1334
02:25:52,880 --> 02:25:59,920
He opened the door and saw that all the food was 
gone. He ran away to fetch the three Immortals.

1335
02:26:01,040 --> 02:26:05,840
When they came, one of them thought 
that their gods had eaten the food.

1336
02:26:06,880 --> 02:26:11,920
'Let's pray to them,' the Immortal 
said, 'for long life for the King.'

1337
02:26:13,120 --> 02:26:15,519
Then Monkey jumped out and called to them.  

1338
02:26:16,160 --> 02:26:23,840
'How could you be such fools?' he said. 'We 
are not gods, we are priests from China. We  

1339
02:26:23,840 --> 02:26:29,680
have eaten all your food and your king will 
have to go somewhere else for a long life.'

1340
02:26:31,040 --> 02:26:33,840
The Taoist Immortals attacked the pilgrims,  

1341
02:26:34,479 --> 02:26:41,120
but Monkey took Sandy in one hand and Pigsy in 
the other and leapt on to a cloud with them.  

1342
02:26:42,160 --> 02:26:48,559
In no time, they were back in their beds, in the 
hotel where they were staying with Tripitaka.

1343
02:26:50,080 --> 02:26:57,040
Next day, the King was very angry when he heard 
that three Buddhist pilgrims wanted to see him.  

1344
02:26:57,920 --> 02:27:00,000
But one of his ministers stepped forward.

1345
02:27:01,439 --> 02:27:06,639
'The country of T'ang is fifty 
thousand kilometres away,' he said.  

1346
02:27:07,600 --> 02:27:14,640
'If they really come from there, they 
must have magic powers. Let's hear them.'

1347
02:27:15,600 --> 02:27:18,720
So the King allowed the pilgrims to come in,  

1348
02:27:19,920 --> 02:27:26,560
but before they could speak, three important 
Taoists came in and made a report to the King.

1349
02:27:27,520 --> 02:27:34,320
'Yesterday,' they said, 'these three killed two 
of our followers and helped five hundred Buddhist  

1350
02:27:34,319 --> 02:27:40,160
priests to escape. That night, they went 
into our temple and ate all the food.'

1351
02:27:41,439 --> 02:27:46,160
The angry King ordered the immediate 
death of the three pilgrims.  

1352
02:27:46,800 --> 02:27:53,280
But before anyone could do anything about the 
order, some men arrived asking urgently for rain.  

1353
02:27:54,479 --> 02:27:57,839
The King thought about the pilgrims' magic powers.

1354
02:27:59,040 --> 02:28:05,680
'There will be a rain-making competition between 
you and the Immortals,' he said to the pilgrims.  

1355
02:28:06,319 --> 02:28:11,840
'If you win, you will go free. 
If you lose, you will die!'

1356
02:28:12,640 --> 02:28:18,480
A tower was quickly built and the King, the 
pilgrims and the Immortals went outside.

1357
02:28:20,000 --> 02:28:24,160
'You must say what you are going to 
pray for,' said Monkey to an Immortal.  

1358
02:28:24,800 --> 02:28:27,120
'How else will we know if you are successful?'

1359
02:28:28,800 --> 02:28:35,120
When the King heard Monkey's words, he said, 
'This little priest is a sensible Monkey.'

1360
02:28:36,640 --> 02:28:41,760
'There is no need to tell you,' said the 
Immortal. 'The King knows what I am going to do.'

1361
02:28:43,200 --> 02:28:50,319
'That is not what I mean. We must each have our 
programme. If we do not, we will get confused.'

1362
02:28:50,960 --> 02:28:59,280
'Yes, fine. I shall cry out four times,' said 
the Immortal. 'At the first cry, wind will come;  

1363
02:28:59,280 --> 02:29:05,840
at the second, clouds will appear in the 
sky; at the third, you will hear thunder;  

1364
02:29:06,479 --> 02:29:13,280
at the fourth, rain will fall. But I shall 
cry out once more and the rain will stop.'

1365
02:29:14,880 --> 02:29:19,440
'Please begin,' said Monkey. 'This 
will be very entertaining for us.'

1366
02:29:20,960 --> 02:29:27,040
The tower was ten metres high. On each side 
there were the twenty-eight flags of the Great  

1367
02:29:27,040 --> 02:29:33,359
House of the Moon. There was a long table with 
burners on it, which gave a sweet-smelling smoke.  

1368
02:29:34,160 --> 02:29:38,479
There was a metal plate with the name 
of the thunder-spirit written on it  

1369
02:29:38,479 --> 02:29:45,519
next to each burner. At the foot of the table 
there were five great bowls of clear water  

1370
02:29:45,520 --> 02:29:53,121
with flowers in them. Behind the tower were 
some Taoists writing down religious teachings.

1371
02:29:55,120 --> 02:29:58,640
The Immortal went to the 
tower and climbed to the top.  

1372
02:29:59,520 --> 02:30:07,440
With his sword in his hand, he recited spells, and 
a strong wind was heard and felt in the air above.

1373
02:30:08,720 --> 02:30:13,200
'That is bad,' whispered Pigsy. 'He is winning.'

1374
02:30:14,160 --> 02:30:17,840
'Quiet, Brother,' whispered 
Monkey, 'and leave it to me.'

1375
02:30:19,040 --> 02:30:25,280
Dear Monkey! He leapt into the air and 
cried, 'Who is in charge of the wind?'

1376
02:30:26,240 --> 02:30:29,679
At once, the Old Woman of the Wind appeared.

1377
02:30:30,880 --> 02:30:36,720
'I am protecting Tripitaka on his way 
to India,' said Monkey. 'We are having  

1378
02:30:36,720 --> 02:30:42,720
a rain-making competition with the Immortals 
here. Why are you helping them instead of us?  

1379
02:30:43,439 --> 02:30:49,919
Stop that wind!' cried Monkey, 
and immediately the wind stopped.

1380
02:30:51,680 --> 02:30:57,120
The Immortal now hit the tower hard 
and the sky filled with clouds.

1381
02:30:58,720 --> 02:31:04,800
'Who is in charge of the clouds?' cried Monkey, 
and the Cloud Boy appeared in front of him.  

1382
02:31:05,680 --> 02:31:10,880
'Stop the clouds!' he commanded, 
and again the sky became clear.

1383
02:31:12,080 --> 02:31:18,720
The Immortal loosened his hair and then 
knocked again on the tower. The Thunder God  

1384
02:31:18,720 --> 02:31:23,920
and the Mother of Lightning appeared in 
the sky, but they bowed towards Monkey.

1385
02:31:25,200 --> 02:31:30,080
'The Jade Emperor in Heaven,' they 
said, 'ordered us to make a storm.'

1386
02:31:30,880 --> 02:31:34,480
'You are allowed to do that,' 
said Monkey, 'but not yet.'

1387
02:31:36,640 --> 02:31:42,640
As there was no thunder and no lightning, 
the Immortal was confused as well as angry.

1388
02:31:44,160 --> 02:31:51,280
'Listen well,' said Monkey, up in the sky. 
'Here are my orders. When I point my cudgel  

1389
02:31:51,280 --> 02:31:59,759
upwards once, you will give me wind. Twice, and 
you will give me clouds. Three times, thunder  

1390
02:31:59,760 --> 02:32:08,240
and lightning. And four times, rain. 'And when I 
point it a fifth time, you will stop the storm.'

1391
02:32:09,680 --> 02:32:14,241
The Immortal sadly left the tower 
and went to speak to the King.

1392
02:32:15,840 --> 02:32:23,840
'I have been watching,' said the King. 'You have 
not produced either wind or rain. What is wrong?'

1393
02:32:24,880 --> 02:32:29,120
'The rain-dragons are not at 
home today,' said the Immortal.

1394
02:32:30,319 --> 02:32:37,439
'Don't believe him!' cried Monkey. 'They are 
all at home. That Immortal has no real power  

1395
02:32:37,439 --> 02:32:44,080
over them. We, the followers of Buddha, 
will soon put them to work. You will see!'

1396
02:32:45,600 --> 02:32:52,480
'Go to the tower,' said the King to Monkey. 'I 
will wait here and see if there is any rain.'

1397
02:32:53,760 --> 02:32:57,281
'I need your help too,' said Monkey to Tripitaka.  

1398
02:32:57,920 --> 02:33:01,920
'Go quietly to the tower and 
start reciting your Scriptures.'

1399
02:33:02,880 --> 02:33:08,640
'My dear friend,' said Tripitaka, 'I do 
not know anything about making rain!'

1400
02:33:09,920 --> 02:33:12,560
'Don't let him pull you into this,'  

1401
02:33:12,560 --> 02:33:18,480
whispered Pigsy to Tripitaka. 'He 
will blame you if no rain comes.'

1402
02:33:19,520 --> 02:33:26,000
'It is true that you do not know how to 
make rain,' said Monkey to Tripitaka. 'But  

1403
02:33:26,000 --> 02:33:31,280
you know how to recite the Scriptures. 
If you do that, I will do the rest.'

1404
02:33:32,720 --> 02:33:39,120
Tripitaka went up the tower, sat 
down and began silently reciting.  

1405
02:33:40,319 --> 02:33:43,519
Then Monkey took his cudgel from behind his ear,  

1406
02:33:44,160 --> 02:33:50,080
and made it bigger until it was nearly a 
metre long. He pointed it towards the sky.

1407
02:33:51,520 --> 02:34:00,081
The Old Woman of the Wind brought out her bag and 
when she opened it, a great wind rushed out of it.  

1408
02:34:00,080 --> 02:34:08,479
It blew through the city, lifting stones and rocks 
high into the air. Monkey pointed again and a  

1409
02:34:08,479 --> 02:34:16,559
black cloud covered the sky, so the people of the 
city could not even see their palace. He pointed  

1410
02:34:16,560 --> 02:34:25,600
again and loud thunder shook the Earth. When he 
pointed a fourth time, rain fell down until it  

1411
02:34:25,600 --> 02:34:33,920
seemed that the Yellow River had fallen out of the 
sky. In seconds, the whole city was under water.

1412
02:34:34,880 --> 02:34:38,240
The people of the city were filled with terror  

1413
02:34:38,240 --> 02:34:45,280
and they all began saying their prayers. The 
rain fell from early morning until midday.

1414
02:34:46,240 --> 02:34:52,399
'Enough!' cried the King. 'Stop the 
rain or nothing will grow this year!'

1415
02:34:54,160 --> 02:34:58,080
Monkey at once pointed a 
fifth time with his cudgel  

1416
02:34:58,800 --> 02:35:03,920
and the storm stopped. There 
was not even a cloud in the sky.

1417
02:35:05,520 --> 02:35:15,281
'Wonderful priests!' cried the happy King. 'So 
it is true! There is always a stronger magic  

1418
02:35:15,280 --> 02:35:25,599
than the strongest! In the past we have seen our 
Immortals bring rain successfully. But even they  

1419
02:35:25,600 --> 02:35:32,560
could not stop it suddenly. Light rain 
always continued for the rest of the day.  

1420
02:35:33,200 --> 02:35:37,840
But these priests stopped the rain completely!'

1421
02:35:39,600 --> 02:35:42,000
The Immortal began making excuses.

1422
02:35:43,040 --> 02:35:46,800
'You said that the rain-dragons were not at home,'  

1423
02:35:46,800 --> 02:35:51,280
the King said, 'and that made 
it impossible to get rain.  

1424
02:35:51,280 --> 02:36:00,399
But look! The Buddhists, in their quiet way, made 
the rain fall. They were successful, not you.'

1425
02:36:01,359 --> 02:36:05,280
Again, the Immortal tried 
to change the King's mind,  

1426
02:36:05,280 --> 02:36:08,800
but Monkey jumped in front 
of him and spoke to the King.

1427
02:36:09,840 --> 02:36:16,560
'Sir, the Dragon Kings made the wind, the 
clouds and the rain. They are still in the sky,  

1428
02:36:17,280 --> 02:36:18,719
so would you like to see them?'

1429
02:36:19,439 --> 02:36:28,639
'Of course!' cried the King. 'I have been king 
for a long time, but I have never seen a dragon. I  

1430
02:36:28,640 --> 02:36:37,440
will reward anyone who can show me one. But if you 
do not produce a dragon, you will be punished.'

1431
02:36:38,640 --> 02:36:42,560
The Taoists knew quite well that 
this was beyond their powers.  

1432
02:36:43,439 --> 02:36:49,839
They tried, but no dragon answered 
their call. Then it was Monkey's turn.

1433
02:36:51,280 --> 02:36:58,080
'Are you there?' Monkey called up into the sky. 
'Let's have a look at you and your brothers.'

1434
02:36:59,359 --> 02:37:05,439
When the four Dragon Kings immediately 
appeared through the clouds, the King began  

1435
02:37:05,439 --> 02:37:12,160
to burn sweet-smelling sticks. His ministers 
went down on their knees in front of them.

1436
02:37:13,120 --> 02:37:21,680
'I feel ashamed,' said the King. 'I have 
troubled them for no reason. Tell them that  

1437
02:37:21,680 --> 02:37:31,840
I do not want to trouble them anymore. I will find 
an opportunity to repay them soon with offerings.'

1438
02:37:32,640 --> 02:37:35,201
'Spirits, you can leave us now,'  

1439
02:37:35,920 --> 02:37:42,319
said Monkey. 'The King will repay you with 
offerings at the earliest opportunity.'

1440
02:37:44,080 --> 02:37:50,240
The Dragons flew off, each to his own 
ocean, and again the sky was clear.

1441
02:37:51,439 --> 02:37:58,000
The King gave orders for a banquet the next day, 
to thank the pilgrims. All the Buddhists were  

1442
02:37:58,000 --> 02:38:04,160
invited to return to the city, and they were 
welcomed to the banquet by the King himself.

1443
02:38:05,520 --> 02:38:11,121
After the banquet, the Buddhist priests 
took the pilgrims to the gates of the city,  

1444
02:38:11,680 --> 02:38:19,920
and they gave Monkey back the hairs he had 
given them. Then Monkey said, 'Now you can see  

1445
02:38:20,479 --> 02:38:27,839
that Buddhism is the True Way, but you 
must obey all priests - Taoist priests  

1446
02:38:27,840 --> 02:38:34,800
too - and become better men. Then these 
hills and streams will be safe forever.'

1447
02:38:36,479 --> 02:38:40,479
The King himself rode out with the pilgrims  

1448
02:38:40,479 --> 02:38:44,319
far beyond the city's walls, where 
they said goodbye.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

1449
02:38:47,280 --> 02:38:48,160
CHAPTER FIVE

1450
02:38:49,040 --> 02:38:50,399
The River to Heaven

1451
02:38:52,640 --> 02:38:56,720
'What has happened to Tripitaka?' 
shouted Monkey from the air.

1452
02:38:57,520 --> 02:39:02,400
'There is no Tripitaka now!' Pigsy shouted back.

1453
02:39:04,960 --> 02:39:10,480
They travelled without stopping for 
many days. Then Tripitaka stopped his  

1454
02:39:10,479 --> 02:39:16,959
horse and said to Monkey, 'Follower, 
when and where are we going to rest?'

1455
02:39:18,080 --> 02:39:25,920
'Comfort,' answered Monkey, 'is for ordinary 
people, so pilgrims cannot expect it. By day  

1456
02:39:25,920 --> 02:39:32,240
or by night, in wet or dry weather, if there 
is a road to travel, we must continue.'

1457
02:39:34,319 --> 02:39:39,200
Soon Sandy shouted, 'There is 
a great river in front of us!'

1458
02:39:40,399 --> 02:39:45,759
'Wait here!' cried Monkey, leaping 
high into the air. Soon he was back.  

1459
02:39:46,960 --> 02:39:53,600
'I cannot see land on the other side,' he 
said, 'but I thought I saw a fisherman. He  

1460
02:39:53,600 --> 02:39:57,680
was standing at the water's edge. 
I will ask him about the river.'

1461
02:39:59,200 --> 02:40:01,920
But it was not a fisherman that Monkey had seen.  

1462
02:40:02,720 --> 02:40:09,840
It was a sign that said: The River That Leads to 
Heaven. Few people have reached the other side.

1463
02:40:11,200 --> 02:40:14,720
When Tripitaka read this, he cried quietly.  

1464
02:40:15,680 --> 02:40:22,560
'I knew so little of the difficulties in 
our way, on the road to India,' he said.

1465
02:40:23,439 --> 02:40:30,559
'Listen,' said Pigsy. 'That music means there 
are priests praying somewhere near here.  

1466
02:40:31,279 --> 02:40:34,719
They will tell us how we 
can get across the river.'

1467
02:40:36,240 --> 02:40:40,800
Following the sound, they soon 
saw a village of several hundred  

1468
02:40:40,800 --> 02:40:46,080
houses. One of them had a flag 
at its gate and lights outside.

1469
02:40:46,760 --> 02:40:50,320
'I shall go in first,' said Tripitaka,  

1470
02:40:51,040 --> 02:40:56,800
'because you three look a little strange 
and I do not want people to be frightened.'

1471
02:40:58,479 --> 02:41:03,200
An old man came to the door and 
when he saw Tripitaka he said,  

1472
02:41:03,760 --> 02:41:10,720
'You have come a little late. The banquet is 
almost finished and there is not much to eat.'

1473
02:41:11,920 --> 02:41:16,000
'I did not come for the 
banquet,' answered Tripitaka.  

1474
02:41:16,000 --> 02:41:21,040
'I have come from China and I would like 
a bed for the night if that is possible.'

1475
02:41:21,920 --> 02:41:27,359
'China is a very long way away,' said the old man,  

1476
02:41:27,359 --> 02:41:32,479
whose name was Ch'en. 'How do I 
know that your words are true?'

1477
02:41:33,840 --> 02:41:36,480
'My three followers have helped me on the journey.  

1478
02:41:37,120 --> 02:41:39,920
They have made it possible 
for me to travel so far.'

1479
02:41:40,880 --> 02:41:44,720
'Well, they had better come in with you.'

1480
02:41:46,640 --> 02:41:51,760
The three pilgrims came rushing in out 
of the dark, leading the white horse,  

1481
02:41:51,760 --> 02:42:01,600
carrying the luggage and shouting. The old man 
fell on the floor, crying, 'Demons! Help! Demons!'

1482
02:42:02,800 --> 02:42:09,600
'Not demons,' said Tripitaka, 'but 
my followers. I know they are ugly,  

1483
02:42:09,600 --> 02:42:14,720
but they are very good at fighting 
tigers, dragons and other creatures.'

1484
02:42:16,160 --> 02:42:22,559
A group of praying priests jumped up 
and ran away in fear. The pilgrims  

1485
02:42:22,560 --> 02:42:26,800
laughed so loudly at this that 
the priests ran even faster.

1486
02:42:28,000 --> 02:42:35,920
'You fools!' cried Tripitaka to his followers. 
'I have tried so hard to teach you to behave  

1487
02:42:35,920 --> 02:42:42,640
correctly! Learn this: It is admirable 
to be good without being taught.  

1488
02:42:43,200 --> 02:42:51,200
It is normal to be good after being taught. 
Only a fool is taught and then is still  

1489
02:42:51,200 --> 02:42:56,319
bad. Do you not understand that I 
will have to take the blame for this?'

1490
02:42:57,680 --> 02:43:04,400
The three stood silently, so the old man believed 
that they really were followers of Tripitaka.  

1491
02:43:05,680 --> 02:43:09,040
He sat Tripitaka in the best place at the table,  

1492
02:43:09,600 --> 02:43:16,480
and food was brought for them all. Tripitaka 
began to recite the Scripture Before Eating,  

1493
02:43:17,120 --> 02:43:23,359
but Pigsy poured all the food into his mouth 
from the bowl before Tripitaka had finished.

1494
02:43:24,479 --> 02:43:35,279
As Pigsy was calling 'More food, more food' to the 
servants, the old man spoke to Tripitaka. 'Did you  

1495
02:43:35,279 --> 02:43:44,080
read the sign by the river? You were quite near 
the Temple of the Great King of Magic,' he said.  

1496
02:43:44,800 --> 02:43:54,960
'He is the god who sends us rain. He makes things 
grow.' But as he spoke, he began to cry loudly.

1497
02:43:56,240 --> 02:44:00,319
'Why are you crying when you 
speak of the God?' asked Monkey.

1498
02:44:01,760 --> 02:44:11,120
'That god is an angry god and every year he 
takes the life of a boy and a girl, so we have  

1499
02:44:11,120 --> 02:44:20,960
few children here. I have one child, a son called 
War Boy, and my brother has one girl, called  

1500
02:44:20,960 --> 02:44:28,880
Much Gold. This year our family must give the 
children to the God and both of them must die.'

1501
02:44:30,720 --> 02:44:33,040
'Let me see the boy,' said Monkey.

1502
02:44:34,319 --> 02:44:41,279
The boy was brought down from his bed and 
ran around eating fruit. Without a word,  

1503
02:44:41,279 --> 02:44:45,840
Monkey transformed himself into a 
boy who looked exactly the same.

1504
02:44:46,640 --> 02:44:54,880
'That is unbelievable,' cried the father. 
'Look! When I call, both come running to me.'

1505
02:44:56,560 --> 02:45:03,440
Monkey then changed back to his own form. 'I 
am going to save this child's life,' he said  

1506
02:45:03,439 --> 02:45:08,799
to the father. 'I will let the Great 
King of Magic kill me for the gods.'

1507
02:45:09,840 --> 02:45:13,840
The old man's brother was standing 
in the doorway, watching and crying.

1508
02:45:15,040 --> 02:45:18,800
'I think you are worried about 
your daughter,' said Monkey.

1509
02:45:20,080 --> 02:45:24,399
'Father,' said the old man, 'I cannot lose her.  

1510
02:45:24,399 --> 02:45:28,639
She is my only child. Who 
will cry for me when I die?'

1511
02:45:30,319 --> 02:45:36,399
Monkey pointed at Pigsy. 'If you feed that 
long-nosed brother of mine enough,' he said,  

1512
02:45:37,040 --> 02:45:40,240
'he will transform himself into your girl  

1513
02:45:40,240 --> 02:45:46,559
and do anything else you ask. The Great 
King of Magic can kill us both together.'

1514
02:45:47,840 --> 02:45:52,640
Pigsy was shocked. 'Leave 
me out of this!' he said.

1515
02:45:53,439 --> 02:45:59,040
'You know what they say,' said Monkey. 
"'Even a chicken must work for its food.'"

1516
02:46:00,160 --> 02:46:08,720
'I am no good at transformations,' complained 
Pigsy. 'I can change into a mountain or a tree,  

1517
02:46:09,359 --> 02:46:14,000
but it is much more difficult 
to change into a small girl.'

1518
02:46:15,200 --> 02:46:19,840
'Don't believe him,' said Monkey to 
the girl's father. 'Bring your child.'

1519
02:46:21,520 --> 02:46:28,241
Soon the man returned with his child, and all 
the priests and servants asked Pigsy to save her.

1520
02:46:29,520 --> 02:46:33,920
'Here she is,' said Monkey. 
'Have a look and be quick.'

1521
02:46:34,960 --> 02:46:43,600
The fool Pigsy shook his head, said 
a spell and cried 'Change!' His head  

1522
02:46:43,600 --> 02:46:48,640
was now the same as the child's but 
his big stomach had not changed.

1523
02:46:49,520 --> 02:46:57,041
'You can hit me if you like,' complained 
Pigsy, 'but I cannot do any better than that.'

1524
02:46:58,640 --> 02:47:02,320
'I can see that I will have to help,' said Monkey.  

1525
02:47:02,319 --> 02:47:07,759
And he blew on Pigsy, who was soon 
like the child from head to foot.

1526
02:47:09,279 --> 02:47:13,599
'What happens now?' asked Monkey. 
'How are we brought to the God?'

1527
02:47:14,640 --> 02:47:22,080
The girl's father came forward. 'It is quite 
simple,' he said. 'You sit in two dishes,  

1528
02:47:22,960 --> 02:47:28,880
two men carry you to the temple, and 
then the Great King of Magic eats you.'

1529
02:47:30,160 --> 02:47:36,479
'Watch me,' Monkey said to Pigsy. 'While he 
is cutting me into pieces, you can run away.'

1530
02:47:37,439 --> 02:47:41,519
'But he might begin with the girl!' cried Pigsy.

1531
02:47:42,479 --> 02:47:49,439
'No,' said War Boy's father quietly. 
'The meal always begins with the boy.'

1532
02:47:50,399 --> 02:47:53,839
'Well, that is lucky,' said Pigsy.

1533
02:47:55,040 --> 02:48:00,640
Suddenly, they all saw lights outside and 
heard the sound of voices as the gate opened.  

1534
02:48:01,359 --> 02:48:06,559
A loud voice cried, 'Bring 
out the boy and the girl!'

1535
02:48:08,720 --> 02:48:14,560
The two fathers cried while the Great King's 
servants carried the boy and the girl away.

1536
02:48:15,600 --> 02:48:19,600
'Great King,' said the villagers, 
when everything was ready,  

1537
02:48:20,160 --> 02:48:26,880
'we now offer you a boy child, War 
Boy, and a girl child, Much Gold,  

1538
02:48:27,439 --> 02:48:33,439
with a pig, a sheep and some wine.' 
They then went back to their homes.

1539
02:48:34,319 --> 02:48:37,840
'I think I will go home too,' said Pigsy.

1540
02:48:38,640 --> 02:48:42,560
'You have no home,' said 
Monkey. 'What rubbish you talk!  

1541
02:48:43,120 --> 02:48:46,479
We have started this job and 
now we have to finish it.'

1542
02:48:48,000 --> 02:48:55,200
Just then, a strong wind blew through the 
door, and as it opened the Great King appeared.  

1543
02:48:55,200 --> 02:49:01,200
He was a horrible creature, with 
eyes like fire and teeth like a pig.

1544
02:49:02,880 --> 02:49:07,520
'Which family do you come 
from?' asked the Great King.

1545
02:49:08,880 --> 02:49:12,240
'The family of Ch'en,' answered Monkey.

1546
02:49:12,240 --> 02:49:17,840
The King did not understand why the 
boy was so brave. Usually the children  

1547
02:49:17,840 --> 02:49:20,640
were too frightened to talk 
before they were killed.

1548
02:49:21,520 --> 02:49:25,840
'You understand that I am now going to eat you?'

1549
02:49:27,040 --> 02:49:28,720
'Do it!' said Monkey.

1550
02:49:30,000 --> 02:49:38,000
'You are too brave,' said the Great King. 
'This time I shall begin with the girl.'

1551
02:49:38,880 --> 02:49:45,440
'No, no!' said Pigsy. 'It is never 
a good idea to change an old custom.  

1552
02:49:46,000 --> 02:49:49,600
Do what you usually do - that is always best.'

1553
02:49:50,880 --> 02:49:57,600
The fool leapt off his dish, changed back into 
Pigsy, took his fork and hit the Great King.  

1554
02:49:58,399 --> 02:50:01,120
Then he and Monkey leapt into the air,  

1555
02:50:01,120 --> 02:50:05,920
just as the Great King changed into a 
wind and disappeared into the river.

1556
02:50:07,359 --> 02:50:14,799
'Oh, let him go now,' said Monkey. 'We will finish 
him tomorrow and get our Master across the river.'

1557
02:50:16,240 --> 02:50:22,319
So they returned to Ch'en's farm, where they 
were soon asleep in the best room in the house.

1558
02:50:23,840 --> 02:50:30,160
But under the river, the Great King was unhappy. 
He told his fish-servants what had happened.  

1559
02:50:30,960 --> 02:50:38,160
He told them about Tripitaka, who was like a 
god. If somebody ate him, they would never die.

1560
02:50:39,520 --> 02:50:47,920
The Great King's fish-sister made a suggestion. 
'Start a cold wind and a great fall of snow,  

1561
02:50:48,479 --> 02:50:55,279
so the river freezes. Then some of us will 
change into human form and walk across it,  

1562
02:50:55,279 --> 02:51:04,319
carrying luggage. Tripitaka is in such a hurry to 
get to India that he will walk across it too. When  

1563
02:51:04,319 --> 02:51:12,399
you hear him above you, heat the ice. The pilgrims 
will fall through it and you will have them all.'

1564
02:51:14,399 --> 02:51:23,279
Just before the sun came up, Tripitaka and 
his followers began to feel cold. 'Pilgrims,'  

1565
02:51:23,279 --> 02:51:26,880
said Monkey, 'should not 
feel either heat or cold.'

1566
02:51:27,920 --> 02:51:34,160
But they could not sleep, and when they looked 
out of the window everything was white. The  

1567
02:51:34,160 --> 02:51:41,519
snow was so lovely that they sat and watched it 
fall. It was like small pieces of white jade.

1568
02:51:42,960 --> 02:51:49,600
Soon servants brought them hot water to wash 
in, hot tea to drink and hot food to eat.  

1569
02:51:50,640 --> 02:51:56,560
They even brought heaters for the rooms, but when 
the meal was finished the pilgrims were colder  

1570
02:51:56,560 --> 02:52:05,121
than ever. By now there was nearly a metre of snow 
outside and, seeing this, Tripitaka began to cry.

1571
02:52:07,120 --> 02:52:10,640
But towards evening everyone 
was talking about the river.  

1572
02:52:11,279 --> 02:52:17,359
It had frozen and people were walking 
on the ice. The next morning the ice was  

1573
02:52:17,359 --> 02:52:24,319
even thicker and Tripitaka gave thanks to the 
Gods for this chance to walk across the river.

1574
02:52:26,000 --> 02:52:29,520
'Master,' said Sandy, 'should we not wait  

1575
02:52:29,520 --> 02:52:35,201
until the ice goes away? Then we can go 
across the river in Mr Ch'en's boat.'

1576
02:52:36,240 --> 02:52:43,599
'But if we wait until the spring,' said Tripitaka, 
'we will lose half a year's travelling. I promised  

1577
02:52:43,600 --> 02:52:49,840
the Goddess Kuan-yin that the journey would 
take three years. Already seven have passed.'

1578
02:52:51,920 --> 02:52:55,840
He ordered Pigsy to put the luggage 
on the horse, and they left.

1579
02:52:57,359 --> 02:53:00,960
When they had gone fifteen or 
twenty kilometres across the ice,  

1580
02:53:01,520 --> 02:53:06,241
Pigsy showed Tripitaka how to 
carry his stick across his body.

1581
02:53:07,680 --> 02:53:10,960
'Ice often has holes in it,' he explained.  

1582
02:53:11,520 --> 02:53:18,720
'If you put your foot in a hole, you will go 
down into the water. It will close above you  

1583
02:53:18,720 --> 02:53:25,920
and you will never get out again. Carry your 
stick across your body and you will feel safer.'

1584
02:53:27,200 --> 02:53:31,439
Monkey looked disbelieving, but 
they all did as Pigsy had said.

1585
02:53:32,560 --> 02:53:38,000
They rode all night until the sun 
began to come up. Then they stopped to  

1586
02:53:38,000 --> 02:53:42,560
eat some food from their luggage 
and then continued towards the West.

1587
02:53:43,840 --> 02:53:49,600
But after some time, the ice began to 
break and the white horse almost fell.  

1588
02:53:50,800 --> 02:53:57,760
They continued walking, not knowing that the Great 
King and his fish-followers were waiting below.  

1589
02:53:59,040 --> 02:54:05,840
Suddenly, a great hole opened in the ice. 
Monkey at once leapt high into the air,  

1590
02:54:06,560 --> 02:54:12,800
but the white horse and all the 
others fell through it. The Great King  

1591
02:54:12,800 --> 02:54:19,840
took Tripitaka and carried him down 
to the Great Palace under the water.

1592
02:54:21,359 --> 02:54:25,120
'Where is my fish-sister?' said the Great King.  

1593
02:54:25,760 --> 02:54:32,080
'Come, fetch the sharp knives. Let's 
eat Tripitaka and live forever.'

1594
02:54:32,840 --> 02:54:41,279
'Great King,' answered the Fish-Sister. 'Let's 
wait for a couple of days until we can be sure  

1595
02:54:41,279 --> 02:54:44,080
that his followers cannot spoil our fun.'

1596
02:54:45,520 --> 02:54:52,720
The King agreed, and Tripitaka was put in a 
great stone box at the back of the palace.

1597
02:54:54,240 --> 02:55:00,399
At the same time, Pigsy and Sandy had 
managed to get the luggage out of the water  

1598
02:55:00,399 --> 02:55:05,759
and put it on to the horse's back. They 
started swimming back the way they had come.

1599
02:55:07,359 --> 02:55:11,519
'What has happened to Tripitaka?' 
shouted Monkey from the air.

1600
02:55:12,399 --> 02:55:20,719
'There is no Tripitaka now!' Pigsy shouted 
back. 'We are going back to Ch'en's farm.'

1601
02:55:27,920 --> 02:55:33,760
Mr Ch'en cried uncontrollably when he 
heard what had happened to Tripitaka.

1602
02:55:35,200 --> 02:55:40,080
'Don't worry,' said Monkey. 'I think 
the Master will live for a long time.  

1603
02:55:41,040 --> 02:55:45,680
Let's dry our clothes and then we will 
go back and finish that creature!'

1604
02:55:47,680 --> 02:55:54,880
Back at the river, Monkey asked Pigsy to carry 
him down while Sandy swam behind them. And at  

1605
02:55:54,880 --> 02:56:00,400
the bottom of the river they found a gate 
with the sign Turtle House written on it.

1606
02:56:01,760 --> 02:56:10,000
Monkey whispered, 'You two hide at each side of 
the door!' Then he changed himself into a fish and  

1607
02:56:10,000 --> 02:56:17,279
swam inside. The Great King and his fish-followers 
were talking about eating Tripitaka,  

1608
02:56:18,000 --> 02:56:25,840
but Monkey could not see his Master. Then he 
heard Tripitaka crying inside a stone box.

1609
02:56:26,880 --> 02:56:31,040
'Don't worry,' said Monkey, 
'we will soon get you out.'

1610
02:56:32,160 --> 02:56:37,599
'Be quick! Oh, be quick!' cried 
Tripitaka from inside his box.

1611
02:56:38,399 --> 02:56:46,000
'I am going now,' said Monkey, 'but I 
shall return.' And soon he and Pigsy  

1612
02:56:46,000 --> 02:56:48,319
and Sandy were back at the riverbank.

1613
02:56:49,840 --> 02:56:55,200
'I am not at my best in the water, so it 
is not a good plan for me to go down again  

1614
02:56:55,200 --> 02:56:57,760
and fight the Great King,' said Monkey.  

1615
02:56:58,720 --> 02:57:04,080
'I shall go to the Goddess of the Southern 
Ocean for help. I shall not waste a minute.'

1616
02:57:06,080 --> 02:57:13,040
Dear Monkey! He shot up in the air on a magic 
light, leapt on a cloud and found Kuan-yin.  

1617
02:57:14,000 --> 02:57:17,760
She was expecting him, but had 
not finished getting dressed.

1618
02:57:19,279 --> 02:57:25,279
'Let's leave now,' she said, when she saw 
Monkey. 'We will go and save Tripitaka.'

1619
02:57:26,720 --> 02:57:32,800
Monkey went down on his knees in front of her. 'Do 
you not want to finish dressing first?' he asked.

1620
02:57:33,680 --> 02:57:38,160
'It is too much trouble,' she 
answered. 'I am going like this.'

1621
02:57:40,000 --> 02:57:43,359
She left on her cloud, followed by Monkey.

1622
02:57:44,319 --> 02:57:50,880
'Well, that was quick!' said Pigsy, 
as they appeared. 'You did well to  

1623
02:57:50,880 --> 02:57:56,480
get a goddess to come immediately, before 
she had even finished combing her hair!'

1624
02:57:58,000 --> 02:58:01,600
The Goddess sailed low over 
the river like a cloud.  

1625
02:58:02,399 --> 02:58:09,040
Untying the belt from her dress, she tied a basket 
to it and pulled the basket through the water.  

1626
02:58:09,920 --> 02:58:19,200
She repeated the words, 'The dead go, the living 
stay,' seven times and pulled the basket up.  

1627
02:58:20,000 --> 02:58:25,760
There was a gold fish in it. Its 
tail moved and its eye stared.

1628
02:58:27,120 --> 02:58:32,960
'Go at once into the water and fetch 
your Master,' said the Goddess to Monkey.

1629
02:58:34,240 --> 02:58:37,519
'But what shall I do with the 
Great King?' asked Monkey.

1630
02:58:38,800 --> 02:58:45,680
'The Great King is in the basket,' said the 
Goddess. 'He used to live in a little pool  

1631
02:58:45,680 --> 02:58:54,160
in my garden. Every day he used to put his head 
out and listen to the Scriptures, until at last  

1632
02:58:54,160 --> 02:59:01,359
he held great magical powers. But one day 
there was a great storm and the water took  

1633
02:59:01,359 --> 02:59:08,719
him far out to sea. I thought that he might 
be using his magic against your Master.  

1634
02:59:09,439 --> 02:59:15,839
So without stopping to comb my hair, I 
made this magic basket to catch him in.'

1635
02:59:17,760 --> 02:59:23,920
'If you want to make humans believe in the 
Gods,' said Monkey, 'you will wait here. I  

1636
02:59:23,920 --> 02:59:28,880
will call the people of the village to hear 
this story and look at your golden face.'

1637
02:59:30,399 --> 02:59:33,839
So men and women, young and old,  

1638
02:59:33,840 --> 02:59:38,800
were soon hurrying to the river to go down 
on their knees in front of the Goddess.  

1639
02:59:39,600 --> 02:59:45,920
One of them later painted a famous painting 
called Kuan-yin with the Fish Basket.

1640
02:59:47,439 --> 02:59:53,200
When the Goddess had returned to the 
Southern Ocean, Pigsy and Sandy dived  

1641
02:59:53,200 --> 02:59:59,760
down to the Great King's palace. All the 
Great King's fish-followers were dead,  

1642
03:00:00,399 --> 03:00:06,080
so they soon helped Tripitaka out of the 
stone box and took him back to Ch'en's farm.

1643
03:00:07,520 --> 03:00:12,800
'We are sorry, Sirs,' said the Ch'en 
brothers, 'that you had so many problems.'

1644
03:00:13,760 --> 03:00:20,640
'Oh, that is all finished now,' said Monkey. 
'The important thing is that next year,  

1645
03:00:20,640 --> 03:00:25,120
and every other year, your village 
will not lose its children.  

1646
03:00:25,840 --> 03:00:30,160
But we would be glad if you could give 
us a boat to carry us across the river.'

1647
03:00:31,680 --> 03:00:37,840
All the villagers started to make boats. But 
when the pilgrims went back to the river,  

1648
03:00:37,840 --> 03:00:44,480
they heard a voice: 'Oh, great Monkey 
King, you do not need to build a boat.  

1649
03:00:45,120 --> 03:00:53,279
I will take you.' And above the waters they saw 
the white head and the enormous body of a turtle.

1650
03:00:55,200 --> 03:01:02,399
'You!' cried Monkey. 'You demon! If you come 
near us, I will kill you with my cudgel.'

1651
03:01:03,439 --> 03:01:06,479
'Great Monkey King,' said the turtle,

1652
03:01:07,120 --> 03:01:15,439
'listen to me. I am not a follower of the Great 
King. His palace below the river used to be mine.  

1653
03:01:15,439 --> 03:01:22,799
Then one day that creature came swimming into 
the river killed many of my family and made the  

1654
03:01:22,800 --> 03:01:31,600
others work for him. I am grateful for all that 
you have done - you have made us free again.'

1655
03:01:33,200 --> 03:01:38,559
'Promise me and promise the Gods 
that this is all true,' said Monkey.

1656
03:01:39,439 --> 03:01:47,040
The turtle opened his red mouth wide. 
'I promise you and all the Gods.

1657
03:01:47,040 --> 03:01:54,800
If I do not take Tripitaka safely across 
the river, my bones will turn to water.'

1658
03:01:56,399 --> 03:02:02,879
The turtle came out of the river, and people 
saw that his back was fifteen metres wide.

1659
03:02:04,800 --> 03:02:10,320
'Climb on the turtle's back,' called Monkey 
to the others. 'He has promised that we  

1660
03:02:10,319 --> 03:02:16,960
will be safe. When creatures speak human 
language, their words are usually true.'

1661
03:02:19,120 --> 03:02:25,920
The white horse was led to the middle of the 
turtle's back. Tripitaka stood to the left, Sandy  

1662
03:02:25,920 --> 03:02:33,359
to the right, and Pigsy behind the horse's tail. 
Monkey put himself in front of the horse's head.

1663
03:02:34,800 --> 03:02:44,000
'Now, turtle,' he cried. 'Go gently, because if 
you do not, there will be a cudgel on your head!'

1664
03:02:44,000 --> 03:02:48,080
With this warning, the turtle 
moved smoothly over the water.  

1665
03:02:49,200 --> 03:02:54,479
As the pilgrims left, all the people of 
the village bowed and thanked Buddha.

1666
03:02:55,600 --> 03:03:01,600
The turtle travelled quickly, and in less 
than a day they had arrived at the other side.

1667
03:03:03,120 --> 03:03:07,519
Tripitaka said to the turtle, 'I 
have nothing that I can give you.  

1668
03:03:08,160 --> 03:03:11,840
But I would like to thank you 
for taking us across the river.'

1669
03:03:12,960 --> 03:03:20,399
'Master,' replied the turtle, 'there is something 
that you could do for me. I have been trying to  

1670
03:03:20,399 --> 03:03:29,120
become perfect for about a thousand years, and 
that is a long time. I can now use human speech,  

1671
03:03:29,680 --> 03:03:36,640
but I am still a turtle. Please ask 
the Buddha if I can become a human.'

1672
03:03:38,640 --> 03:03:42,241
Tripitaka gladly promised 
to ask Buddha the question,  

1673
03:03:42,960 --> 03:03:45,920
and the turtle swam back to his home in the river.

1674
03:03:47,520 --> 03:03:53,840
Again Pigsy carried the luggage, and Monkey 
helped Tripitaka on to the white horse.  

1675
03:03:54,479 --> 03:03:58,319
With Sandy behind them, they 
soon found the road to the West.

1676
03:04:00,160 --> 03:04:05,680
They travelled for many months. The country was 
very different from anything they had seen before.  

1677
03:04:06,560 --> 03:04:10,560
The flowers were like jewels, 
the grass looked magical  

1678
03:04:11,120 --> 03:04:13,439
and there were strange and wonderful trees.

1679
03:04:15,520 --> 03:04:22,000
In every village, families were entertaining 
priests. On every hill, Immortals were  

1680
03:04:22,000 --> 03:04:28,720
practising control over their bodies. In every 
wood, pilgrims were reciting and singing.

1681
03:04:30,640 --> 03:04:38,161
Every night, they found somewhere to stay and left 
again at the first light of day. They travelled on  

1682
03:04:38,160 --> 03:04:46,639
in this way for many more days until suddenly the 
light grew bright and they saw a wonderful castle.

1683
03:04:47,760 --> 03:04:54,640
'Monkey,' said Tripitaka admiringly, 
pointing at it, 'that's a fine place!'

1684
03:04:56,319 --> 03:05:02,960
'Do you remember,' said Monkey, 'how often 
on our journey you have bowed in front of  

1685
03:05:02,960 --> 03:05:10,240
the caves and hiding-places and palaces 
of false magicians? It is strange that  

1686
03:05:10,240 --> 03:05:18,240
you do not even get off your horse now - 
when you see the Buddha's holy castle!'

1687
03:05:18,240 --> 03:05:21,040
So Tripitaka, in great excitement,  

1688
03:05:21,600 --> 03:05:28,161
jumped down from his horse. When they reached 
the gates, a young priest came out to greet them.

1689
03:05:29,279 --> 03:05:34,240
He asked, 'Are you the pilgrims who have 
come from the East for the Scriptures?'

1690
03:05:35,600 --> 03:05:41,360
The boy was dressed in beautiful clothes 
and carried a bowl of jade dust in his hand.  

1691
03:05:42,800 --> 03:05:45,840
Monkey knew him at once, and turned to Tripitaka.

1692
03:05:47,200 --> 03:05:54,880
'This,' he said, 'is the Golden-Headed Immortal of 
the Jade Temple at the foot of the Holy Mountain.'

1693
03:05:57,200 --> 03:06:01,200
'Here you are at last!' said 
the Golden-Headed Immortal.  

1694
03:06:02,080 --> 03:06:08,240
'It is now ten years since the Goddess 
Kuan-yin told me to expect your arrival.  

1695
03:06:09,040 --> 03:06:13,840
Year after year I have waited, 
but there has been no sign!'

1696
03:06:15,600 --> 03:06:22,241
'Great Immortal,' said Tripitaka, bowing low, 
'I cannot thank you enough for your patience.'

1697
03:06:23,920 --> 03:06:28,480
Inside the temple, sweet-smelling 
hot water was brought to wash in,  

1698
03:06:29,120 --> 03:06:32,640
and after supper the pilgrims 
were shown to their beds.

1699
03:06:34,240 --> 03:06:39,200
Early the next day, Tripitaka put 
on his finest clothes and jewellery  

1700
03:06:39,760 --> 03:06:41,840
and greeted the young Immortal.

1701
03:06:42,880 --> 03:06:49,920
'That is better,' said the young Immortal. 
'Yesterday you looked rather untidy,  

1702
03:06:50,640 --> 03:06:58,640
but today you look like a true child of Buddha! 
You must let me show you the way. Monkey knows it,  

1703
03:06:58,640 --> 03:07:02,720
but only by air, and you 
must travel on the ground.'

1704
03:07:04,319 --> 03:07:10,479
Taking Tripitaka by the hand, he led 
the pilgrims through the temple gardens  

1705
03:07:10,479 --> 03:07:14,639
to the back of the building and 
up a path to the hill behind.

1706
03:07:15,760 --> 03:07:18,080
'Do you see that mountain in front of you?'  

1707
03:07:18,800 --> 03:07:26,320
said the young Immortal, pointing up. 'That is 
where Buddha has his home. I shall now turn back.'

1708
03:07:27,680 --> 03:07:33,120
Tripitaka at once began bowing low, 
hitting his head on the holy ground.

1709
03:07:34,319 --> 03:07:38,000
'If you are going to do that 
all the way up,' said Monkey,  

1710
03:07:38,000 --> 03:07:41,840
'there will not be much of your 
head left by the time we get there!'

1711
03:07:43,279 --> 03:07:48,719
So Tripitaka stopped bowing and they 
climbed some way, walking easily.  

1712
03:07:50,000 --> 03:07:53,840
Then they came to a fast-moving 
river with rough water.

1713
03:07:54,960 --> 03:07:58,080
Tripitaka said, 'This cannot be the way.'  

1714
03:07:58,960 --> 03:08:07,439
But then he saw a bridge and a sign which said 
Cloud Reach Bridge. When they came to the bridge,  

1715
03:08:08,080 --> 03:08:15,120
they saw that it was just some trees laid end to 
end. It was only a little wider than a man's hand.

1716
03:08:16,160 --> 03:08:21,920
'Monkey!' cried Tripitaka, afraid. 
'I cannot walk across that!'

1717
03:08:23,120 --> 03:08:29,519
