03:29:16,640 --> 03:29:23,040
Scriptures. The demons attacked all through the 
night, stopping only when the sun began to come  

1904
03:29:23,040 --> 03:29:28,399
up. And although nobody could see them, 
Monkey hit out with his cudgel at them,  

1905
03:29:28,399 --> 03:29:33,839
holding it in both hands and hitting 
first to the right and then to the left.

1906
03:29:35,520 --> 03:29:40,720
Tripitaka, who was already wet from 
the storm, was left shaking with fear.

1907
03:29:41,760 --> 03:29:48,160
'Monkey,' he asked in a shocked 
voice, 'what does all this mean?'

1908
03:29:48,160 --> 03:29:55,279
'It is jealousy,' answered Monkey. 'The success of 
our journey has put jealousy in the heart of every  

1909
03:29:55,279 --> 03:30:03,120
demon in Heaven and on Earth, because our power 
is almost as great as theirs now. It is good that  

1910
03:30:03,120 --> 03:30:10,319
you kept the Scriptures close to you. That and 
my cudgel saved us from losing the holy words.'

1911
03:30:11,680 --> 03:30:15,840
Tripitaka then understood and he 
thanked Monkey for his protection.

1912
03:30:17,120 --> 03:30:25,439
When the sun was hotter, they dried their clothes 
and the Scriptures on a rock. Even today this rock  

1913
03:30:25,439 --> 03:30:32,239
is called The Rock Where the Scriptures Were 
Dried. They also dried their shoes and clothes.

1914
03:30:33,760 --> 03:30:37,280
When they had almost finished, 
some workers came past.  

1915
03:30:38,560 --> 03:30:44,720
They said, 'Are you not the gentlemen who crossed 
the river to fetch the Scriptures from India?'

1916
03:30:45,760 --> 03:30:50,720
'That is right,' said Pigsy. 
'How do you recognise us?'

1917
03:30:52,160 --> 03:30:54,960
'We are from Mr Ch'en's farm,' they answered.

1918
03:30:55,680 --> 03:30:59,040
'How far is it from here?' Pigsy asked.

1919
03:30:59,840 --> 03:31:06,080
'If you went about twenty kilometres south from 
here, you would come to it,' they answered.

1920
03:31:07,279 --> 03:31:11,599
'Let's take the Scriptures 
and dry them at the farm,'  

1921
03:31:11,600 --> 03:31:18,320
said Pigsy. 'If we go there, we can sit 
down comfortably and get something to eat.'

1922
03:31:19,600 --> 03:31:26,161
'I am not going,' said Tripitaka. 'We 
can dry the scriptures very well here.'

1923
03:31:26,160 --> 03:31:28,880
But then Mr Ch'en himself appeared.  

1924
03:31:29,920 --> 03:31:35,920
'I see that you have got the Scriptures,' 
he said happily. 'Please come home with me!'

1925
03:31:37,120 --> 03:31:42,080
'Wait until our Scriptures are dry,' said 
Monkey. 'Then we will go home with you.'

1926
03:31:42,960 --> 03:31:49,279
'I see that your clothes are wet too. 
What has happened to you?' asked Mr Ch'en.

1927
03:31:50,640 --> 03:31:55,520
Tripitaka explained about the 
white turtle. When he finished,  

1928
03:31:55,520 --> 03:32:02,720
Mr Ch'en again asked them to follow him home. 
In the end, Tripitaka accepted the kind offer.  

1929
03:32:03,760 --> 03:32:08,000
But when they were collecting the 
Scriptures, some of the paper stuck  

1930
03:32:08,000 --> 03:32:15,760
to the rock, and part of the last sheet of paper 
was lost. That is why it is incomplete today.  

1931
03:32:16,640 --> 03:32:22,640
And still today you can find some writing 
on the Rock Where the Scriptures Were Dried.

1932
03:32:24,560 --> 03:32:30,480
Tripitaka was very upset. 'We were 
not careful enough,' he said sadly.

1933
03:32:31,520 --> 03:32:38,960
'Don't get yourself so upset,' said Monkey. 'These 
Scriptures are now as they are supposed to be.  

1934
03:32:39,760 --> 03:32:46,080
Heaven and Earth are not more complete. The 
missing part is a secret and it is not meant  

1935
03:32:46,080 --> 03:32:52,399
to be read by others. You were as careful 
as you needed to be. You did nothing wrong.'

1936
03:32:54,160 --> 03:33:02,000
Back at the farm, they were welcomed by everybody 
there, young and old, and given all the best wine  

1937
03:33:02,000 --> 03:33:10,319
and food. As a Buddha, though, Tripitaka had 
lost his taste for earthly food, and Monkey  

1938
03:33:10,319 --> 03:33:18,319
wanted only fruit. Sandy ate very little, 
and even Pigsy ate less than he had before.

1939
03:33:18,319 --> 03:33:23,599
'I do not know why I cannot 
eat more,' he said sadly.

1940
03:33:25,760 --> 03:33:34,080
After they had eaten, Mr Ch'en said, 'We have had 
some pictures painted of you. We wanted to thank  

1941
03:33:34,080 --> 03:33:42,239
you for saving War Boy and Much Gold.' Then War 
Boy and Much Gold came into the room and bowed.  

1942
03:33:42,880 --> 03:33:48,560
The pilgrims were invited to look at pictures 
of themselves in the upstairs room of the farm.

1943
03:33:49,600 --> 03:33:56,800
'Yours is very like you,' said Pigsy, 
pushing his elbow gently into Monkey's side.

1944
03:33:57,439 --> 03:34:00,960
'I think yours is wonderfully like you too,'  

1945
03:34:00,960 --> 03:34:07,439
said Sandy to Pigsy. 'But the Master's 
painting is a little too handsome, really.'

1946
03:34:08,720 --> 03:34:11,920
'I think it is very good,' said Tripitaka.

1947
03:34:13,040 --> 03:34:17,680
The brothers Ch'en and all their workers 
prayed to these pictures every day.

1948
03:34:18,399 --> 03:34:22,879
Since their prayers had started, there 
had been no more damage from rain  

1949
03:34:22,880 --> 03:34:25,120
and everybody had had plenty to eat.

1950
03:34:26,479 --> 03:34:33,120
'That is a gift from Heaven, not from us,' said 
Monkey. 'But we will certainly try to protect you.  

1951
03:34:33,920 --> 03:34:38,160
You will have many children and those 
children will have many children.  

1952
03:34:38,800 --> 03:34:44,640
Your animals will grow fat, and the wind and 
the rain will come at the right time of year.'

1953
03:34:45,840 --> 03:34:50,960
The people thanked him again. And 
again they offered more fruit and cake.

1954
03:34:51,920 --> 03:35:01,040
'It is my bad luck,' said Pigsy. 'I used 
to be able to eat a lot, but in those days  

1955
03:35:01,040 --> 03:35:09,840
no one pushed food on me. Now I eat very 
little and everybody wants to see me eat more!'  

1956
03:35:11,200 --> 03:35:14,639
Because he did not want to 
insult the Ch'en family,  

1957
03:35:14,640 --> 03:35:20,960
Pigsy managed to eat eight or nine dishes 
of vegetables and twenty or thirty cakes.

1958
03:35:22,560 --> 03:35:30,640
It was now late at night. Tripitaka watched the 
Scriptures but he felt nervous. 'I think we should  

1959
03:35:30,640 --> 03:35:37,840
leave,' he told Monkey. 'If we stay here too 
long, people will try to get our secrets from us.'

1960
03:35:38,640 --> 03:35:44,161
'I agree with you,' said Monkey. 'We had better 
go quietly while everyone is still asleep.'

1961
03:35:45,920 --> 03:35:53,440
Pigsy was not a fool now. Sandy and the horse 
clearly saw the need to go too. And as the  

1962
03:35:53,439 --> 03:35:59,599
pilgrims left the farm, a sweet-smelling 
wind took them up and away on a cloud.

1963
03:36:00,960 --> 03:36:06,239
In the morning, the villagers came again 
with offers of fruit and other special food.  

1964
03:36:07,279 --> 03:36:12,000
It was a terrible surprise when they 
found that the pilgrims had disappeared.  

1965
03:36:12,800 --> 03:36:18,160
They looked everywhere for them, but 
after a few hours they gave up hope.

1966
03:36:19,359 --> 03:36:26,319
'Why have you taken our living Buddha away?' 
they cried to the God of Continuing Days.

1967
03:36:28,399 --> 03:36:34,160
Since that time, four times a year, the 
villagers have performed a special dance  

1968
03:36:34,160 --> 03:36:40,960
in front of the pictures of the Master and his 
followers. The farm has been turned into a temple  

1969
03:36:41,520 --> 03:36:48,400
and at every hour of every day there are people 
praying on their knees there. Some pray for better  

1970
03:36:48,399 --> 03:36:54,639
health, some pray for protection on a journey 
and others pray for their children's future.

1971
03:36:56,160 --> 03:37:02,960
Less than a day after they left Ch'en's farm, the 
pilgrims could see in the distance the towers of  

1972
03:37:02,960 --> 03:37:09,359
Ch'ang-an. It was thirteen years and 
nine months since Tripitaka had departed.

1973
03:37:10,479 --> 03:37:15,679
The Emperor had ordered a high tower 
to be built outside the western gates  

1974
03:37:15,680 --> 03:37:23,600
and had named it the Scripture Lookout Tower. 
And now, looking out, he suddenly saw the whole  

1975
03:37:23,600 --> 03:37:31,121
western sky fill with a magic light. A minute 
later, he noticed a sweet smell in the wind.

1976
03:37:32,000 --> 03:37:36,080
The Protectors went with the pilgrims 
as far as the gates of the city.

1977
03:37:37,520 --> 03:37:44,240
'We prefer to wait here for you,' they said 
to Tripitaka. 'The people around here are very  

1978
03:37:44,239 --> 03:37:50,319
tricky. We do not want them to know that we are 
here. And there is no need for your followers  

1979
03:37:50,319 --> 03:37:58,239
to go with you. But you, Master, had better go 
at once and give the Emperor the Scriptures.  

1980
03:37:58,239 --> 03:38:04,399
We will wait for you here and then we will all 
go back and report to Buddha's Holy Mountain.'

1981
03:38:06,000 --> 03:38:10,880
'That sounds fine,' said Monkey. 'But 
how can the Master carry the Scriptures  

1982
03:38:11,439 --> 03:38:15,279
and who is going to lead his 
horse? We had better go with him.'

1983
03:38:16,800 --> 03:38:23,760
'Kuan-yin promised Buddha that the whole journey 
would take only eight days. If you all go,  

1984
03:38:24,319 --> 03:38:30,000
Pigsy will be looking around for food, and you 
will lose time,' said one of the Protectors.

1985
03:38:30,720 --> 03:38:37,600
'How can you be so rude?' cried 
Pigsy. 'Why should I waste time here?  

1986
03:38:38,160 --> 03:38:42,960
I am as anxious as anyone to get 
back to Buddha's Holy Mountain.  

1987
03:38:43,520 --> 03:38:51,760
The Master has become a Buddha and I intend 
to become a Buddha too. You wait here. When  

1988
03:38:51,760 --> 03:38:58,640
we have given the Emperor the Scriptures, I 
will go back with you and will get my reward.'

1989
03:39:00,560 --> 03:39:07,680
Then, with Pigsy carrying the luggage, Sandy 
leading the horse and Monkey at Tripitaka's side,  

1990
03:39:07,680 --> 03:39:09,760
they stopped in front of the tower.

1991
03:39:10,800 --> 03:39:14,400
The Emperor and his ministers 
came down to meet them.

1992
03:39:15,520 --> 03:39:24,560
'So my dear brother has come at last!' the Emperor 
cried, giving him a horse to ride into the city.

1993
03:39:25,920 --> 03:39:30,880
When they were seated in the Great Hall, the 
Scriptures were put in front of the Emperor.  

1994
03:39:31,840 --> 03:39:36,160
Tripitaka told the story of how 
he arrived at the Holy Mountain.  

1995
03:39:37,199 --> 03:39:42,559
He told of the trick played by Buddha's 
two followers. He described how he had,  

1996
03:39:42,560 --> 03:39:48,000
in the end, got the written Scriptures 
by giving his golden bowl as a gift.

1997
03:39:49,120 --> 03:39:53,920
'There are, in total, five thousand 
and forty-eight chapters,' he added.

1998
03:39:54,640 --> 03:40:02,800
The Emperor was very happy and he ordered a 
banquet. Suddenly, he noticed the three pilgrims,  

1999
03:40:02,800 --> 03:40:07,680
who were sitting at the far end of the 
Hall. He thought they looked unusual.

2000
03:40:09,120 --> 03:40:13,920
'I suppose these gentlemen are 
foreigners?' said the Emperor.

2001
03:40:15,359 --> 03:40:19,839
'My oldest follower, named 
Monkey,' said Tripitaka,  

2002
03:40:19,840 --> 03:40:24,239
'came from the Cave of the Water Curtain 
on the Mountain of Flowers and Fruit.  

2003
03:40:25,040 --> 03:40:30,560
Five hundred years ago he made trouble 
in Heaven and Buddha sent him to a stone  

2004
03:40:30,560 --> 03:40:37,200
prison under a mountain. But he became a holy 
man with the help of the Goddess Kuan-yin.

2005
03:40:38,160 --> 03:40:44,239
I was able to free him and take him with 
me as my follower. He protected me on the  

2006
03:40:44,239 --> 03:40:51,279
journey to India and he helped me to get the 
Scriptures. Without him, I would not be here now.

2007
03:40:52,720 --> 03:40:58,160
'My second follower, Pigsy, 
came from the Cloud-Ladder Cave  

2008
03:40:58,160 --> 03:41:06,080
and was at the farm of Mr Kao when I found him. 
He has carried the luggage all through our travels  

2009
03:41:06,080 --> 03:41:09,600
and he was very helpful when 
we had to get across rivers.

2010
03:41:11,120 --> 03:41:15,680
'My third follower, Sandy, 
came from the River of Sands.  

2011
03:41:16,319 --> 03:41:24,239
He too was brought to me by the Goddess Kuan-yin. 
And our horse is not the one that you gave to me.'

2012
03:41:25,120 --> 03:41:31,439
'Really?' said the Emperor. 'It looks the 
same to me. Why did you change horses?'

2013
03:41:32,560 --> 03:41:41,200
'Actually,' said Tripitaka, 'my first horse was 
eaten by this one. But Monkey went to Kuan-yin and  

2014
03:41:41,199 --> 03:41:47,439
the Goddess explained that this horse was really 
a son of the Dragon King of the Western Ocean.  

2015
03:41:48,080 --> 03:41:56,080
He got into some trouble, but he took me to the 
West and so his life was saved. He has carried me  

2016
03:41:56,080 --> 03:42:03,359
well, over the most difficult hills and 
mountains. On the way there, I rode on its back;  

2017
03:42:04,080 --> 03:42:11,600
on the way home, it carried the Scriptures. As 
you can imagine, we are all very grateful to him.'

2018
03:42:12,880 --> 03:42:21,120
'You have been served well. Tell me,' said 
the Emperor, 'how far is it to India?'

2019
03:42:22,319 --> 03:42:26,000
'I know only that the summer 
turned to winter fourteen times.  

2020
03:42:26,720 --> 03:42:32,880
There was no day when we did not ride over 
hills or mountains. Often we rode through  

2021
03:42:32,880 --> 03:42:39,359
large forests or crossed great rivers and we 
passed through too many countries to count.'

2022
03:42:41,840 --> 03:42:44,720
When the banquet was ready, the Emperor asked,  

2023
03:42:45,439 --> 03:42:50,199
'Do your followers know how to 
behave at an Emperor's banquet?'

2024
03:42:50,199 --> 03:42:57,040
'I am afraid that they do not,' said 
Tripitaka. 'They have spent their time  

2025
03:42:57,040 --> 03:42:59,519
mostly in rough country conditions.'

2026
03:43:00,399 --> 03:43:07,439
'Don't worry,' said the Emperor. 'I will not 
blame them. Tell them to come to the banquet.'

2027
03:43:09,279 --> 03:43:16,000
There was dancing and singing and music and food 
at the banquet, and it was a very happy day.  

2028
03:43:16,960 --> 03:43:23,359
In the evening, when the meal ended, the pilgrims 
went to Tripitaka's old temple in the woods.  

2029
03:43:24,239 --> 03:43:27,599
There the priests welcomed them with a bow.

2030
03:43:28,800 --> 03:43:33,840
This time, inside the temple, 
Pigsy did not shout for more food  

2031
03:43:34,399 --> 03:43:41,920
and Monkey and Sandy behaved perfectly. 
All three were now Spirits of Wisdom,  

2032
03:43:42,479 --> 03:43:48,799
and it was not difficult for them to stay 
quiet. When night came, they all went to sleep.

2033
03:43:50,239 --> 03:43:55,120
Early next morning, the Emperor 
woke and called for his secretaries.

2034
03:43:56,319 --> 03:44:01,519
'All night I could not sleep because 
I was thinking of good enough words  

2035
03:44:01,520 --> 03:44:08,880
to thank my brother for his success. I 
have now, in my head, a few sentences,  

2036
03:44:09,439 --> 03:44:13,759
although they are nothing compared 
to the wisdom of the Scriptures.'

2037
03:44:15,439 --> 03:44:18,399
He asked the secretaries to write down his words,  

2038
03:44:18,960 --> 03:44:25,040
which later became known to all as the 
Introduction to Buddha's Holy Teachings.

2039
03:44:26,960 --> 03:44:33,359
The Emperor then asked Tripitaka to read from 
some of the Holy Scriptures in the holiest  

2040
03:44:33,359 --> 03:44:40,559
temple in the city. As the Scriptures were so 
valuable, the Emperor ordered his secretaries  

2041
03:44:40,560 --> 03:44:46,161
to make copies, which were later 
sent to every city in China.

2042
03:44:47,760 --> 03:44:54,560
As Tripitaka started reading, he smelled the 
sweet wind and the Protectors appeared in the  

2043
03:44:54,560 --> 03:45:03,200
air above the pilgrims. They said, 'You must all 
leave the Scriptures and follow us to the West.'

2044
03:45:04,560 --> 03:45:12,320
At once Monkey and the others, including the white 
horse, got up from the ground. Tripitaka put down  

2045
03:45:12,319 --> 03:45:18,160
the Scripture that he had started reading. He 
was lifted straight up to the Ninth Heaven.  

2046
03:45:19,120 --> 03:45:24,160
The Emperor and his ministers bowed low 
to the ground as they were carried away.

2047
03:45:25,600 --> 03:45:28,800
Later, all the people of the city prayed  

2048
03:45:28,800 --> 03:45:34,080
and read the Great Scriptures, and 
their lives were much better after that.

2049
03:45:35,439 --> 03:45:41,120
The four pilgrims and the white horse 
were taken back to Buddha's Holy Mountain  

2050
03:45:41,120 --> 03:45:49,359
by the Protectors. There they found that 
their great journey had taken just eight days.  

2051
03:45:50,239 --> 03:45:55,279
On the Holy Mountain they and 
all the Gods waited for Buddha.

2052
03:45:57,120 --> 03:46:02,720
When everyone was ready, Buddha 
appeared and spoke first to Tripitaka.

2053
03:46:03,920 --> 03:46:12,399
'Holy priest,' he said, 'in a past life you 
were close to me and you were called Golden  

2054
03:46:12,399 --> 03:46:21,359
Tree. But because you did not obey my teaching, 
you had to start life again in the East. Now you  

2055
03:46:21,359 --> 03:46:30,559
have obeyed me so well that I am making you a 
Buddha. Your title will be Buddha of Ability.

2056
03:46:32,080 --> 03:46:39,920
'Monkey, because you made trouble in Heaven, you 
were put under the Mountain of Metal, Wood, Water,  

2057
03:46:39,920 --> 03:46:48,239
Fire and Earth. Fortunately, when your time there 
was finished, you turned your heart to religion,  

2058
03:46:48,800 --> 03:46:57,120
to the fight against wrongdoing and the fight for 
good. On your recent journey you have done so well  

2059
03:46:57,760 --> 03:47:05,840
that I am making you a Buddha. You will be 
the Buddha of Success in Difficult Times.

2060
03:47:08,000 --> 03:47:16,239
'Pigsy, you were a soldier of the water armies 
of Heaven. But at a banquet you drank too much  

2061
03:47:16,239 --> 03:47:21,599
and insulted a goddess. And for this 
you were born again in the human world,  

2062
03:47:22,160 --> 03:47:28,559
looking very much like an animal. When 
you were living at the Cloud-Ladder Cave,  

2063
03:47:28,560 --> 03:47:36,800
you found religion and offered your protection to 
Tripitaka on his journey. You are still greedy,  

2064
03:47:37,520 --> 03:47:45,840
but because you carried the luggage all the way, I 
am now making you the Keeper of the Holy Temple.'

2065
03:47:46,880 --> 03:47:54,800
'Hey!' said Pigsy. 'You have just made the 
others Buddhas. Why am I not a Buddha too?'

2066
03:47:56,000 --> 03:48:03,199
'Because,' answered Buddha, 'your conversation 
and appearance are still not fine enough  

2067
03:48:03,760 --> 03:48:10,560
and you still eat too much. But I 
have so many followers in the world  

2068
03:48:10,560 --> 03:48:17,680
that you will get plenty to eat in your new 
job. You will have nothing to complain about.'

2069
03:48:19,359 --> 03:48:24,559
Pigsy knew that he had to accept his 
new job. He did not say another word.

2070
03:48:26,319 --> 03:48:34,399
'Sandy, you were a great spirit, but at a banquet 
you broke a dish of great value and you were sent  

2071
03:48:34,399 --> 03:48:41,839
to the human world. There you lived in the 
River of Sands and you hungrily ate people.  

2072
03:48:42,800 --> 03:48:51,920
But after that you found religion. You promised to 
protect and help Tripitaka, and you did. Because  

2073
03:48:51,920 --> 03:49:00,880
of this, I am lifting you high among us and 
giving you the title of Golden-Bodied Soldier.'

2074
03:49:02,399 --> 03:49:06,719
Sandy bowed. Happily, he accepted his new title.

2075
03:49:08,399 --> 03:49:16,559
Then Buddha turned to the white horse. 'You,' 
he said, 'were a child of the Dragon King of  

2076
03:49:16,560 --> 03:49:25,280
the Western Ocean, but you disobeyed your father 
and were guilty of bad behaviour. Fortunately,  

2077
03:49:25,840 --> 03:49:31,680
you found religion. Because you 
carried Tripitaka to the West,  

2078
03:49:31,680 --> 03:49:37,840
and the Holy Scriptures on the return 
journey, you too must have your reward.  

2079
03:49:39,040 --> 03:49:44,880
From this day, you will be one 
of the eight Heavenly Dragons.'

2080
03:49:46,399 --> 03:49:49,599
The white horse made a sign 
to show how grateful it was.  

2081
03:49:50,319 --> 03:49:55,840
It was led to the back of the Holy Mountain, 
where there was the Pool of Magic Dragons,  

2082
03:49:55,840 --> 03:50:03,440
and it was pushed into the pool. After a short 
time, it began to change shape and its coat began  

2083
03:50:03,439 --> 03:50:12,639
to change to a golden colour. Its four feet rested 
on the clouds and then it flew up out of the pool.  

2084
03:50:13,439 --> 03:50:17,679
It was now changed from a horse to a magic dragon.

2085
03:50:19,040 --> 03:50:24,479
'Master,' said Monkey to Tripitaka, 
'I am now a Buddha, like you.  

2086
03:50:25,359 --> 03:50:28,639
I should not have to wear a cap 
so that you can control me.'

2087
03:50:29,920 --> 03:50:37,440
'It was put on you,' said Tripitaka, 'at a time 
when you knew nothing. Then we needed to control  

2088
03:50:37,439 --> 03:50:47,839
you. Now you are a Buddha and it has gone. Feel 
your head and you will see. It is not there now.'

2089
03:50:49,199 --> 03:50:53,199
Monkey put his hand on his 
head. Tripitaka was right;  

2090
03:50:53,920 --> 03:50:59,760
the cap had gone. A grateful 
smile spread across his face.

2091
03:51:01,120 --> 03:51:05,840
All the spirits of Heaven 
watched as Tripitaka, Monkey,

2092
03:51:05,840 --> 03:51:11,040
Pigsy, Sandy and the horse 
received their new, holy titles.

2093
03:51:12,160 --> 03:51:15,359
While they went to their places in the Great Hall,  

2094
03:51:15,359 --> 03:51:21,519
many loud voices began to pray to them. 
They were accepted with open arms.  

2095
03:51:22,319 --> 03:51:31,199
And from that day, Pigsy did not shout for more 
food and Monkey and Sandy behaved perfectly.  

2096
03:51:32,319 --> 03:51:39,920
The reason for this was simple. All three 
had received the greatest of gifts - wisdom.

2097
03:51:41,840 --> 03:51:49,120
I give this, my book, to you, dear reader, so 
you can understand the beauty of Buddha's Land.  

2098
03:51:49,920 --> 03:51:53,840
It will be a reward for kindness, and it will help  

2099
03:51:53,840 --> 03:52:00,560
with the suffering of the lost souls of this 
world. I would like to think that my readers  

2100
03:52:00,560 --> 03:52:11,840
will turn their hearts towards the True Way, and 
will be born again in the World of True Happiness.

